Baddeck , And That Sort of Thing is a travel journal written by Charles Dudley Warner , the American author who co - wrote The Gilded Age :
The Fire Eternal is a 2007 novel by English author , Chris d'Lacey .
Mr Darwin 's Shooter is a 1998 novel by Roger McDonald .
Vote for Larry is a comedic political fictional romantic novel by Janet Tashjian .
`` Everyday Use '' is a widely studied and frequently anthologized short story by Alice Walker .
Harmful Intent ( 1990 ) is a novel by Robin Cook .
Chronicles of Wormwood is a six - part comic book limited series written by Garth Ennis , drawn by Jacen Burrows , and colored by Andrew Dalhouse .
Alexandre le Grand is a tragedy in 5 acts ( of 3 , 5 , 7 , 5 and 3 scenes , respectively ) and verse by Jean Racine .
Prentice Alvin ( 1989 ) is an alternate history / fantasy novel by Orson Scott Card .
All Alone in the Universe is a children 's novel by American author Lynne Rae Perkins .
The Physical Principles of the Quantum Theory ( German : Physikalische Prinzipien der Quantentheorie ) by Nobel laureate ( 1932 ) Werner Heisenberg and subsequently translated by Carl Eckart and Frank C. Hoyt .
Dick Sand , A Captain at Fifteen ( French : Un capitaine de quinze ans ) is a Jules Verne novel published in 1878 .
Danny Deever is an 1890 poem by Rudyard Kipling , one of the first of the Barrack - Room Ballads .
La vida inútil de Pito Pérez is a novel by Mexican author José Rubén Romero following the picaresque genre .
Fefu and Her Friends was the fourteenth play by Cuban American playwright María Irene Fornés , originally written and produced in 1977 .
Las fuerzas extrañas ( Spanish for : The Strange Forces ) is a collection of short stories by Argentine writer Leopoldo Lugones , first published in 1906 .
Disgrace is a novel by J. M. Coetzee , published in 1999 .
On Certainty ( German : Über Gewißheit ) is a philosophical book composed from the notes written by Ludwig Wittgenstein just prior to his death .
The Lady in the Morgue ( 1936 ) is one of the novels by Jonathan Latimer featuring private detective William Crane .
Until Thy Wrath Be Past ( Swedish : Till dess din vrede upphör ) is a 2008 crime novel by Swedish writer Åsa Larsson , fourth in the Rebecka Martinsson series .
God 's Spy is a 2007 bestselling thriller novel by Juan Gómez - Jurado originally published in Spain .
The Disinherited is a proletarian novel written by Jack Conroy .
Number 31328 ( Greek : Το Νούμερο 31328 ) is an autobiographical novel by Elias Venezis .
Around the World in Seventy - Two Days is a book by journalist Elizabeth Jane Cochrane , writing under her pseudonym , Nellie Bly .
Os Flagelados do Vento Leste ( Portuguese meaning `` The Victims Of The East Wind '' ) is a novel published in 1960 by Cape Verdean author Manuel Lopes .
Flyy Girl is young adult / new adult literature and an urban fiction book written by Omar Tyree .
Do n't Let the Pigeon Stay Up Late ! is a bestselling children 's picture book by Mo Willems .
The Valkyries ( Portuguese : As Valkírias ; ISBN 978 - 0062513342 ) is a 1992 novel by Paulo Coelho .
Set This House on Fire is a novel by William Styron , set in a small village of the Amalfi coast in Italy , centred on the themes of evil and redemption .
The Spiritual Canticle ( Cántico Espiritual ) , is one of the poetic works of the Spanish mystical poet St. John of the Cross .
The Five Gold Bands is an early science fiction novel by Jack Vance , first published in the November 1950 issue of Startling Stories magazine .
Corrie ! is a comedy stage play written in 2010 by award - winning playwright and Coronation Street scriptwriter Jonathan Harvey .
`` A Predicament '' is a humorous short story by Edgar Allan Poe , usually combined with its companion piece `` How to Write a Blackwood Article . ''
A Confederate General from Big Sur is Richard Brautigan 's first novel , published in 1964 .
The Virgin 's Lover is a historical novel written by British author Philippa Gregory .
For Love of the Game is a novel by American author Michael Shaara , published posthumously in 1991 .
Le Papillon des étoiles ( The Butterfly of the Stars ) is a 2006 novel by French author Bernard Werber .
The Natural Economic Order ( German : Die natürliche Wirtschaftsordnung durch Freiland und Freigeld ; published in Bern in 1916 ) is considered Silvio Gesell 's most important book .
`` The Ruum '' is a 1953 short story with a pursuit theme by the American author Arthur Porges and is probably his best known work .
The Stolen Bacillus and Other Incidents is a collection of fifteen fantasy and science fiction short stories written by the English author H. G. Wells between 1893 and 1895 .
Fusion Fire is a science fiction novel by Kathy Tyers originally published in 1987 , and later rewritten and republished in 2000 .
Conrad 's Fate is a children 's fantasy novel by British author Diana Wynne Jones published by Collins in 2005 .
Pedro and Me is an autobiographical graphic novel by Judd Winick regarding his friendship with AIDS educator Pedro Zamora after the two met while on the reality television series , The Real World :
The Complete Psionics Handbook was published as a 128-page softcover book by TSR , Inc. , with design by Steve Winter , and monster updates by Blake Mobley .
The Warrior of World 's End is a fantasy novel written by Lin Carter set on a decadent far - future Earth in which all the world 's land masses have supposedly drifted back together to form a last supercontinent called Gondwane .
Columbia & Britannia ( 2009 ) is an anthology of alternate history stories edited by Adam Chamberlain and Brian A. Dixon .
Religion and Nothingness ( Japanese : Shūkyō to wa Nanika ; the original title translates literally as `` What is Religion ? '' ) is a 1961 book by the Japanese philosopher Keiji Nishitani .
' A Germ - Destroyer ' is a short story by Rudyard Kipling .
Dark Princess , written by sociologist W. E. B. Du Bois in 1928 , is one of his five historical novels .
Bestiario is a book of eight short stories written by Julio Cortázar .
My Lost Mexico ( 1992 ) is a nonfiction account by American author James A. Michener about his endeavor to write a big novel about Mexico in the grand style of his other popular novels like Hawaii .
Half Past Human is a fixup science fiction novel by American author T. J. Bass , published in 1971 .
Mistress of Mellyn was the first Gothic romance novel written by Eleanor Hibbert under the pen name Victoria Holt .
The Four Loves is a book by C. S. Lewis which explores the nature of love from a Christian and philosophical perspective through thought experiments .
Double Persephone is a self - published poetry collection written by Canadian author Margaret Atwood in 1961 .
Sky - Walk ( alternatively Sky Walk , Skywalk , etc . ) is the first completed novel by Charles Brockden Brown .
My Wicked , Wicked Ways is an autobiography written by Australian actor Errol Flynn with the aid of ghostwriter Earl Conrad .
Two - Headed Poems is the eighth book of poems by Canadian author Margaret Atwood .
Myths of the Near Future is a short - story collection by J. G. Ballard , first published in 1982 .
Basic Chess Endings ( abbreviated BCE ) is a book on chess endgames which was written by Grandmaster Reuben Fine and originally published on October 27 , 1941 .
Les Burgraves is a historical play by Victor Hugo , first performed by the Comédie - Française on 7 May 1843 .
Culture and Imperialism is a collection of essays by Edward Said published in 1993 .
Everything 's Eventual is a collection of 14 short stories written by Stephen King and published in 2002 .
Book of Imaginary Beings was written by Jorge Luis Borges , published in 1957 under the original Spanish title Manual de zoología fantástica , and expanded in 1967 and 1969 in Spain to the final El libro de los seres imaginarios .
Ranger 's Apprentice is a series written by Australian author John Flanagan .
Immortality , Inc. is a 1959 science fiction novel by American writer Robert Sheckley , about a fictional process whereby a human 's consciousness may be transferred into a brain - dead body .
Paws and Whiskers is a 2014 fundraising anthology for the Battersea Dogs and Cats Home , featuring some of the best children 's stories about cats and dogs of all time , selected by multi - award - winning and best - selling children 's author Jacqueline Wilson , with illustrations by Nick Sharratt .
The Swish of the Curtain is a children 's novel by Pamela Brown ( 1924 - -1989 ) .
The Snow Empress is a 2007 mystery novel written by Laura Joh Rowland , set in the Genroku ( AD 1688 - -1704 ) of historical Japan It is the 12th book in the Sano Ichiro series .
Two Sought Adventure is a 1957 collection of fantasy short stories by Fritz Leiber .
Islam and the West is a 1993 book written by Middle - East historian and scholar Bernard Lewis .
The Stars ' Tennis Balls is a psychological thriller novel by Stephen Fry , first published in 2000 .
The Wallet of Kai Lung is a collection of fantasy stories by Ernest Bramah , all but the last of which feature Kai Lung , an itinerant story - teller of ancient China .
The Quants is the debut New York Times best selling book by Wall Street journalist Scott Patterson .
Learned Pigs & Fireproof Women is a book written by stage magician , actor and writer Ricky Jay .
`` The Day Before the Revolution '' is a Nebula Award - winning short story by Ursula K. Le Guin , first published in 1974 .
The Goops books , originally published between 1900 and 1950 , were created by the artist , art critic , poet , author and humorist Gelett Burgess .
The Morning of the Magicians , first published as Le Matin des magiciens , was written by Louis Pauwels and Jacques Bergier in 1960 .
The Law and the Lady is a detective story , published in 1875 by Wilkie Collins .
The Crisis and a Crisis in the Life of an Actress ( Danish : Krisen og en Krise i en Skuespillerindes Liv ) was a series of articles written by the Danish philosopher Søren Kierkegaard in 1847 and published in the Danish newspaper Fædrelandet ( The Fatherland ) in 1848 under the pseudonym Inter et Inter .
Mildred Keith is a children 's novel series written by Martha Finley ( 1828 - 1909 ) between 1876 and 1894 .
The Third Culture is a 1995 book by John Brockman which discusses the work of several well - known scientists who are directly communicating their new , sometimes provocative , ideas to the general public .
Smarakasilakal ( Malayalam : സ്മാരകശിലകൾ , English : Memorial Stones ) is a Malayalam novel written by Punathil Kunjabdulla in 1977 .
The Poverty of Historicism is a 1957 book by philosopher Karl Popper , in which he seeks to persuade the reader of both the danger and the bankruptcy of the idea of historicism .
Abaddon 's Gate is a science fiction novel by James S. A. Corey ( pen name of Daniel Abraham and Ty Franck ) .
Remedia Amoris ( Love 's Remedy or The Cure for Love ) is an 814-line poem in Latin by Roman poet Ovid .
If They Give You Lined Paper , Write Sideways is a book by Daniel Quinn , author of Ishmael .
The Wheel of Darkness is a novel by Douglas Preston and Lincoln Child released on August 28 , 2007 by Grand Central Publishing .
Return to the Field ( 歸田賦 ) is a literary work written in the Chinese style known as a rhapsody , or fu style : it is by Zhang Heng ( AD 78 - -139 ) , an official , inventor , mathematician , and astronomer of the Han Dynasty of China ( 202 BC--220 AD ) .
Written in the late 19th century by H. G. Wells and first published in The Butterfly ( September 1899 ) , ( and collected in The Obliterated Man and Other Stories , ( Dec 1925 ) ) A Vision of Judgment is a short story in 9 sections .
Bloodchild and Other Stories is the only and rather brief collection of science fiction stories and essays by Octavia E. Butler .
The Enemy Stars , written by Poul Anderson , is a science - fiction novel published in 1959 by J.B Lippincott in the US and by Longmans in Canada .
The Bomber ( Swedish : Sprängaren ) is a crime novel by Liza Marklund about her heroine Annika Bengtzon .
DisneyWar is an exposé of Michael Eisner 's 20-year tenure as chairman and CEO at The Walt Disney Company by James B. Stewart .
Cry of Morning is a novel by the English - born author , Brian Cleeve .
The Door Below is a collection of fantasy and horror and mystery short stories by author Hugh B. Cave .
`` Extempore '' ( alternate title `` The Beach Where Time Began '' ) is a science fiction short story written by Damon Knight .
Assassin 's Quest is a 1997 fantasy novel by Robin Hobb , the third in her Farseer Trilogy and follows the exploits of FitzChilvalry Farseer .
The Rise of Mormonism is a 2005 book by the sociologist of religions Rodney Stark .
Monster Nation ( 2005 ) is a serial novel by David Wellington .
The Question Concerning Technology ( German : Die Frage nach der Technik ) is a work by Martin Heidegger seeking to derive the essence of technology and humanity 's role .
The Chequer Board is a novel by Nevil Shute , first published in the United Kingdom in 1947 by William Heinemann Ltd. The novel deals fairly with the question of racism within the US forces during World War II and portrays black characters with great sympathy and support .
The Still Alarm is a melodramatic play by Joseph Arthur that debuted in New York in 1887 and enjoyed great success , and was adapted to silent films in 1911 , 1918 , and 1926 .
Champions of Valor was published in November 2005 , and was designed by Thomas M. Reid and Sean K. Reynolds .
A Lineage of Grace is a series of five historical fiction novellas written by the American author Francine Rivers .
The Tibetan Book of Living and Dying , written by Sogyal Rinpoche in 1992 , is a presentation of the teachings of Tibetan Buddhism based on the Tibetan Book of the Dead or Bardo Thodol .
The Degrees of Knowledge ( French : Distinguer pour unir , ou Les Degrés du Savoir ) is a 1932 book by Jacques Maritain , his major contribution to epistemology .
Eloise in Moscow is the fourth of the Eloise series of children 's books written by Kay Thompson and illustrated by Hilary Knight .
Tutankhamun and the Daughter of Ra is a novel written by Moyra Caldecott in 1989 .
Did Marco Polo Go to China ? is a 1995 book by Frances Wood , arguing that Venetian explorer Marco Polo never visited China as told , but travelled no further than Persia , basing his description of China on accounts from Persian travellers .
Satori in Paris is a 1966 novella by American novelist and poet Jack Kerouac .
Der perfekte Mord , published in 1961 , is a detective fiction novel written by German author Frank Arnau .
The Confessions of a Young Man ( 1886 in French ; 1888 in English ) is a memoir by Irish novelist George Moore who spent about 15 years in his teens and 20s in Paris and later London as a struggling artist .
Northworld is a 1990 militaristic science fiction novel by David Drake set in a time when the Consensus rules everything except for Northworld , the missing planet .
Asimov 's Chronology of the World by Isaac Asimov explains in chronological order important events that happened in our world from the Big Bang until the end of World War II . Each chapter covers a certain time period .
A Presumption of Death is a mystery novel by Jill Paton Walsh , based loosely on The Wimsey Papers by Dorothy L. Sayers .
The Shahnameh , also transliterated as Shahnama ( Persian : شاهنامه‎‎ pronounced ( ʃɒːhnɒːˈme ) , `` The Book of Kings '' ) , is a long epic poem written by the Persian poet Ferdowsi between c. 977 and 1010 CE and is the national epic of Greater Iran .
Wide Sargasso Sea is a 1966 postcolonial novel by Dominica - born British author Jean Rhys .
The War that Time Forgot was a comic book feature published by DC Comics beginning in 1960 in the title Star Spangled War Stories , created by Robert Kanigher , Ross Andru and Mike Esposito .
`` The Battler '' is a short story written by Ernest Hemingway , published in the 1925 New York edition of In Our Time , by Boni & Liveright .
The three - volume Res gestae saxonicae sive annalium libri tres ( `` The Deeds of the Saxons , or Three Books of Annals '' ) is a chronicle of 10th century Germany written by Widukind of Corvey .
How the Self Controls Its Brain is a book by Sir John Eccles , proposing a theory of philosophical dualism , and offering a justification of how there can be mind - brain action without violating the principle of the conservation of energy .
Justin Morgan Had a Horse is a children 's historical novel by Marguerite Henry , illustrated by Wesley Dennis and published by Wilcox & Follett of Chicago in 1945 .
Uhritulet ( Finnish : The Sacrificial Fires ) is a historical novel by Finnish author Kaari Utrio .
Catechismus in der windischenn Sprach or shortly Catechismus ( Catechism , also known as Katekizem v slovenskem jeziku or shortly Katekizem in modern Slovene ) , is a book written by the Slovene Protestant preacher Primož Trubar in 1550 .
`` Robot AL-76 Goes Astray '' is a humorous science fiction short story by Isaac Asimov , originally published in the February 1942 issue of Amazing Stories and included in the collections The Rest of the Robots ( 1964 ) and The Complete Robot ( 1982 ) .
The Septembers of Shiraz ( 2007 ) is a critically acclaimed debut novel by Iranian American author Dalia Sofer .
Redemptoris custos ( Guardian of the Redeemer ) is the title of an apostolic exhortation by Pope John Paul II on Saint Joseph .
My Present Age is the title of a Canadian novel by Guy Vanderhaeghe which was first published in 1984 .
A Semester in the Life of a Garbage Bag is a novel by Gordon Korman , a Canadian - born author who now lives in New York City .
Masters of Time is a collection of two science fiction novellas by author A. E. van Vogt .
Horse Under Water ( 1963 , ISBN 0 - 399 - 10419 - 4 ) is the second of four Len Deighton spy novels featuring an unnamed British agent protagonist ( named Harry Palmer in the film adaptions ) .
Warbreaker is a stand - alone fantasy novel written by American author Brandon Sanderson .
The Willows at Christmas is a children 's novel by English writer William Horwood , first published in 1999 .
Anna of the Five Towns is a novel by Arnold Bennett , first published in 1902 and one of his best - known works .
Miss Viola Swamp is styled `` the meanest substitute teacher in the whole world '' , in three children 's picture books by Harry Allard and illustrated by James Marshall :
The American Girl ( Swedish : Den amerikanska flickan ) is a 2005 novel by author Monika Fagerholm .
Reach for Tomorrow ( ISBN 0 - 345 - 32651 - 2 ) is a collection of short stories by science fiction writer Arthur C. Clarke .
The Spirit of Dorsai is a collection of two science fiction stories by Gordon R. Dickson .
In the DVD commentary , Frank Miller indicated that he was initially motivated to write That Yellow Bastard after his disappointment with The Dead Pool , the fifth and final film in the Dirty Harry series .
Deep Secret is a fantasy novel by Diana Wynne Jones , published by Gollancz in 1997 .
The Lies of Locke Lamora is a 2006 fantasy novel by Scott Lynch , the first book of the Gentleman Bastard series .
Perverzion is a novel written by Ukrainian author Yuri Andrukhovych .
Firefox Down is a 1983 novel by author Craig Thomas .
The Legacy of Muslim Rule in India is a book by the historian K. S. Lal published in 1992 .
The Absence of War is a play by English playwright David Hare , the final installment of his trilogy about contemporary Britain .
The Web of Indian Life ( 1904 ) is a book written by Sister Nivedita .
The Last Pin is a series of mystery stories by author Howard Wandrei .
Ecclesia in America is the apostolic exhortation written by Pope John Paul II , published on 22 January 1999 .
The Unadulterated Cat by Terry Pratchett , illustrated by Gray Jolliffe , is a book written to promote what Pratchett terms the ' Real Cat ' , a cat who urinates in the flowerbeds , rips up the furniture , and eats frogs , mice and sundry other small animals .
Keeping Faith ( 1999 ) is a novel by bestselling author Jodi Picoult about a custody battle involving a seven - year - old girl who may be seeing God .
It 's Been a Good Life ( 2002 ) is a book edited by Janet Asimov .
The Courtship of Princess Leia is a 1994 bestselling Star Wars book by Dave Wolverton .
Bird Neighbors , published in 1897 , was the first major work by nature writer Neltje Blanchan .
Proposition Player was a six - issue American comic book limited series created by writer Bill Willingham and artist Paul Guinan , published by the American comic book label Vertigo imprint of DC Comics .
Trelawny of the ' Wells ' is an 1898 comic play by Arthur Wing Pinero .
`` Rogues in the House '' is one of the original short stories starring the fictional sword and sorcery hero Conan the Cimmerian , written by American author Robert E. Howard and first published in Weird Tales magazine c. January 1934 .
Notes from a Big Country , or as it was released in the United States , I 'm a Stranger Here Myself , is a collection of articles written by Bill Bryson for The Mail on Sunday 's Night and Day supplement during the 1990s , published together first in Britain in 1998 and in paperback in 1999 .
The Gray Prince is a science fiction novel by Jack Vance , first published in two parts in Amazing Science Fiction magazine ( August and October 1974 issues ) with the title The Domains of Koryphon .
The Pilgrim 's Regress is a book of allegorical fiction by C. S. Lewis .
Le Rouge et le Noir ( French pronunciation : ​(lə ʁuʒ e lə nwaʁ ) ; French for The Red and the Black ) is a historical psychological novel in two volumes by Stendhal , published in 1830 .
The Southpaw was the first of the Henry Wiggen baseball novels by Mark Harris , published in 1953 .
The Fifth Child is a short novel by the British writer Doris Lessing , first published in the United Kingdom in 1988 , and since translated into a number of languages .
Promise Not to Tell is a 2007 mystery novel with supernatural elements written by Vermont author Jennifer McMahon .
The Price of the Ticket is a collection of James Baldwin 's writing that was published in 1985 .
The Variable Man is a novella written and sold by Philip K. Dick before he had an agent .
Return of the Brute is a novel written by Irish writer Liam O'Flaherty and published in 1929 .
The Original Adventures of Hank the Cowdog by John R. Erickson is the first book in the Hank the Cowdog series for children .
Benjamin 's Crossing is a 1996 historical novel written by Jay Parini about the Jewish critic and philosopher Walter Benjamin , and his escape over the Pyrenees from Nazi occupied France into Spain .
Graphic Storytelling and Visual Narrative is a 1996 book by American cartoonist Will Eisner that provides an formal overview of comics .
`` Bluebeard '' ( French : Barbe bleue ) is a French folktale , the most famous surviving version of which was written by Charles Perrault and first published by Barbin in Paris in 1697 in Histoires ou contes du temps passé .
La Sagouine is a play written by New Brunswick author Antonine Maillet that tells the story of la Sagouine , an Acadian cleaning lady from rural New Brunswick .
Combatting Cult Mind Control is a non - fiction work by Steven Hassan described as a `` Guide to Protection , Rescue , and Recovery from Destructive Cults . ''
`` Sir Hereward and Mister Fitz Go to War Again '' is a 2007 fantasy novelette by Garth Nix .
`` Null - O '' is a 1958 science fiction short story by Philip K. Dick .
How We Decide , is a 2009 book by journalist Jonah Lehrer , that provides biological explanations of how people make decisions and offers suggestions for making better decisions .
The Discoverie of Witchcraft is a partially sceptical book published by the English gentleman Reginald Scot in 1584 , intended as an exposé of medieval witchcraft .
The Bottle Factory Outing is a 1974 novel written by Beryl Bainbridge , it was shortlisted for the Booker Prize that year , won the Guardian Fiction Prize and is regarded as one of her best .
The Bachelor Girl ( French : La Garçonne ) is a novel by Victor Margueritte first published in 1922 .
Michael Jackson 's Dangerous Liaisons is a book by the writer and paedophile activist Tom O'Carroll , writing under the pen - name Carl Toms , in which he reviews all - extensively the controversially intimate relationships of the American singer Michael Jackson with young boys .
Is That You , Herb ? is a short story by author Ray Bradbury .
Sundays at Tiffany 's is a romance novel by the authors James Patterson and Gabrielle Charbonnet released on April 29 , 2008 .
`` The Devil and Tom Walker '' is a short story by Washington Irving and King George that first appeared in their 1824 collection Tales of a Traveller , as part of the `` Money - Diggers '' section .
Groenten uit Balen is a Flemish theatre play written by author Walter van den Broeck in 1972 .
Paradise Lost is an epic poem in blank verse by the 17th - century English poet John Milton ( 1608 - -1674 ) .
Jacques the Fatalist and his Master ( French : Jacques le fataliste et son maître ) is a novel by Denis Diderot , written during the period 1765 - 1780 .
Imaginary Homelands is a collection of essays written by Salman Rushdie covering a wide variety of topics .
Goodbye , Mickey Mouse is a historical novel by Len Deighton published on October 12 , 1982 .
The Integral Trees is a 1984 science fiction novel by Larry Niven ( first published as a serial in Analog in 1983 ) .
Peter and Alexis ( Russian : Пётр и Алексей ) is a novel by Dmitry Merezhkovsky , written in 1903 - 1904 and first published in Nos . 1 - -5 , 9 - -12 , 1904 , Novy Put magazine .
Travel Scholarships ( French : Bourses de voyage ) is an 1903 adventure novel by Jules Verne .
The Man Who Went Back ( 1940 ) is an adventure novel by Warwick Deeping about a man who has a car accident in 1939 England .
A Faint Cold Fear is the third novel in the Grant County series by author Karin Slaughter .
Memorandums taken on a journey from Paris into the southern parts of France and Northern Italy , in the year 1787 , or Memoranda , is a text by Thomas Jefferson , written during a trip beginning February 28 , 1787 from France to Italy .
Uncle Cleans Up ( 1965 ) is a children 's story written by J. P. Martin as part of his Uncle series .
Clybourne Park ( 2010 ) is a play by Bruce Norris written as a spin - off to Lorraine Hansberry 's play A Raisin in the Sun ( 1959 ) .
For Kings and Planets is a 1999 novel by Ethan Canin centering on two college students at Columbia University and following them through their intertwined lives .
The Seed and the Sower is a book by South African writer Laurens van der Post , consisting of three interrelated stories blended into a novel , first published in 1963 .
Notes of a Son and Brother is an autobiography by Henry James published in 1914 .
A Pair of Aces is a collection of novellas and screenplays written by American author Joe R. Lansdale and Neal Barrett Jr. At this time it is only available as a Amazon Kindle e - book .
The Ichneutae ( Ancient Greek : Ἰχνευταί , Ichneutai , `` trackers '' ) , also known as the Searchers , Trackers or Tracking Satyrs , is a fragmentary satyr play by the fifth - century BCE Athenian dramatist Sophocles .
The Princess Mayblossom is a French literary fairy tale written by Madame d'Aulnoy in 1697 .
`` Where Love Is , God Is '' ( sometimes also translated as `` Where Love Is , There God Is Also '' or `` Martin the Cobbler '' ) is a short story by Russian author Leo Tolstoy .
Attentatet i Pålsjö skog ( Attack in Pålsjö Forest in English ) is a 1996 alternate history novel by Hans Alfredson .
Bridge of Ashes is an experimental science fiction novel by Hugo- and Nebula - award winning author , Roger Zelazny .
The Cronin Omnibus is a single volume of three A. J. Cronin novels :
The Wonder of Women or The Tragedy of Sophonisba is an early Jacobean stage play written by the satiric dramatist John Marston .
The Victorian Chaise - Longue ( 1953 ) is a novella by the English novelist Marghanita Laski .
Life of Constantine the great ( Greek : Βίος Μεγάλου Κωνσταντίνου ; Latin : Vita Constantini ) is a panegyric written in Greek in honor of Constantine the Great by Eusebius of Caeserea in the 4th century AD It was never completed due to the death of Eusebius in 339 .
William Shakespeare 's Sonnet 43 employs antithesis and paradox to highlight the speaker 's yearning for his beloved and sadness in ( most likely ) his absence , and confusion about the situation described in the previous three sonnets .
Voices of the Apalachicola is a book by Faith Eidse chronicling the history of the Apalachicola River in Northern Florida , United States .
Stop - Time , published in 1967 , is a memoir by American author Frank Conroy , and tells the story of his poor childhood and early adulthood , growing up in New York City and Florida .
Lady Audley 's Secret is a sensation novel by Mary Elizabeth Braddon published in 1862 .
Magical Beginnings is an anthology of fantasy short stories edited by Steven H. Silver and Martin H. Greenberg , first published in paperback by DAW Books in February 2003 .
Dark Apprentice is the second novel in the The Jedi Academy Trilogy by Kevin J. Anderson ; many of the events of this novel are also described from the perspective of Corran Horn in I , Jedi .
`` A Bathroom of Her Own '' is a short story by Robert A. Heinlein about a political campaign in the U.S. after World War II . Written in 1946 , it was unpublished until printed in Heinlein 's Expanded Universe ( 1980 ) .
Adventures in the Rifle Brigade is the name of two Vertigo comic book limited series created by writer Garth Ennis and artist Carlos Ezquerra .
Za trochu lásky ... is a Czech novel , written by František Kožík and published in 1997 .
I quattro libri dell'architettura ( The Four Books of Architecture ) is an Italian treatise on architecture by the architect Andrea Palladio ( 1508 - -1580 ) .
Cast of Shadows is a 2005 suspense novel by the American writer Kevin Guilfoile .
The Forgotten Soldier ( 1965 ) , originally published in French as Le soldat oublié , is an autobiographical account of Guy Sajer 's observations as a German soldier on the Eastern Front during World War II .
The contents presented in Crossing the Threshold of Hope were originally intended to be broadcast as a live television interview with Vittorio Messori , an Italian journalist and writer .
The Tragedy of Hamlet , Prince of Denmark , often shortened to Hamlet ( /ˈhæmlᵻt/ ) , is a tragedy written by William Shakespeare at an uncertain date between 1599 and 1602 .
Dead Man 's Land is a book by Robert Ryan , based in World War I. It involves Sherlock Holmes ' sidekick , Dr. Watson ( created by Arthur Conan Doyle ) .
Deadly Perfume is a 1991 thriller novel written by Gordon Thomas .
The Banner of Joan is an epic poem by H. Warner Munn .
The Vanishers is the title of a spy novel by Donald Hamilton which was first published in 1986 .
Everville is a novel by British author Clive Barker .
The Corsican Brothers ( French : Les Frères corses ) is a novella by Alexandre Dumas , père , first published in 1844 .
The Priest 's Graveyard is a thriller novel by Ted Dekker , published in April 2011 .
The High Lord is the third book in The Black Magician series by Trudi Canavan .
The Autumn Castle is a 2003 horror / fantasy novel by Kim Wilkins .
Fevre Dream is a 1982 vampire novel written by best - selling U. S. novelist George R. R. Martin .
Le Château des cœurs ( The Castle of Hearts ) was a féerie by Gustave Flaubert , published in 1880 in the review La Vie moderne under the editorship of Émile Bergerat .
Dragons ' Wrath is a novel by Justin Richards from the Virgin New Adventures starring the fictional archaeologist Bernice Summerfield .
Granny Was a Buffer Girl is a realistic young - adult novel by Berlie Doherty , published by Methuen in 1986 .
`` Venus and the Seven Sexes '' is a science - fiction story written by William Tenn in 1949 .
The First Chronicles of Druss the Legend is a fantasy novel first published in 1993 and was written by British author David Gemmell .
Fudge - a - Mania is a 1990 children 's novel by Judy Blume and the third in the Fudge series ( fourth if Otherwise Known as Sheila the Great is counted as part of the series ) .
Ormayude Arakal ( The Cells of Memory ) is a collection of memoirs by Vaikom Muhammad Basheer originally serialised in Chandrika Weekly and published as a book by National Book Stall in 1973 .
Lulu Dark Can See Through Walls is a 2005 young adult mystery novel written by Bennett Madison .
Come Like Shadows is Volume VIII of the novel sequence Alms for Oblivion by Simon Raven , published in 1972 .
The Disappearing Dwarf ( 1983 ) is James Blaylock 's second published book , and the second of the trilogy that started with The Elfin Ship .
The Road to Samarcand is a novel by English author Patrick O'Brian , published in 1954 and set in Asia during the 1930s .
Tecknens rike ( lit . The Empire of Signs ) is a 1989 book by Swedish author and sinologist Cecilia Lindqvist about the history of Chinese language writing .
Early Work is a poetry collection by Patti Smith , published in 1994 .
13 Carat Diamond and Other Stories is a collection of short stories by Khin Myo Chit .
The Wishing Game is a psychological suspense novel by Patrick Redmond .
An Experiment with an Air Pump is a play by British playwright Shelagh Stephenson inspired by the painting An Experiment on a Bird in the Air Pump by Joseph Wright .
The Phantom Blooper is a 1990 novel written by Gustav Hasford and the sequel to The Short - Timers ( 1979 ) .
`` Fading Voices '' ( Polish : `` Milknące głosy '' ) is an 1883 short story by the Polish writer Bolesław Prus , the leading representative of Realism in 19th - century Polish literature .
Elijah of Buxton is an award winning children 's novel written by Christopher Paul Curtis and published in 2007 .
Once Is Not Enough is a 1973 novel by Jacqueline Susann .
Beasts of Burden is a comic book series created by writer Evan Dorkin and artist Jill Thompson , and published by American company Dark Horse Comics .
The Sect of the Phoenix ( original Spanish title : `` La secta del Fénix '' ) is a short story by Argentine writer Jorge Luis Borges , first published in Sur in 1952 .
The Singular Life of Albert Nobbs ( French : La Vie singulière d'Albert Nobbs ) is a play by French author Simone Benmussa .
Basic Theology ( 1986 , 1999 ) is a Systematic Theology book written by Christian author Charles Caldwell Ryrie and published by Moody Publishers .
Liebe zu Böhmen ( 1972 ) is an autobiography of the interwar leading tennis player and late writer Roderich Menzel .
The Texas - Israeli War : 1999 is a 1974 science - fiction novel by Jake Saunders and Howard Waldrop .
From the Notebooks of a Middle School Princess is a 2015 children 's novel written and illustrated by Meg Cabot and a spinoff of the author 's popular young adult fiction series , The Princess Diaries .
On Love and Death is a collection of essays written by Patrick Süskind concerning the connection between `` the two elemental forces of human existence . ''
Black Workers ' Struggle for Equality in Birmingham is a 2001 book written by David Montgomery , Professor of History Emeritus at Yale University , in collaboration with Horace Huntley of the Birmingham Civil Rights Institute .
The Mystery of the Stuttering Parrot by Robert Arthur , Jr. is the second in the Three Investigators series .
Fables for the Frivolous is one of the earliest works by the American parodist Guy Wetmore Carryl .
Ika Musume ( 侵略!イカ娘 , lit . Invade ! Squid Girl ) with the subtitle The invader comes from the bottom of the sea ! , is a Japanese manga series by Masahiro Anbe , which began serialization in Weekly Shōnen Champion in July 2007 .
The Fall of the Towers is a trilogy of science fantasy books by Samuel R. Delany .
The Woman 's Bible is a two - part non - fiction book , written by Elizabeth Cady Stanton and a committee of 26 women , published in 1895 and 1898 to challenge the traditional position of religious orthodoxy that woman should be subservient to man .
Behind the Paint is the 2003 autobiography of American hip hop artist Joseph Bruce , better known as Violent J , one half of the Detroit , Michigan hip hop group Insane Clown Posse .
I Am America ( And So Can You ! ) is a 2007 satirical book by American comedian Stephen Colbert and the writers of The Colbert Report .
America , Empire of Liberty is the title of a radio series and book by historian David Reynolds about American history .
Future on Fire ( 1991 ) is a science fiction anthology edited by Orson Scott Card .
The Boy Who Dared is a 2008 novel by American children 's author Susan Campbell Bartoletti .
The Languages of Pao is a science fiction novel by Jack Vance , first published in 1958 , in which the Sapir--
Grunts ! ( 1992 ) is the satiric fantasy novel by Mary Gentle .
Delicate Edible Birds is a short story collection written by Lauren Groff .
Ray the Animation is a science fiction anime television series based on a manga by Akihito Yoshitomi .
Storm over Laos , a contemporary history was written in 1961 by Prince Sisouk na Champassak .
The Bastard of Istanbul is a 2006 novel by Turkish bestselling female author Elif Şafak , written originally in English and published by Viking Adult .
The Tragedy of Mister Morn is a verse drama by Russian novelist Vladimir Nabokov .
`` How I Met My Husband '' is a short story written by Alice Munro , first published in 1974 as a part of her collection Something I 've Been Meaning to Tell You .
The Difference Between the Democritean and Epicurean Philosophy of Nature ( German : Differenz der demokritischen und epikureischen Naturphilosophie ) is a book written by the German philosopher Karl Marx as his university thesis .
Arabia Through the Looking Glass is Jonathan Raban 's first travel book , published in 1979 , describing his travels in the Middle East , the Arab countries he visits and the people he meets along the way .
Memed , My Hawk ( Turkish : İnce Memed , meaning `` Memed , the Slim ) is a 1955 novel by Yaşar Kemal .
`` The Pool of the Black One '' is one of the original short stories starring the sword and sorcery hero Conan the Cimmerian , written by American author Robert E. Howard .
`` Little Herr Friedemann '' ( orig . German Der kleine Herr Friedemann ) is a short story by Thomas Mann .
A Carne ( in English : The Flesh ) is a 1888 Naturalist novel by Júlio Ribeiro .
The Iliad ( /ˈɪliəd/ ; Ancient Greek : Ἰλιάς Ilias , pronounced ( iː.li.ás ) in Classical Attic ; sometimes referred to as the Song of Ilion or Song of Ilium ) is an ancient Greek epic poem in dactylic hexameter , traditionally attributed to Homer .
Devoted is the sequel to the New York Times bestselling novel Elixir by American entertainer Hilary Duff with Elise Allen .
Dark Passage ( 1946 ) is a crime novel by David Goodis and was the basis for the 1947 film noir of the same name .
The Lute and the Scars is a collection of stories by Yugoslav author Danilo Kiš .
Portals of Tomorrow is an anthology of science fiction stories edited by August Derleth , intended as the first in a series of `` year 's best '' volumes .
For Whom the Bell Tolls is a novel by Ernest Hemingway published in 1940 .
The Peony Pavilion ( Chinese : 牡丹亭 ; pinyin : Mǔdān tíng ; Wade -- Giles : Mu - tan t'ing ) is a play written by Tang Xianzu in the Ming Dynasty and first performed in 1598 at the Pavilion of Prince Teng .
The CIA and the Cult of Intelligence is a 1974 controversial non - fiction political book written by Victor Marchetti , a former special assistant to the Deputy Director of the Central Intelligence Agency , and John D. Marks , a former officer of the United States Department of State .
Honoured Enemy ( or Honored Enemy in the US ) is a fantasy novel by Raymond E. Feist and William R. Forstchen .
Los versos del capitán is a book by the Chilean poet Pablo Neruda , winner of the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1971 .
99 Coffins is a 2007 vampire novel written by David Wellington .
The Lemon Table is the second collection of short stories produced by Julian Barnes , and has the general theme of old age .
On the Marble Cliffs ( Auf den Marmorklippen ) is a novella by Ernst Jünger published in 1939 describing the upheaval and ruin of a serene agricultural society .
The Martian Sphinx is a science fiction novel by John Brunner , writing under the pen - name of Keith Woodcott .
Miss Saigon is a musical by Claude - Michel Schönberg and Alain Boublil , with lyrics by Boublil and Richard Maltby , Jr. It is based on Giacomo Puccini 's opera Madame Butterfly , and similarly tells the tragic tale of a doomed romance involving an Asian woman abandoned by her American lover .
English Hours is a book of travel writing by Henry James published in 1905 .
Lady Susan is a short epistolary novel by Jane Austen , possibly written in 1794 but not published until 1871 .
Glory Road is a novel by Robert A. Heinlein , originally serialized in The Magazine of Fantasy & Science Fiction ( July -- September 1963 ) and published in hardcover the same year .
`` The Dust of Death '' is a science fiction / mystery short story by Isaac Asimov that was first published in the January 1957 issue of Venture Science Fiction Magazine and reprinted in the 1968 collection Asimov 's Mysteries .
`` To a Mouse , on Turning Her Up in Her Nest with the Plough '' ( Scots : `` Tae a Moose '' ) is a Scots poem written by Robert Burns in 1785 , and was included in the Kilmarnock volume .
Wicked Appetite is a 2010 novel by Janet Evanovich set in Salem , Massachusetts .
Welcome to Alflolol is volume four in the French comic book ( or bande dessinée ) science fiction series Valérian and Laureline created by writer Pierre Christin and artist Jean - Claude Mézières .
The End of Nature is a book written by Bill McKibben , published by Anchor in 1989 .
The Liezi ( Chinese : 列子 ; Wade -- Giles : Lieh - tzu ) is a Daoist text attributed to Lie Yukou , a c. 5th century BCE Hundred Schools of Thought philosopher , but Chinese and Western scholars believe it was compiled around the 4th century CE .
The Malcontenta is a 1995 Ned Kelly Award winning novel by the Australian author Barry Maitland .
Beyond the Dar Al - Harb is a collection of three fantasy and science fiction stories by Gordon R. Dickson .
`` Drums of Tombalku '' is an American fantasy short story , one of the original ones written in the 1930s by Robert E. Howard featuring Conan the Cimmerian .
The Love of a Good Woman is a collection of short stories by Canadian writer Alice Munro , published by McClelland and Stewart in 1998 .
The Private Papers of Henry Ryecroft is a semi - fictional autobiographical work by George Gissing in which the author casts himself as the editor of the diary of a deceased acquaintance , selecting essays for posthumous publication .
The Hills of Varna ( published in the USA as Shadow of the Hawk ) is a children 's historical novel by Geoffrey Trease , published in 1948 .
`` Zone of Terror '' is a short story by British author J. G. Ballard , first appearing in the March 1960 edition of New Worlds ( Volume 31 , Number 92 ) and then in the 1962 collection The Voices of Time and Other Stories .
Nostradamus Ate My Hamster is a fantasy novel by British author Robert Rankin .
The Cardturner is a novel written by Newbery Medal winner Louis Sachar and published by Delacorte Press in May 2010 .
Ayumi Hamasaki Bon or Ayu no Deji Deji Nikki is a photobook by Japanese pop singer Ayumi Hamasaki .
The Military Philosophers is the ninth of Anthony Powell 's twelve - novel sequence A Dance to the Music of Time .
Uncle Tom 's Cabin ; or , Life Among the Lowly , is an anti - slavery novel by American author Harriet Beecher Stowe .
Karanapaddhati is an astronomical treatise in Sanskrit attributed to Puthumana Somayaji , an astronomer - mathematician of the Kerala school of astronomy and mathematics .
`` Beyond the Black River '' is one of the original short stories about Conan the Cimmerian , written by American author Robert E. Howard and first published in Weird Tales magazine , v. 25 , nos . 5 - 6 , May - June 1935 .
Billion - Dollar Brain is a 1966 Cold War spy novel by Len Deighton .
Officers and Gentlemen is a 1955 novel by the British novelist Evelyn Waugh .
The Life of Castruccio Castracani ( Italian Vita di Castruccio Castracani ) is a short work by Niccolò Machiavelli .
Blood , Sweat & Tea is a book by ambulance technician Brian Kellett , writing under the pseudonym Tom Reynolds , about life in the London Ambulance Service .
Crystal Boys ( 孽子 , pinyin : Nièzǐ , `` sons of sin '' ) is a novel written by author Pai Hsien - yung and first published in 1983 in Taiwan .
Last Human is the title of a 1995 science fiction comedy novel written by Doug Naylor .
The Gown of Glory is a 1952 novel by the American writer Agnes Sligh Turnbull ( 1888 - -1982 ) .
Ram Sarup Ankhi ( Punjabi : ਰਾਮ ਸਰੂਪ ਅਣਖੀ ) was a Sahitya Akademi Award winner Punjabi writer , novelist and poet of Punjab .
Gustave Tassell ( February 4 , 1926 -- June 9 , 2014 ) was an American fashion designer and Coty Award winner who became a fashion star in the early 1960s with starkly refined clothes that appealed to women like Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis , Greer Garson and Princess Grace of Monaco .
Alexander Panchenko ( 1953 in Chelyabinsk -- 2009 in Kazan ) was a Russian chess Grandmaster and honoured coach who headed the All - Russian chess school .
In 2012 the three members of a - ha , Morten Harket , Magne Furuholmen and Paul Waaktaar Savoy , were appointed Knights of the 1st Class of the Royal Norwegian Order of St. Olav for their contribution to Norwegian music .
Tony Tedeschi is an American pornographic film actor and AVN Hall of Fame inductee .
Karl - Heinz Wiebe ( 10 April 1916 -- 1 October 2012 ) was a German chief engineer on a U - boat in World War II and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) .
He died while still serving in the department as a result of the Dutch Military Aggression II . Supeno is now regarded as a National Hero of Indonesia .
The papal legate , cardinal Bonifazio Bevilacqua ( 1571 - -1627 ) , who had commissioned these paintings , was so pleased that he invested Ventura Salimbeni with the Order of the Golden Spur , a very selective papal order .
Hans Dortenmann ( 11 December 1921 -- 1 April 1973 ) was a German Luftwaffe ace and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) during World War II . The Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership .
Thurman Ruth was inducted into the Gospel Music Hall of Fame .
Nona Gaprindashvili ( Georgian : ნონა გაფრინდაშვილი ; born 3 May 1941 ) is a Georgian chess player , the sixth women 's world chess champion ( 1962 - -1978 ) , and first female Grandmaster .
On May 7 , 2014 Mustafa Dzhemilev has been awarded -- being thus its first recipient -- the Solidarity Prize by the Republic of Poland .
Gu Xiaobing ( Chinese : 谷笑冰 ; born July 12 , 1985 in Xinghua , Taizhou , Jiangsu ) is a Chinese chess player holding the title of Woman Grandmaster .
Mustafa Şekip Birgöl was awarded in 1927 the Medal of Independence with red ribbon .
Otto Edler von Ballasko ( 29 April 1919 -- 5 February 2005 ) was a Bohemian German Luftwaffe bomber pilot and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross during World War II . The Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership .
Cerdas Barus ( born 1 January 1961 in Karo , North Sumatra ) is an Indonesian chess Grandmaster ( 2004 ) .
Ravi Arimilli ( born 1963 ) is an IBM Fellow and Chief Architect .
Vladimir Feldman ( born 13 Sep 1959 in Zhitomir , Ukraine ) is an Australian chess International Master ( IM ) and experienced chess coach .
Lenty Frans ( born 8 February 1994 ) is a Belgian model and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned Miss Belgium 2016 .
Mika Karttunen ( born 30 May 1981 ) is a Finnish chess player , International Master .
Geoffrey Dyer ( born 1947 , Hobart , Tasmania ) is an Australian artist who won the Archibald Prize in 2003 with a portrait of Richard Flanagan .
Accelerando won the 2006 Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel , and the 2010 Estonian SF Award for Best Translated Novel of 2009 .
Vizeadmiral Kurt - Caesar Hoffmann ( 26 August 1895 -- 19 May 1988 ) was a Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross recipient during World War II and commander of the battleship Scharnhorst .
On 2 June 1982 , Yad Vashem recognised Jan Karski as Righteous Among the Nations .
Cay - Lorenz Baron von Brockdorff ( 25 August 1923 -- 11 September 1997 ) was a highly decorated Oberleutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II and a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
Major General Algernon Fuller became a Commander of the Order of the British Empire in 1941 .
Leandro Katz 's work has earned the Guggenheim Fellowship , the Rockefeller Foundation Fellowship , and the National Endowment for the Arts Fellowship , and he has received support from the New York State Council on the Arts , the Jerome Foundation , and the Hubert Bals Fund , Rotterdam International Film Festival .
Jose Rodela ( born June 15 , 1937 ) is a U.S. Army veteran of the Vietnam War and a recipient of the Medal of Honor .
Detlev Graf von Garnier - Turawa ( 24 September 1906 -- 27 June 1944 ) was a highly decorated Hauptmann of the Reserves in the Wehrmacht during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross .
General Sir Hugh Rowlands VC , KCB ( 6 May 1828 -- 1 August 1909 ) was a Welsh recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Werner Stumpf ( 15 March 1917 -- 13 October 1942 ) was a German Luftwaffe ace and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross during World War II . Stumpf claimed 48 aerial victories , 2 over the Western Front , 23 over the Eastern Front and 23 over the Mediterranean Front .
Aleksandar Wohl ( born 21 July 1963 ) is an Australian chess player , attaining the rank of International Master .
Sonia Rolt OBE ( 15 April 1919 -- 22 October 2014 ) was a campaigner for the Inland Waterways Association ( IWA ) of Great Britain and was made an Officer of the Order of the British Empire in 2010 for her services to industrial archaeology and heritage .
Captain Jerauld Wright was awarded his first Legion of Merit in recognition of his participation in Operation Kingpin .
Krishna Sobti ( Hindi : कृष्णा सोबती ; born 18 February 1925 ) is a Hindi fiction writer and essayist , who won the Sahitya Akademi Award in 1980 for her novel Zindaginama and in 1996 , was awarded the Sahitya Akademi Fellowship , the highest award of the Akademi .
In 1994 , the Zapruder film footage was deemed `` culturally , historically , or aesthetically significant '' by the United States Library of Congress and was selected for permanent preservation in the National Film Registry .
Kenichi Fukui was co - recipient of the Nobel Prize in Chemistry in 1981 with Roald Hoffmann , for their independent investigations into the mechanisms of chemical reactions .
Necip Torumtay was decorated with the Turkish Armed Forces Medal of Distinguished Service .
Constantin Lupulescu ( born 25 March 1984 in Buftea , Romania ) is a Romanian chess Grandmaster ( 2006 ) .
Rajeshwari Sachdev is a Hindi film actress who is most known for her role in Shyam Benegal 's film Sardari Begum ( 1996 ) , for which she won the 1997 National Film Award for Best Supporting Actress .
Subbaraman Vijayalakshmi ( born 25 March 1979 ) is an Indian chess player who holds the FIDE titles of International Master and Woman Grandmaster , the first female player in her country to achieve these titles .

So You Do n't Know Korff Yet ? ( German : Nanu , Sie kennen Korff noch nicht ? ) is a 1938 German comedy crime film directed by Fritz Holl and starring Heinz Rühmann , Victor Janson and Franz Schafheitlin .
Tall Story is a 1960 American romantic comedy film made by Warner Bros. , directed by Joshua Logan and starring Anthony Perkins with Jane Fonda , in her first screen role , at the age of 22 .
Zombie Island Massacre is a 1984 horror film directed by John N. Carter and starring famed congressman 's wife and Playboy model , Rita Jenrette .
Le Gang ( Italian : La gang del parigino ) is a 1977 French - Italian film starring Alain Delon .
Les Trésors de Satan , released in the United States as The Treasures of Satan and in Britain as The Devil 's Money Bags , is a 1902 French short silent film directed by Georges Méliès .
Living with Michael Jackson is a television film , in which Martin Bashir interviewed Michael Jackson over a span of 8 months , from May 2002 to January 2003 .
Con Games is a 2001 American direct to video action drama film written and directed by Jefferson Edward Donald , starring Tommy Lee Thomas , Eric Roberts , Martin Kove , Amy Fadhli , and the late Matthew Ansara .
The Manny ( German : Der Nanny ) is a 2015 German comedy film directed and co - written by Matthias Schweighöfer , starring himself as a greedy and super - busy real - estate developer , and Milan Peschel as a victim of his development who accidentally ends up babysitting his 2 children .
Baby Brother is a 1927 American Our Gang short film featuring Oliver Hardy .
Assassination Games is a 2011 American action film directed by Ernie Barbarash , and starring Jean - Claude Van Damme and Scott Adkins .
The Ballad of Uhlans ( Уланская баллада ) is a 2012 Russian historical adventure film directed by Oleg Fesenko , and stars Sergei Bezrukov , Anna Chipovskaya , Anton Sokolov and Vladimir Gostyukhin .
Beware of Pity is a 1946 British romantic drama film directed by Maurice Elvey and starring Lilli Palmer , Albert Lieven and Cedric Hardwicke .
Liebe Dein Symptom wie Dich selbst ! ( German : Thou shalt love thy symptom as thyself ; 1996 ) is a German documentary film about the Slovenian philosopher and psychoanalyst Slavoj Žižek .
Big Hearted Herbert is a 1934 domestic comedy film starring Aline MacMahon and Guy Kibbee as a middle - aged couple .
What Next ? is a 1928 British silent comedy film directed by Walter Forde and starring Forde , Pauline Johnson and Frank Stanmore .
Ti ho cercata in tutti i necrologi ( `` I 've been looking for you in all the obituaries '' ) is an English / Italian dramatic film directed by Giancarlo Giannini .
Jonas in the Jungle is a 2013 documentary film by Peter Sempel about the filmmaker Jonas Mekas .
Return to Action is a 1990 Hong Kong action film produced and directed by Chen Kuan - tai and starring Alex Man , Rosamund Kwan , Mark Cheng , Shing Fui - On and Chen himself in a supporting role .
The Purple Plain ( aka Llanura Roja ) is a 1954 British war film , directed by Robert Parrish , with Gregory Peck playing a Canadian pilot serving in the Royal Air Force in the Burma Campaign in the closing months of the World War II , who is battling with depression after having lost his wife .
Waking Madison , ( originally titled Mad World ) , is an independent drama / thriller film written and directed by Katherine Brooks and starring Sarah Roemer and Elisabeth Shue .
Starring Rd Mochtar , Roekiah , and Eddy T. Effendi , it follows a masked man known only as `` Gagak Item '' ( `` Black Raven '' ) .
Trial Without Jury is a 1950 American mystery film directed by Philip Ford and starring Robert Rockwell , Barbra Fuller and Kent Taylor .
Chasing Liberty is a 2004 American romantic comedy film directed by Andy Cadiff and starring Mandy Moore and Matthew Goode .
Goodnight , Ladies and Gentlemen ( Italian : Signore e signori , buonanotte , French : Mesdames et messieurs bonsoir ) is a 1976 French - Italian comedy film starring Vittorio Gassman , Ugo Tognazzi , Nino Manfredi , Paolo Villaggio , Marcello Mastroianni , Senta Berger , Adolfo Celi and Felice Andreasi .
Trabbi Goes to Hollywood ( English title : Driving Me Crazy ) is a 1991 US comedy film directed by Jon Turteltaub , starring Thomas Gottschalk , Billy Dee Williams , Dom DeLuise , and James Tolkan .
Young Billy Young is a 1969 western movie starring Robert Mitchum and featuring Angie Dickinson , Robert Walker , Jr. ( in the title role ) , David Carradine , Jack Kelly ( who plays a villain and dresses exactly as he had for his role on television 's Maverick ) , Deana Martin and Paul Fix .
Nicholas on Holiday ( French : Les Vacances du Petit Nicolas ) is a 2014 French family comedy film directed by Laurent Tirard , starring Mathéo Boisselier , Valérie Lemercier , Kad Merad , Dominique Lavanant , François - Xavier Demaison and Bouli Lanners .
From This Day Forward is a 1946 American drama film directed by John Berry , starring Joan Fontaine and Mark Stevens .
The Green Cloak ia a surviving 1915 silent film mystery directed by Walter Edwin and starring Broadway stage actress Irene Fenwick .
Let asfaltového holuba ( `` Fly of the Asphalt Pigeon '' ) is a 1991 Czechoslovak psychodrama , starring Ondřej Vetchý , Szidi Tobias , Roman Luknár and György Cserhalmi .
No One Killed Jessica is a 2011 Indian biographical thriller film starring Rani Mukerji and Vidya Balan , produced by UTV Spotboy and directed by Rajkumar Gupta .
8 mm 2 is a 2005 direct - to - video It stars Johnathon Schaech and Lori Heuring .
Monster 's Ball is a 2001 American erotic romantic drama film directed by German - Swiss director Marc Forster starring Billy Bob Thornton , Halle Berry , and Heath Ledger .
Bhuvana Oru Kelvi Kuri ( English : Bhuvana is a question mark ) is a 1977 Tamil - language Indian feature film directed by SP . Muthuraman , starring Sivakumar , Rajinikanth and Sumithra .
A sequel to the 2008 film Ip Man , Ip Man 2 was directed by Wilson Yip and stars Donnie Yen , who reprises the leading role .
The Wannabes , ( US title : Criminal Ways ) , is a 2003 Australian comedy film starring Nick Giannopoulos , Russell Dykstra , Isla Fisher , Ryan Johnson , Michael Carman , Lena Cruz , Tony Nikolakopoulos , Costas Kilias , Chantal Contouri and Felix Williamson .
Professor Pyarelal is a 1981 Hindi film produced by TM Bihari and directed by Brij Sadanah and featuring Dharmendra , Zeenat Aman , Simi Garewal , Shreeram Lagoo , Amjad Khan and Nirupa Roy in the lead roles .
Shudhu Tumi is a 2004 Bengali film directed by Abhijit Guha and Sudeshna Roy , produced by Sagar Bhora and Siddhartha Bhora , and starring Prosenjit Chatterjee and Koel Mallick in the lead roles .
Alien Hunter is a 2003 television science - fiction - thriller film , directed by Ron Krauss and stars James Spader , Carl Lewis and Leslie Stefanson .
Starring Peter Coyote , Mel Smith and Billie Whitelaw , the film is adapted from Slayground , the 14th Parker novel ( although the main character has been renamed to `` Stone '' in this adaptation ) , written by Donald Westlake under the name Richard Stark .
Midnight Beating is a 2010 Chinese horror film directed by Zhang Jiabei and starring Hong Kong veteran actors Simon Yam and Francis Ng .
The Man Without a Body ( also known as Curse of Nostradamus ) is a low budget 1957 British horror film directed by Charles Saunders and W. Lee Wilder and starring Robert Hutton , George Coulouris and Julia Arnall .
Thee Kulikkum Pachai Maram is a 2013 Tamil - language Indian feature film directed by duo M.Vineesh and M.Prabheesh , starring Prajin and Sarayu in lead roles .
She Knew All the Answers is a 1941 comedy film made by Columbia Pictures , directed by Richard Wallace , and starring by Joan Bennett and Franchot Tone .
Prison on Fire - Life Sentence is a 2001 Hong Kong crime thriller film directed by Edmond Yuen and starring Ben Wong , Iris Wong , Tommy Wong , William Ho , Lee Wai Kei , Chapman To and Bill Lung .
My Fan Ramu is a 2013 Malayalam film directed by debutant Nikhil K. Menon , starring Saiju Kurup and Rajeev Pillai in the lead roles .
Yathra ( Malayalam : യാത്ര , meaning The Journey ) is a 1985 Malayalam film directed by Balu Mahendra , and starring Mammootty and Shobana .
Let Us Live is a 1939 crime thriller film directed by John Brahm starring Maureen O'Sullivan , Henry Fonda and Ralph Bellamy .
The Legend of Silk Boy is a 2010 Chinese animated film directed by David Liu and starring Jackie Chan .
Huns and Hyphens is a 1918 American silent comedy film featuring Larry Semon and Stan Laurel .

The Soul of Nigger Charley is a 1973 blaxploitation western film directed by Larry Spangler and starring Fred Williamson .
Who Was the Man ? is a 1921 American short Western film directed by Lee Kohlmar , released by Universal Film Mfg . Co. and featuring Hoot Gibson .

Ung Thị ( 14 October 1913 - 10 February 2001 ) was a prominent Vietnamese businessman who , together with his wife Nguyen Thi Nguyet Nga , built and operated the Rex Hotel and Cinema in Ho Chi Minh City .
Patrick Sookhdeo ( born 20 March 1947 ) is the director of the Institute for the Study of Islam and Christianity and was for 22 years International Director of the Barnabas Fund .
María Xesús Pato Díaz ( born 29 August 1955 , in Ourense , Galicia ) , most commonly known as Chus Pato , is a Galician writer and political activist .
Viktor Lőrincz ( born 28 April 1990 ) is a Hungarian Greco - Roman wrestler .
Lal Mani Joshi ( 27 July 1935 , Kumaon Hills , Uttarakhand , India -- 16 July 1984 , Delhi , India ) was an eminent Buddhist scholar and professor of comparative religions and Buddhist studies in a number of distinguished universities of India and USA .
Elanson Henry Lacy , known as Harry Lacy ( 1853 - December 14 , 1920 ) was an American actor , a star in his time best known for playing the role of Jack Manley in the hit play The Still Alarm in the 1880s and 1890s .
Gene H. Bell - Villada ( born 1941 in Haiti ) is an American literary critic , novelist , translator and memoirist , with strong interests in Latin American Writing , Modernism , and Magic Realism .
Dr Carolyn Browne ( born 19 October 1958 in Yorkshire ) is a British diplomat , currently Ambassador to Kazakhstan .
Felipe Fernández - Armesto ( born 1950 ) is a British historian and author of several popular works of history .
Jacquie O'Neill ( born 1969 in Yorkshire , England ) is an English illustrator .
Hal Bennett , born George Harold Bennett ( 1936 -- 2004 ) , was an author known for a variety of books .
Sharon McPherson ( born 16 June 1965 ) is a Scottish writer and book publisher .
Jennie Fletcher ( 19 March 1890 -- 17 January 1968 ) , later known by her married name Jennie Hyslop , was a British competitive swimmer , Olympic gold medallist , and former world record - holder .
Salman Butt ( Punjabi / Urdu : سلمان بٹ ‎ , Salmān Buṭṭ ; born 7 October 1984 ) is a Pakistani cricketer who was jailed in Britain for match fixing in 2011 .
Richard Van Camp ( born 8 September 1971 ) is a Tłı̨chǫ writer from Fort Smith , Northwest Territories .
Ofer Shelah ( Hebrew : עפר שלח‎ , born 9 February 1960 ) is an Israeli journalist and politician .
Christopher Neil ( born 1948 ) is a British record producer , songwriter , singer and actor .
Gaius or Gnaeus Hosidius Geta ( ca 20 - aft . 95 ) was a Roman Senator and general who lived in the 1st century .
Sardar Qamar Zaman Khan ( Urdu:سردار قمر زمان خان ) was born on 19 August 1952 , in village Panyali Tehsil and District Bagh , Azad Kashmir .
Rachel Wyse ( born 22 January 1985 in Dublin ) is an Irish Sky Sports News anchor and equestrian show jumper .
Walid Hamid Tawfiq al - Tikriti ( Arabic : وليد حميد توفيق التكريتي‎ ) ( or Walid Hamid Tawfiq al - Nasiri ) ( born 1954 ) was the Governor of Basra from September 2002 to April 2003 and the Director of the Iraqi Special Security Organization from June 2001 to September 2002 .
Frank Drown ( born ca . 1920 ) is an American author and former missionary .
Melinda Schneider ( born 7 October 1971 , as Melinda - Jane Bean ) is an Australian country music performer and songwriter .
Sampooran Singh Kalra ( born 18 August 1934 ) , known popularly by his pen name Gulzar , is an Indian poet , lyricist and film director .
Filippo Magnini ( Italian pronunciation : ( fiˈlippo maɲˈɲini ) ; born 2 February 1982 ) is an Italian swimmer , who was twice 100 metres freestyle World champion and three times European champion at that distance .
Murad Qureshi ( born 27 May 1965 ) is a British Labour and Co - operative Party politician , and a Member of the London Assembly .
Albert Chartier ( 16 June 1912 -- 25 February 2004 ) was a French - Canadian cartoonist and illustrator , best known for having created the comic strip Onésime .
Margaretha Byström ( born 2 August 1937 in Stockholm ) is a Swedish actress ( film , theater , television ) , writer and director .
Neil Clephane - Cameron ( born Neil Clephane Cameron , 4 October 1960 ) is a historian , writer and actor from Battle in East Sussex ( Great Britain ) .
Amos Hadar ( Hebrew : עמוס הדר‎‎ 7 September 1923 -- 13 January 2014 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment between 1974 and 1981 .
Miles Tredinnick , also known as Riff Regan , ( born Warrington 18 February 1955 ) is a rock musician , songwriter and a stage and screenwriter .
Candice Cohen - Ahnine ( c. 1977 -- 16 August 2012 ) was a French Jewish mother involved in a legal battle with Saudi Prince Sattam bin Khalid bin Nasser Al Saud over custody for her child Aya , who she said was kidnapped from her .
Tunde Jegede ( born 28 January 1972 ) is a composer and multi - instrumentalist in contemporary classical , African and pop music , who was born in England and as a child travelled to Africa to learn the art of the kora .
Du Fuwei ( 598?-624 ) , known during service to Tang Dynasty as Li Fuwei ( 李伏威 ) , was an agrarian leader who rose against the rule of Emperor Yang of Sui at the end of the Chinese dynasty Sui Dynasty .
Judith Chazin - Bennahum ( born 8 April 1937 ) is a ballet dancer , choreographer , dance historian , writer , and educator .
Kerstin Lindblad - Toh , born 1970 , is a Swedish scientist .
Anne Clausdatter , also known as Anne Arnold and Anna Clausdatter ( born 5 June 1659 in Skien , died 11 April 1713 at Borgestad Manor ) was a Norwegian businesswoman and owner of Borgestad Manor in Skien , one of the largest estates of Bratsberg .
Jack Preger ( born 25 July 1930 in Manchester , England ) is a British doctor who has been offering medical treatment as well as vocational training to the poor in the Indian city of Kolkata and in other parts of West Bengal since 1972 .
Jessica Martin ( born 25 August 1962 , Fulham , London ) is an English actress , singer and impressionist whose career has diversified to include comic writing and illustrating .
Helmi Loussaief ( born 12 February 1986 ) is a French born , Tunisian football player who currently plays for PKNS FC as a Midfielder in the Malaysia Super League .
Julie Fowlis ( born 20 June 1979 ) is a Scottish folk singer and multi - instrumentalist who sings primarily in Scottish Gaelic .
Nancy Davenport ( born 1965 Vancouver , British Columbia ) is a Canadian photographer .
Neil Coulbeck ( 1952 -- July 11 , 2006 ) was a banker with the Royal Bank of Scotland ( RBS ) .
Kaye Donachie ( born 1970 in Glasgow ) is a contemporary British painter based in London .
María Fernanda Navia Cardona ( born 1 January 1979 in Bogotá ) is a Colombian journalist , model , and former beauty queen .
Joanna Krupa ( Polish pronunciation : ( jɔˈanːa ˈkrupa ) ; born 23 April 1979 ) is a Polish American model , actress and animal rights activist .
Bogdan Stoyanov ( Bulgarian : Богдан Стоянов ) born 24 March 1987 is a Bulgarian footballer currently playing for FC Pirin Blagoevgrad as a midfielder .
John Jacob Faesch ( 1726 -- 1799 ) was a Swiss ironmaster who established the Mount Hope Iron Furnace in the Mount Hope village section of Rockaway Township , New Jersey in 1772 which played an important role in providing munitions and tools during the Revolutionary War .
Claudine Bouché ( 27 September 1925 -- 7 April 2014 ) was a French film editor .
Sir Albert Ruskin Cook , CMG , OBE , MD ( 22 March 1870 -- 23 April 1951 ) was a British born medical missionary in Uganda , and founder of Mulago Hospital and Mengo Hospital .
Elizabeth Ogborne ( 1763 / 4 -- 22 December 1853 ) was a British Antiquary for Essex .
Rosa Frederica Baring FitzGeorge ( 9 March 1854 - 10 March 1927 ) , was the second daughter of Mr. William Henry Baring , J.P. and Elizabeth Hammersley , of Norman Court in West Tytherley , Hampshire , England .
William Cecil , 17th Baron de Ros of Helmsley ( May 1590 -- 27 June 1618 ) .
Anton Füster , also spelled as Fister ( 5 January 1808 -- 12 March 1881 ) was an Austrian Roman Catholic priest , theologian , pedagogue , radical political activist and author of Slovene origin .
Henry Raine Barker ( 11 November 1829 - 1902 ) was an English lawyer , banker and rower who won three events at Henley Royal Regatta in the same year in 1852 Barker was the son of Richard Barker of London .
Henry Steedman ( 1866 - -1953 ) was a Scottish - born Australian botanist .
Beatriz Balzi ( Buenos Aires 1936 - -2001 ) was a renowned Argentinean pianist , professor and musicologist specialized in contemporary Latin - American music .
Sir Richard Buller ( 1578 - -1642 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1621 and 1642 .
John Barkstead ( died 1662 ) was an English Major - General and Regicide .
Pietro Giovanni Abbati ( in English , Peter John Abbati ) ( 1683 - 1745 ) was an Italian set designer , painter and engraver .
Zheng Yingtao ( Chinese : 鄭櫻桃 ; died 349 ) was an empress of the Chinese / Jie state Later Zhao .
Rinus van den Bosch ( January 10 , 1938 -- 14 April 1996 ) was a Dutch artist , who worked as sculptor , photographer , installation artist , painter , and draftsman .
Ralph Hart Tweddell ( 25 May 1843 -- 3 September 1895 ) was a British mechanical engineer , known particularly for inventing the portable hydraulic riveter , which greatly facilitated the construction of boilers , bridges and ships .
Gavin Milroy ( 1805 - -1886 ) was a Scottish physician and medical writer .
Chiang Yee ( simplified Chinese : 蒋彝 ; traditional Chinese : 蔣彝 , Pinyin : Jiǎng Yí , Wade -- Giles : Chiang Yee ) ( 19 May 1903 -- 26 October 1977 ) , self - styled as `` The Silent Traveller '' , was a Chinese poet , author , painter and calligrapher .
Kozaburo Hirai ( 平井康三郎 ; 10 September 1910 - 30 November 2002 ) was a Japanese composer and professor of music .
Ernie McAlpine ( 11 February 1902 -- 1 June 1984 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William J. Henry ( c.1867 - -1955 ) was an American hymn writer and evangelist .
Alexander Catsch ( also Katsch ; 1913 - -1976 ) was a German - Russian medical doctor and radiation biologist .
Robert Dundas , 2nd Viscount Melville KT , PC , FRS ( 14 March 1771 -- 10 June 1851 ) was a British statesman , the son of Henry Dundas , the 1st Viscount .
Henry Sloane Cooper ( September 12 , 1888 -- 1970 ) was an Ontario embroidery manufacturer and political figure .
Juan Maria Schuver ( born as- Joannes Maria Schuver ) ( February 26 , 1852 - August 1883 ) was a Dutch explorer who was a native of Amsterdam .
Fanny Umphelby ( 1788 - - 9 April 1852 ) was a British author who authored a popular primer known by the shortened title The Child 's Guide to Knowledge , ... by a Lady .
Árpád Prandler ( 23 February 1930 -- 5 February 2014 ) was a Hungarian jurist , who served as an Ad Litem Judge of the International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia based in The Hague , Netherlands between 2006 and 2013 .
Basil Mesardonites was the Catapan of Italy , representing the Byzantine Emperor there , from 1010 to 1016 or 1017 .
Philips Vingboons ( or Vinckboons , Vinckeboons , Vinckbooms ) ( c. 1607 -- 2 October 1678 ) was a Dutch architect .
Charles Chewings ( 16 April 1859 -- 9 June 1937 ) was an Australian geologist and anthropologist .
Stanley Middleton FRSL ( 1 August 1919 -- 25 July 2009 ) was a British novelist .
William Dressler ( 1890 - -1969 ) was a cardiologist born in Poland , who went on to become a Director of Cardiology at Maimonides Medical Center .
Fang Zhenwu ( Chinese : 方振武 ; pinyin : Fāng Zhènwǔ ) ( 1885 -- December 1941 ) was a Chinese military officer in the early 20th century .
Heinz Arnold ( 12 February 1919 in Flöha in Saxony -- 17 April 1945 ) was a former German Luftwaffe fighter ace .
Count Franz von Oppersdorff ( 1778 - 1818 ) was a Silesian nobleman and a great lover of music , who commissioned Beethoven 's Fourth and Fifth Symphonies .
Edward Fortunatus ( or in German Eduard Fortunat ) of Baden ( 17 September 1565 -- 8 June 1600 ) was Margrave of Baden - Rodemachern and Baden - Baden .
Sir Herbert Ashman , 1st Baronet ( 11 June 1854 -- 26 September 1914 ) was the first Lord Mayor of Bristol .
Khanlar Safaraliyev ( Azerbaijani : Xanlar Səfərəliyev ) ( c.1878 -- 19 September 1907 ) was an Azerbaijani oil field worker , labor organizer , and Moslem social democrat .
Sir John Benjamin Macneill FRS ( 1793 -- 2 March 1880 ) was an eminent Irish civil engineer of the 19th century , closely associated with Thomas Telford .
Krobo Edusei ( 26 December 1915 -- 13 February 1984 ) was a Ghanaian politician and a high - profile member of Kwame Nkrumah 's government .
Hugh Ottaway ( 1925 -- 6 November 1979 ) was a prominent British writer on concert music .
Josef Hassid ( Polish : Józef Chasyd ) ( 28 December 1923 -- 7 November 1950 ) was a Polish violinist .
Sir Robert Austen , 3rd Baronet ( March 1664 - June 1706 ) , was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1699 to 1701 .
Herbert Thewlis ( 31 August 1865 -- 30 November 1920 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played two matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club in 1888 , against the MCC and Gloucestershire .
Domenico Merlini ( Polish : Dominik Merlini ) ( 22 February 1730 -- 20 February 1797 ) was an Italian - Polish architect whose work was mostly in the classical style .
Sir Leon Bagrit ( 13 March 1902 -- 22 April 1979 ) was a leading British industrialist and pioneer of automation .
Johan Nordhagen ( 23 March 1856 in Veldre -- 28 August 1956 ) was a Norwegian painter and artist .
Stefan Kunicki ( Ukrainian : Стефан Куницький ) of Sas Coat of Arms ( died 1684 ) was a hetman of Right - bank Ukraine .
Sampson Hopkins ( died 1622 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1614 and 1622 .
Wu Jiaji ( Chinese : 吳嘉紀 ; Wade -- Giles : Wu Chia - chi , 1618 - -1684 ) was a Chinese poet , and an associate of the official and literary figure Zhou Lianggong .
Xu Ling ( Chinese : 徐陵 ; pinyin : Xú Líng ) ( 507 - -583 ) was the compiler and editor of the famous poetry anthology New Songs from the Jade Terrace during the poetically prolific Southern Dynasties era , 420 - -589 .
Shaun Wylie ( 17 January 1913 -- 2 October 2009 ) was a British mathematician and World War II codebreaker .
Luis de Velasco y Velasco , 2nd Count of Salazar , 1st Marquess of Belvedere , ( Valladolid , Spain , 1559 -- Dunkirk , Spanish Netherlands ( present - day France ) , 1625 ) , was a Spanish military commander during the French Wars of Religion and the Eighty Years ' War .
Admiral Rainer Feist ( 12 April 1945 -- 19 May 2007 ) was an officer in the German Navy until his retirement in 2004 .
Luis Antonio Regalado Reyes ( b. January 10 , 1922 -- † 2001 ) was a Salvadoran footballer and coach .
Ferdinando Cavalleri ( 1794 - -1867 ) was an Italian history and portrait painter .
One records a Jehans Erardi dying in 1258 while another records Jehan Erart dying in 1259 .
Gabriele Serbelloni , better known as Gabrio Serbelloni ( also Gabrio Cerbellon in Spanish ) , ( 1509 - January 1580 ) was an Italian condottiero and general .

Christopher Terne M.D. ( also Tearne ) ( 1620 - -1673 ) was an English physician .
Kereopa Te Rau ( ? -- 5 January 1872 ) was a leader of Pai Marire ( Hauhau ) , a Māori religion .
Friedrich Gottlob Uhlemann ( 26 November 1792 , Zeitz -- 19 April 1864 ) was a German Protestant theologian and educator best known as the author of orientalist grammar works .
Moritz Roth ( 25 December 1839 , in Basel -- 4 November 1914 , in Gottlieben am Untersee ) was a Swiss pathologist remembered for describing Roth 's spots .
Dhimitër Ilo ( ? - 1947 ) was an Albanian patriot from Korçë , back then Ottoman Empire .
Hugo Wenzel ( 23 August 1891 -- 24 January 1940 ) was a German politician ( SPD , USPD , KPD ) .
Edmond de Burca ( died 1514 ) was 12th Mac William Iochtar and lord of Lower ( North ) Connacht , Ireland .
Yaqut al - Musta'simi ( also Yakut - i Musta'simi ) ( died 1298 ) was a well - known calligrapher and secretary of the last Abbasid caliph .
Ambrosius Francken I ( 1544 - -1618 ) was a Flemish painter known for his religious works and historical allegories painted in a late Mannerist style .
George Challenor ( 28 June 1888 -- 30 July 1947 ) was a West Indian cricketer who was part of the first West Indies Test side .
Belu Zilber ( born Herbert Zilber ; October 14 , 1901 - -February 1978 ) was a Romanian communist activist .
Richard Penderel ( c.1606 - 7 February 1672 ) was a Roman Catholic farmer , and a supporter of the Royalist cause during the English Civil War .
Matilda Alice Victoria Wood , ( 12 February 1870 -- 7 October 1922 ) , professionally known as Marie Lloyd /ˈmɑːri/ ; was an English music hall singer , comedian and musical theatre actress during the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Hedwig of Gudensberg , also known as Hedwig of Hesse ( 1098 - -1148 ) was a member of the Gisones family .
Luciano Pistoi ( 1927 - -1995 ) , art critic , dealer , journalist and publisher , promoter and organizer of cultural events .
Francis Bennon Ducrue was a missionary in Mexico , b. in Munich , Bavaria , of French parents , 10 June 1721 ; d. there 30 March 1779 .
Arnt Eliassen ( 9 September 1915 -- 22 April 2000 ) was a Norwegian meteorologist who was a pioneer in the use of numerical analysis and computers for weather forecasting .
Dominique Heckmes ( 1 September 1878 -- 4 February 1938 ) was a Luxembourgian composer and music critic .
Sir John Doddridge ( Doderidge or Dodderidge , etc . ) ( 1555 - -1628 ) was an English lawyer , appointed Justice of the King 's Bench in 1612 and served as Member of Parliament for Barnstaple in 1589 and for Horsham in 1604 .
James Howell ( c. 1594 -- 1666 ) was a 17th - century Anglo - Welsh historian and writer who is in many ways a representative figure of his age .
Antonín Pospíšil ( 6 October 1903 -- 15 June 1973 ) was a Czechoslovakian politician of the Catholic Czechoslovakian People 's Party during the Communist Party 's rule , when other legal parties had to play the role of CP satellites .
Finn Lambrechts DFC ( 16 June 1900 -- 8 December 1956 ) was a Norwegian military officer , a Lieutenant General of the Royal Norwegian Air Force .
