Viola of Teschen , later known as Elizabeth ( Polish : Wiola Elżbieta cieszyńska , Czech : Viola Alžběta Těšínská ) ( ca . 1291 -- 21 September 1317 ) , was a Polish princess member of the House of Piast in the Cieszyn branch and by marriage Queen of Bohemia and Poland .
Sir Archibald Russell , CBE , FRS ( 30 May 1904 -- 29 May 1995 ) was a British aerospace engineer who worked most of his career at the Bristol Aeroplane Company , before becoming managing director of the Filton Division when Bristol merged into British Aircraft Corporation in 1960 .
Hugh de Lacy , 1st Earl of Ulster ( ~1176 -- after December 26 , 1242 ) was the younger son of Hugh de Lacy , Lord of Meath .
Frans Mortelmans ( Antwerp , 1 May 1865 -- Antwerp , 11 April 1936 ) was a Belgian painter , draughtsman and engraver .
Bernard Adeney ( 2 August 1878 - 4 April 1966 ) was an English painter and textile designer .
Vivian Nickalls ( 1871 - 1947 ) was a British rower who won the Wingfield Sculls three times and the Diamond Challenge Sculls at Henley Royal Regatta in 1891 .
Emil Sonderegger ( born 28 November 1868 in Herisau -- died 15 July 1934 ) was a Swiss military officer who later became involved in the country 's far right political scene .
Marta Labarr ( 1912 - -1999 ) was a singer and actress who appeared in eleven British and French films , usually as a leading lady .
Aimoin ( c. 960 -- c. 1010 ) , French chronicler , was born at Villefranche - de - Longchat about 960 , and in early life entered the monastery of Fleury , where he became a monk and passed the greater part of his life .
Christiaan Tom Neumeier ( 2 February 1921 -- 26 December 1991 ) was a Dutch rower who won the European title in the double sculls in 1947 , together with Henk van der Meer .
Walter Karig ( 13 November 1898 - 30 September 1956 ) was a prolific author , who served as a U.S. naval captain .
Berenguer de Palou II ( died 1241 ) was bishop of Barcelona from 1212 to 1241 .
Christopher Bagshaw ( 1552 -- 1625 ? ) was an English academic and Roman Catholic priest .
Caroline Mary Luard ( died 24 August 1908 ) was the victim of an unsolved murder , known as the Seal Chart Murder , after she was mysteriously shot and killed at an isolated summerhouse in a heavily wooded area near Ightham , Kent .
Agnes Jónsdóttir ( died 1507 ) , was the abbess of the Benedictine convent Reynistaðarklaustur in Iceland 1461 - -1507 .
Pierre Joseph Marie Granville , known as Jonathas Granville ( 1785 - 1839 ) was a Haitian educator , legal expert , soldier and a diplomat .
Lavinia Derwent was the pen name of Scottish author and broadcaster Elizabeth Dodd MBE ( 1909 - -1989 ) .
Frederick A. Henninger ( 1865 - 1944 ) , commonly known as F. A. Henninger , was a leading architect of Omaha , Nebraska .
Samuel A. Carlson ( 1868 - -1961 ) was mayor of Jamestown , New York .
Charles Herbert Mayo ( 1845 - -1929 ) was a Dorset clergyman and antiquarian .
Frederick Herzog ( 1925 - -1995 ) was a professor of systematic theology at Duke University .
Fredrika Eleonora von Düben ( 1738 - -1808 ) was a Swedish dilettante painter and Embroidery artist , an honorary member of the Royal Swedish Academy of Arts ( 1783 ) .
Léon Pourtau ( 1872 -- 4 July 1898 ) was a French painter and musician .
Francis Rynd AM , MRCS , MRIA ( 1801 - 1861 ) was an Irish physician , famous for inventing the hollow needle used in hypodermic syringes .
Edwin Francis Walker ( 13 December 1872 in Chicago , Illinois -- 3 December 1956 , in Los Angeles , California ) was a research assistant at the Southwest Museum in Los Angeles and later one of its most prolific investigators .
Michael Werikhe ( 25 May 1956 -- 9 August 1999 ) , also known as `` the Rhino Man '' was a Kenyan conservationist .
Ludovic Lindsay , 16th Earl of Crawford ( 1600 - -1652 ) took part in the strange plot of 1641 called The Incident .
Adila Fachiri ( 26 February 1886 -- 15 December 1962 ) was a Hungarian violinist who had an international career but made her home in England .
John Frederick France F.R.C.S. Eng . , JP ( Born on 15 December 1817 , christened on 16 January 1818 at St Luke , Chelsea , London , died on 6 October 1900 at St Leonards on Sea , Sussex ) was the Ophthalmic Surgeon at Guy 's Hospital from 1847 until 1849 .
Jacob Stolt - Nielsen , Jr. ( 12 May 1931 -- 15 February 2015 ) was a Norwegian entrepreneur .
Tod Ensign ( d. May 2014 ) was an American veteran 's rights lawyer and Director of Citizen Soldier , a non - profit GI and veterans rights advocacy group based in New York City .
Peder Olsen Walløe ( 1716 -- 27 April 1793 ) was a Dano - Norwegian Arctic explorer most noted for his historic exploration of the former Norse settlements on Greenland .
Sonam Rapten , also known as Sonam Choephel ( 1595 - 1657 ) was regent in Tibet from 1642 to 1658 .
Ambrosio Martínez Bustos ( 1614 - 1672 ) was a Spanish Baroque painter active in Granada .
Aaron ben Menahem Mendel ( 1800 - -1873 ) was a Russian rabbi , who flourished at the beginning of the nineteenth century .
Princess Wilhelmine of Baden ( 21 September 1788 -- 27 January 1836 ) , was by birth Princess of Baden and by marriage Grand Duchess consort of Hesse and the Rhine .
Balian of Ibelin ( French : Balian d'Ibelin ; c. 1143 -- 1193 ) was a crusader noble of the Kingdom of Jerusalem in the 12th century .
Mlađa Veselinović ( 21 April 1915 - 27 December 2012 ) was a Serbian actor and translator .
Li Di ( Chinese : 李迪 ; pinyin : Lǐ Dí ; Wade -- Giles : Li Ti ; c. 1100 -- after 1197 ) was a Chinese imperial court painter in the Song Dynasty .
Edmund , Earl of Rutland ( 17 May 1443 -- 30 December 1460 ) was the fifth child and second surviving son of Richard Plantagenet , 3rd Duke of York , and Cecily Neville .
Eric Reichman ( 25 August 1904 -- 19 June 1984 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William Stretton ( April 1755 - 12 March 1828 ) was a builder and architect based in Nottingham .
George Ide Butler ( 1834 -- 1918 ) was a Seventh - day Adventist minister , administrator , and author .
Thomas Stoughton ( 1521 - -1576 ) , of Stoughton , Surrey and West Stoke , Sussex , was an English politician .
Daniel Kraemer ( 1816 - -1882 ) was the first English - speaking pioneer to settle Placentia , California .
Cyril Lloyd Jones , ( 1881 - -1981 ) , was a British railway engineer , joined the Nizam 's State Railways ( NSR ) in 1904 and was associated with NSR for until 1934 .
Johannes Stadius or Estadius ( Flemish : Jan Van Ostaeyen ; French : Jean Stade ) ( ca . 1 May 1527 -- 17 June 1579 ) , was a Belgian astronomer , astrologer , and mathematician .
Ímar mac Arailt ( died 1054 ) was an eleventh - century ruler of Kingdom of Dublin and perhaps the Kingdom of the Isles as well .
Marcel Wolfers ( 1886 - -1976 ) was a Belgian sculptor , well known for his war memorials completed in the Interwar Period ( 1919 - -39 ) .
John Faunce Leavitt ( 1905 - -1974 ) was a well - known shipbuilder , writer on maritime subjects , painter of marine canvases , and curator of Mystic Seaport in Mystic , Connecticut .
Armindo Rodrigues de Sttau Monteiro ( 16 December 1896 -- 15 October 1955 ) , known as Armindo Monteiro , was a Portuguese university professor , businessman , diplomat and politician who exercised important functions during the Estado Novo period .
Haim Ben - Asher ( Hebrew : חיים בן - אשר‎ , born Haim Finkel on 10 July 1904 , died 14 July 1998 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Mapai between 1949 and 1955 .
Albert Lange Fliflet ( 10 May 1908 -- 14 April 2001 ) was a Norwegian philologist and translator .
Sextus Aurelius Victor ( c. 320 -- c. 390 ) was a historian and politician of the Roman Empire .
Bob Gosani ( b. 1934 d. 1972 ) was a South African photographer .
John Maron ( Arabic : يوحنا مارون‎ , Youhana Maroun ; Latin : Ioannes Maronus ) ( born in 628 in Sirmaniyah or Sarmin , present Syria -- died in 707 in Kfarhy , Lebanon ) , was a Syriac monk , and the first Maronite Patriarch .
Hildebrando Castro Pozo ( 1890 - -1945 ) was a Peruvian sociologist and politician .
Thomas Papillon ( 1623 - -1702 ) was an English merchant and politician , an influential figure in the City of London for half a century .
William Jonathan `` Jonty '' Alsop ( 1901 - -1964 ) was a professional boxer from Wales who fought under the name Young Allsopp .
Anton Johnson Brandt ( 21 March 1893 -- 14 October 1951 ) was a Norwegian veterinarian .
Sigrid Sparre ( Sigrid Maria Josefina Ingeborg Richissa Eufemia Ulfhild ; 1 September 1825 -- 17 November 1910 ) was a Swedish lady in waiting and noblewoman , known for her relationship with Charles XV of Sweden .
William J. Blake ( 1894 - -1968 ) was a broker , novelist and Marxist political economist .
Henry Geiger ( August 10 , 1908 - 15 February 1989 ) was the editor , publisher , and chief writer of MANAS Journal which was published from 1948 - 1988 .
Sir Evan Williams , 1st Baronet , of Glyndwr ( 2 July 1871 -- 3 February 1959 ) was a Welsh industrialist .
Samuel Storey , Baron Buckton ( 18 January 1896 -- 17 January 1978 ) , known as Sir Samuel Storey , 1st Baronet , from 1960 to 1966 , was a British Conservative politician .
Gifford A. Cochran ( died 1930 ) was an American entrepreneur and sportsman from New York City .
Duke Alexander of Württemberg ( 20 December 1804 -- 28 October 1881 ) was a member of the dynasty which ruled the German kingdom of Württemberg .
William Usmar ( b. 4 Oct 1812 , d. 12 May 1879 ) was married to Bridget Terry Smart ( b. 18 Jul 1811 , d. circa 1881 ) on 5 Jul 1840 at the Parish Church in Maidstone , Kent , England .
Pietro della Vecchia , also sometimes known as Pietro Muttoni , ( 1603 -- 8 September 1678 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .
Oliver Chase Quick ( 21 June 1885 , Sedberg , now Cumbria -- 21 January 1944 , Longborough , Gloucester ) was an English theologian and Anglican priest .
Major General Charles Scrope Hutchinson R.E. C.B. ( 1826 - 1912 ) was Chief Inspecting Officer for Railways from 1892 to 1895 .
Margaret Gray ( 1913 - -2010 ) was a teacher and school head , most notably serving as head of the Godolphin and Latymer School from 1963 to 1973 .
William Mowse ( Mouse , Mosse ) ( died 1588 ) was an English lawyer and Master of Trinity Hall , Cambridge .
Sir Henry Bunbury , 3rd Baronet ( 29 November 1676 -- 12 February 1733 ) was a British Tory politician .
Tetsumi Kudo ( 23 February 1935 -- 12 November 1990 ) , was a Japanese artist associated with the Neo - Dada tradition .
Marko Natlačen ( 24 April 1886 -- 13 October 1942 ) was a Slovenian politician and jurist , who also served as the last ban ( Governor ) of the Drava Banovina in the Kingdom of Yugoslavia .
Air Marshal Sir Charles Broughton KBE , CB ( 27 April 1911 -- 17 May 1998 ) was a Royal Air Force officer who became Air Member for Supply and Organisation .
Ljudevit ( pronounced ( ʎûdeʋit ) ) or Liudewit ( Latin : Liudewitus , often also Ljudevit Posavski ) , was the Duke of Lower Pannonia from 810 to 823 .
Antonio Salamone ( December 12 , 1918 in San Giuseppe Jato -- May 31 , 1998 in São Paulo ) was a member of the Sicilian Mafia and a member of the first Sicilian Mafia Commission .
Helena of Oświęcim ( Polish : Helena Oświęcimska ; 1478/80 -- after 1524 ) , was a Polish princess member of the House of Piast from the Oświęcim branch and ruling Duchess of Karniów since 1506 until 1523 .
Hannibal Vyvyan , sometimes spelled Vivian ( 1545 -- 4 February 1610 ) , of Trelowarren in Cornwall , was an English Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
James Halpin ( June 1843 - 26 July 1909 ) was an Irish farmer , building contractor and politician .
Captain F. W. L. Thomas , c.1812 - 1885 , RN , FSA ( Scot ) was a naval officer , photographer , and historian .
Robert Reece ( 2 May 1838 -- 8 July 1891 ) was a British comic playwright and librettist active in the Victorian era .
Heinrich Kramer ( c. 1430 -- 1505 ) , also known under the Latinized name Henricus Institor , was a German churchman and inquisitor .
Hiram Edson ( 1806 - -1882 ) was a pioneer of the Seventh - day Adventist Church , known for introducing the sanctuary doctrine ( investigative judgment ) to the church .
Ensign Charles Ewart ( 1769 -- 23 May 1846 ) was a Scottish soldier of the Royal North British Dragoons ( more commonly known as the Scots Greys ) , famous for capturing the regimental eagle of the 45e Régiment de Ligne ( 45th Regiment of the Line ) at the Battle of Waterloo .
Mario Mellado García ( died October 2014 ) was a Mexican lawyer , politician and judge .
Henri Caesar , also known as Black Caesar , ( fl . 1791 - 1830 ) was allegedly a 19th - century Haitian revolutionary and pirate .
Vasco da Gama Rodrigues ( 27 January 1909 , Paul do Mar , Madeira - 3 May 1991 ) , was a Portuguese poet .
Antonio Madiona ( Siracusa - Siracusa , 1719 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .
Major - General Arthur Wollaston Bartholomew CB CMG CBE DSO ( 5 May 1878 -- 29 January 1945 ) was Commander of British Troops in China .
Nikolaos Kontopoulos ( Greek : Νικόλαος Κοντόπουλος , 1889 - 1958 ) was a Greek writer .
Richard Holmlund ( 26 October 1963 -- 5 October 2011 ) was a Swedish football manager .
Are Vesterlid ( 28 July 1921 -- 29 August 2013 ) was a Norwegian architect .
Peter Finnerty ( 1766?--11 May 1822 ) was an Irish printer and publisher , and a United Irishman .
Arthur Sidney Lyon ( 1817 - -1861 ) , was a journalist and newspaper proprietor , who was also known as ' the father of the press in colonial Queensland ' .
Sir John Dalzell , 2nd Baronet ( died 1689 ) was a Scottish politician .
Mustafa Necati died due to appendicitis on 1 January 1929 , the very same day the Nation Schools were opened .
Frank Dennis ( 11 June 1907 -- 21 November 2000 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played in 89 matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club from 1928 to 1933 , and three for the Minor Counties from 1936 to 1939 .
Joseph Riddick ( 1735 - Nov. 18 , 1818 ) was a North Carolina politician who served as Speaker of the North Carolina Senate for 11 years from 1800 to 1804 and from 1806 to 1811 .
Don Juan de Guzmán Itztolinqui ( reigned 1526 - -1569 ) was a post - Conquest tlatoani ( ruler ) of the altepetl ( ethnic state ) of Coyoacán in the Valley of Mexico .
David Dewaele ( born 19 March 1976 in Hazebrouck , Nord - Pas - de - Calais as David Sébastien Dewaele ; died 27 February 2013 in Hazebrouck ) was a French actor .
Michael Kantakouzenos or Cantacuzenus ( Greek : Μιχαήλ Καντακουζηνός , died 3 March 1578 ) , nicknamed Şeytanoğlu ( Turkish for `` son of the Devil '' ) , was an Ottoman Greek magnate , noted for his immense wealth and political influence .
Andy Whitfield ( died 11 September 2011 ) was a Welsh actor .
John Davies Knatchbull Lloyd(28 April 1900 - -13 December 1978 ) , generally known as J. D. K. Lloyd , was born on 28 April 1900 at Plas Trefaldwyn , Montgomery in the present day county of Powys in mid Wales .
Ludwig Rabus ( also Rab or Günzer ) ( 10 October 1523 -- 22 July 1592 ) was a German Lutheran theologian .
Abd al - Mu'min ( 1094 - -1163 ) also known as Abdelmoumen al - Goumi ( Arabic : عبد المؤمن بن علي or عبد المومن الــكـومي‎ , Berber : ⵄⴰⴱⴷ ⵍⵎⵓⵎⵏ ⵍⴳⵓⵎⵉ ) was a prominent member of the Almohad movement .
William John Finley Warren ( December 14 , 1873 -- 1963 ) was a farmer , rancher and political figure in Saskatchewan .
Emil Blichfeldt ( 5 November 1849 -- 20 October 1908 ) was a Danish architect who worked in the Historicist style .
Elizabeth Knepp or Knipp ( died 1681 ) was a British actress , singer , and dancer .
Karl Dietrich Leonhard Engel ( born Oldenburg , 21 February 1824 ; died Adlershof , February 1913 ) was a German musician and writer .
Astrid Ydén ( 1881 - 1963 ) was a Swedish harpist .
Herman Baer ( born of Jewish parents in Herxheim , Germany , Jan. 29 , 1830 ; died Charleston , South Carolina , Jan. 2 , 1901 ) was an American author .
Michael Sprinker ( 8 February 1950 in Elgin , Illinois -- 12 August 1999 ) was a literary critic known for his writings on Louis Althusser , Walter Benjamin and Bertolt Brecht , among others , as well as for his editorial work at Verso , Cambridge University Press , the New Left Review and The Minnesota Review .
Richard Bruce Arthur ( 2 November 1921 -- 22 March 1998 ) was an Australian freestyle wrestler who won a silver medal in the middleweight division at the 1950 British Empire Games ; he finished fourth in 1954 .
Mary Smith Lockwood ( 1831 - 1922 ) was one of the founders of the Daughters of the American Revolution .
Conyers Darcy , 2nd Earl of Holderness ( 1622 -- 13 December 1692 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1679 and later became a peer .
Raja Swarup Singh ( 30 May 1812 -- 26 January 1864 ) was a Sikh Raja of Jind of the Phulkian dynasty who reigned from 1834 to 1864 .
Edward Bailey ( 1814 - -1903 ) was the most accomplished of the Hawaiian missionary period artists in Hawaii .
György Deák - Bárdos ( 1905 in Budapest -- 1991 ) was a Hungarian composer , organist , singer and music teacher .
Avgust Berthold ( 20 July 1880 -- 1 August 1919 ) was a Slovenian photographer who is associated with the Impressionist movement .
Alban Francis ( died 1715 ) was an English Benedictine monk .
Tuan Guru Dato ' Bentara Setia Haji Nik Abdul Aziz Nik Mat ( 10 January 1931 -- 12 February 2015 ) was a Malaysian politician and Muslim cleric .
Sir Ralph Kilner Brown , OBE , TD , DL ( 28 August 1909 -- 15 June 2003 ) , was a British hurdling athlete , Liberal Party politician and judge .
Injong of Goryeo ( 29 October 1109 -- 10 April 1146 ) ( r. 1122 - -1146 ) was the 17th monarch of the Korean Goryeo dynasty .
Manfred Wimmer ( 1944 - -1995 ) was the first Western professional go player .
Elizur Wright ( 12 February 1804 -- 22 November 1885 ) was an American mathematician and abolitionist .
Dennis Howard Green ( 26 June 1922 -- 5 December 2008 ) was Schröder Professor of German at the University of Cambridge .
Heikki Nurmio ( 1887 - 1947 ) - Finnish jäger and writer .
Kristian Lerche Bøckman ( 11 March 1887 -- 1974 ) was a Norwegian mining director .
Henry Howard , 5th Earl of Suffolk ( 18 July 1627 -- 10 December 1709 ) was the youngest son of Theophilus Howard , 2nd Earl of Suffolk , but inherited the title , because none of his brothers left surviving sons .
Yujiulü Wuti ( Chinese : 郁久閭吳提 ; pinyin : Yùjiǔlǘ Wútí ) khan of the Rouran ( July , 429-September , 444 ) with the title of Chilian Khan ( 敕連可汗 ) .
Franz Hübner(18 November 1846 Drossen , near Frankfurt an der Oder - 31 December 1877 ) was a German entomologist Between 1875 and 1877 he collected insects for the Museum Godeffroy in Samoa , Tonga and New Britain .
Otto Frederick Hunziker ( 25 December 1873 -- 16 November 1959 ) was a pioneer in the American and international dairy industry , as both an educator and a technical innovator .
Henry Thew Stevenson ( April 22 , 1870 -- 1957 ) was a teacher and writer .
Alexander George Findlay ( 1812 - -1875 ) was an English geographer and hydrographer .
Birgitte Christine Kaas , married Huitfeldt ( 2 October 1682 -- 14 August 1761 ) was a Norwegian poet and translator of psalms .
Michael Craze ( 29 November 1942 -- 8 December 1998 ) was a British actor noted for his role of Ben Jackson , a companion of the Doctor , in the long - running BBC science fiction television series Doctor Who .
Paul Bern ( December 3 , 1889 -- September 5 , 1932 ) was a German - born American film director , screenwriter and producer for MGM , where he became the assistant to Irving Thalberg .
Ahmad Lozi ( also spelled Ahmad al - Lawzi ) ( 1925 -- 18 November 2014 ) was a Jordanian politician .
Richard Peter Tudor Sillett ( known as Peter Sillett ) ( 1 February 1933 -- 13 March 1998 ) was an England footballer .
Sinan Şamil Sam ( 23 June 1974 -- 30 October 2015 ) was a Turkish heavyweight professional boxer .
Yohanna Barnaba Abdallah ( died 1924 ) was a clergyman and historian of the Yao people of central Africa .
Sergei Chavain , also spelled Čavajn ( Mari : Сергей Чавайн , pronounced ( tʃɑˈβɑɪn ) ; 6 October 1888 , Maly Karamas -- 11 November 1937 ) was a Mari poet and playwright , born Sergei Grigorievich Grigoriev ( Russian : Серге́й Григо́рьевич Григо́рьев ) .
John Bowes , 1st Baron Bowes PC ( I ) ( 1691 -- 22 July 1767 ) was an Anglo - Irish peer politician and judge , noted for his great legal ability , but also for his hostility to Roman Catholics .
Christy Keogh ( 29 June 1943 -- 19 July 2002 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a left corner - forward for the Wexford senior team .
Montague Gore ( 1800 - 8 September 1864 ) , was a British politician and author .
Kjetil Mårdalen ( 12 January 1925 -- 4 November 1996 ) was a Norwegian nordic combined skier who competed in the 1950s .
Herbert James Carter ( 23 April 1858 -- 16 April 1940 ) was an English - born Australian schoolmaster and entomologist .
Vice - Admiral James Hosken ( 6 December 1798 -- 2 January 1885 ) was a British naval officer and a pioneer of ocean steam navigation .
Ngamaru Rongotini Ariki ( c. 1831 -- 31 March 1903 ) was a sovereign of the Cook Islands .
Manche Masemola ( 1913 - -1928 ) is a South African Christian martyr .
John Knill ( 1 January 1733 -- 29 March 1811 ) born at Callington in Cornwall was a slightly eccentric mayor of St Ives , Cornwall , UK , in 1767 and Collector of Customs at St Ives from 1762 - -1782 .
Pavao Tijan ( born in Senj in 1908 - died in Madrid in 1997 ) was a Croatian encyclopaedist who spent the latter half of his life in Spain .
Georg Monsen ( 19 December 1922 -- 10 April 2015 ) was a Norwegian former footballer and football manager .
Shakir Mustafa Salim ( 1919 - 1985 ) was a famous Iraqi social anthropologist who taught in the Department of Sociology at Baghdad University .
Edward Wedlake Brayley ( 1773 -- 23 September 1854 ) was an English antiquary and topographer , closely associated with John Britton .
David Irvin ( 1794 - -1872 ) was a United States territorial judge .
Xu Zhongxing ( ? - 1578 ) was a Chinese litterateur of the Ming Dynasty .
Tom Drummond ( 6 August 1897 -- 26 May 1970 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thane Houser ( 27 July 1891 Honey Creek , Indiana --23 November 1967 Columbus , Indiana ) was an American racecar driver .
H. B. Parkinson ( 29 September 1884 -- 19 August 1970 ) was a British film pioneer .
Abraham van Blijenberch ( or Blyenberch ) ( 1575/6 - 1624 ) was a Flemish painter .
Madhukar Dattatraya Deoras ( 11 December 1915 - 17 June 1996 ) , popularly known as Balasaheb Deoras , was the third Sarsanghchalak of the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh ( RSS ) .
Molly Dingle MBE ( 1892 -- 1974 ) educator , born St. John 's , Newfoundland .
John Whistler ( ca . 1756 -- 3 September 1829 ) was a soldier , born in Ulster , Ireland .
Tomás Ó Con Cheanainn ( 1921 -- 13 June 2015 ) was an Irish scholar and historian .
Ellsworth Young ( 1866 Albia , Iowa -- 1952 Evanston , Illinois ) was an American magazine and book illustrator , and a noted painter of landscapes .
Anaximenes of Miletus ( /ˌænækˈsɪməˌniːz/ ; Greek : Ἀναξιμένης ; c. 585 -- c. 528 BCE ) was an Ancient Greek Pre - Socratic philosopher active in the latter half of the 6th century BC . One of the three Milesian philosophers , he is identified as a younger friend or student of Anaximander .
Mary Irene Parlby ( née Marryat ; 9 January 1868 -- 12 July 1965 ) was a Canadian women 's farm leader , activist and politician .
Bridgetta Clark ( January 13 , 1891 - November 1980 ) was an American silent film actress .
Publius Metilius Nepos ( c. 45 - -118 ) was a Roman politician during the late 1st century .
Christopher Saxton died in either 1610 or 1611 .
John Wigham Richardson ( 7 January 1837 -- 15 April 1908 ) was a British shipbuilder on Tyneside during the late 19th and early 20th century .
Marina Yurlova ( Russian : Мари́на Максимилиа́новна Ю́рлова ; 25 February 1900 - 1 April 1984 ) was a Russian child soldier and author .
James Jago FRS , ( 1815 -- 1893 ) was an English physician .
Johann Adam Hoyer was a clockmaker and master craftsman in Josefstadt ( now the 8th district of Vienna ) died 1838 .
Rosetta Sherwood Hall ( born Liberty , Sullivan County , New York ; September 19 , 1865 , died 1951 ) was a medical missionary and educator .
Sir Robert Broke SL ( died 5 or 6 September 1558 ) was a British justice , politician and legal writer .
Sir William Wilkinson Addison ( 4 April 1905 -- 1 November 1992 ) , was an English historian , author and jurist .
Andrew Brice ( 1690 - -1773 ) was an English printer and writer .
Shmuel Shilo or Shmulik Shiloh ( Hebrew : שמואל שילה‎ , 1 December 1929 -- 4 October 2011 ) was an Israeli actor , director and producer , born in the Second Polish Republic , and best remembered for his role on the Israeli production of Rechov SumSum , a popular TV show based on Sesame Street .
Aristeidis Dimitratos ( Greek : Αριστείδης Δημητράτος ) ( 1902 - 1986 ) was a Greek trade union functionary and politician .
Jan Tomasz Drohojowski from Drohojów ( b. 1535 , d .. 12 November 1605 in Przemyśl ) was a Polish nobleman , referendarz wielki koronny , starosta of Przemyśl , a Polish ambsaadaor in Istanbul in 1578 , an owner of the castle in Rybotycze .
Cheng Qian ( simplified Chinese : 程潜 ; traditional Chinese : 程潛 ; pinyin : Chéng Qián ; Wade -- Giles : Ch'eng Ch'ien ; 31 March 1882 -- 5 April 1968 ) was a Chinese military general .
Alban Thomas ( 1686 - -1771 ) was a Welsh doctor , librarian and antiquarian , who followed in his father 's footsteps in supporting Welsh literature , being particularly associated with efforts by Moses Williams to publish Welsh - language manuscripts .
Wilfred Carter ( 19 June 1896 -- 1 November 1975 ) was an English sportsman who played first class cricket for Derbyshire County Cricket Club between 1920 and 1926 and football for Watford Football Club at the same time .
Chandra Kumar De ( Chondrokumar De ) ( 1889 - -1946 ) was a writer and collector of medieval folklore and folk ballads of East Bengal villages , mostly in Mymensingh now in Bangladesh .
James Hans Hamilton ( February 1810 -- 30 June 1863 ) , was an Anglo - Irish Member of Parliament .
Dennis Nikrasch ( September 12 , 1941 -- 2010 ) was a Vegas slot cheater and a former locksmith who was responsible for spearheading the biggest casino theft in Las Vegas history , by grabbing $ 16,000,000 from rigging slot machines over a 22-year period .
Father Edward Yarnold S.J. ( 14 January 1926 -- 23 July 2002 ) was a prominent Jesuit theologian and Master of Campion Hall from 1965 to 1972 at the University of Oxford in England .
József Ficzkó or Fitzkó ( Burgenland Croatian : Jožef Ficko ) ( 15 March 1772 -- 28 November 1843 ) was a Slovene born Roman Catholic priest and writer .
Martin Bucer ( early German : Martin Butzer ) ( 11 November 1491 -- 28 February 1551 ) was a German Protestant reformer based in Strasbourg who influenced Lutheran , Calvinist , and Anglican doctrines and practices .
B. V. Subbamma also known as Bathineni , Venkata Subbamma ( 1 July 1925 -- 12 January 2009 ) was an Indian theologian and scholar .
Diogo de Mendonça Corte - Real ( 17 June 1658 -- 9 May 1736 ) was an accomplished Portuguese diplomat and statesman , and Secretary of State to King Peter II and John V.
Air Vice - Marshal George Henry Morley CB CBE(Mil . ) OBE FRCS ( 22 February 1907- 26 May 1971 ) was a British military doctor , an expert on plastic surgery , particularly the treatment of burns , and senior RAF officer .
Robert Lee Burns ( 1930/31 -- 2002 ) was an American bank robber who was the subject of an interstate battle over an issue of parole of convicted criminals .
Christopher Hinton , Baron Hinton of Bankside OM KBE FRS FREng ( 12 May 1901 -- 22 June 1983 ) was a British nuclear engineer , and supervisor of the construction of Calder Hall , the world 's first large - scale commercial nuclear power station .
Nellie Wallace ( 18 March 1870 -- 24 November 1948 ) was a British music hall star , actress , comedienne , dancer and songwriter who became one of the most famous and best loved music hall performers .
Abu Ayyub Sulayman ibn Wahb ( died July / August 885 ) was a senior official of the Abbasid Caliphate who served several times as vizier .
Thomas Hailes Lacy ( 1809 - 1 August 1873 ) was a British actor , playwright , theatrical manager , bookseller , and theatrical publisher .
Johan Bergenstråhle ( 13 May 1756 -- 7 March 1840 in Stockholm ) was a Swedish military officer who participated in Russo - Swedish War ( 1788 - 1790 ) , and the Finnish War .
William George Ward ( 21 March 1812 -- 6 July 1882 ) was an English theologian and mathematician .
Johannes Mensing ( Mensingk ) ( 1477 - -1547 ) was a German Dominican theologian and controversialist , an opponent of Martin Luther .
Tang Wing - Cheung ( Chinese : 鄧永祥 ; 20 June 1916 -- 20 April 1997 ) , MBE , better known by his stage name Sun Ma Sze Tsang ( Chinese : 新馬師曾 ; literally : `` New Ma Sze - Tsang '' ) , was a Cantonese opera singer and actor in Hong Kong .
Augustín Malár ( 18 July 1894 Reitern , Austria -- ? 1945 , Sachsenhausen ) was a Slovak general during World War II .
Sir John Knatchbull , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1636 -- 15 December 1696 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1660 and 1690 .
Harold Rayner ( 27 July 1888 -- 8 December 1954 ) was an American fencer and modern pentathlete .
Svend Johansen ( 10 September 1890 -- 6 October 1970 ) was a Danish painter , scenographer and illustrator .
Yigal Hurvitz ( Hebrew : ; יִגָּאֵל הורביץ‎‎ 1918 -- 10 January 1994 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a government minister in the late 1970s and 1980s .
Pope Valentine ( in Latin : Valentinus ; 800 -- 10 October 827 ) was Pope for two months in 827 .
Andrea Procaccini ( 14 January 1671 -- 1734 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active in Rome as well as in Spain .
Air Marshal Sir ( Horace Ernest ) Philip Wigglesworth , KBE , CB , DSC ( 11 July 1896 -- 31 May 1975 ) was a senior officer in the Royal Air Force .
D. D. Thacker ( 1884 - -1961 ) better known was Diwan Bahadur D. D. Thacker , FRSA was a noted coal miner and philanthropist from Jharia , Dhanbad .
Tun Ledang Shah ( 1234 - -1463 ) was a mythical character ( who was probably based on a real person ) in the ancient Malay history who was assumed to live during the 13th century Srivijayan Empire till the 15th century Sultanate of Malacca .
Gopinath Saha ( 1906 - 1924 ) was a Bengali activist for Indian independence ( from British rule ) and member of the Hindustan Republican Association .
Pietro Aron , also known as Pietro ( or Piero ) Aaron ( ca . 1480 -- after 1545 ) , was an Italian music theorist and composer .
Francisco Tito Yupanqui ( 1550 - -1616 ) was an indigenous Bolivian sculptor .
Thomas Hawksley ( 12 July 1807 -- 15 September 1893 ) was an English civil engineer of the 19th century , particularly associated with early water supply and coal gas engineering projects .
Zalman Susayeff ( also Suzayev ) ( Hebrew : זלמן סוזאיב‎ , born 14 February 1911 , died 25 February 1981 ) was an Israeli businessman and politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the General Zionists between 1951 and 1959 .
Karl Leander Ikonen ( 14 October 1860 , Joroinen - 27 April 1918 , Viipuri ) was a Finnish architect and politician .
Annetto Casolani ( 10 August 1815 - 1 August 1866 ) was a Maltese prelate who served as the first Apostolic Vicar of Central Africa present day Archdiocese of Khartoum in Sudan .
Henning Haslund - Christensen ( 31 August 1896 -- 13 September 1948 ) was a Danish travel writer and anthropologist .
Bruno Mora ( 29 March 1937 -- 10 December 1986 ) was an Italian football player and coach , who played as a right winger ; during his prime he was regarded as one of the best players in the world in his position .
Bela Marsh ( 1797 - 1869 ) was a publisher and bookseller in Boston , Massachusetts , in the 19th century .
Joseph Churba ( c. 1934 - 18 April 1996 ) was a United States Air Force Middle East intelligence expert , author , and political activist known for his support of Israel .
Edith Ogden Harrison ( 16 November 1862 -- 22 May 1955 ) was a well - known and prolific author of children 's books and fairy tales in the early decades of the twentieth century .
Samantha Dubois ( 15 January 1955 -- 1 October 1992 ) was a radio presenter on Radio Caroline during the 1970s and again in 1984 .
John Houlton Marshall ( 9 October 1768 in Halifax , Nova Scotia -- 2 May 1837 in Charlotte Street , Bloomsbury Square , Middlesex ) was a Nova Scotian who was a naval commander throughout the Napoleonic Wars .
Lydia Mackenzie Falconer Miller or Harriet Myrtle ( 1812 -- 11 March 1876 ) was a British writer for children .
Manuel António Vassalo e Silva ( Torres Novas , 8 November 1899 -- Lisbon , 11 August 1985 ) was an officer of the Portuguese Army and an overseas administrator .
John Devereux , 8th Baron Ferrers of Chartley ( 1463 -- 3 May 1501 ) was an English peer .
Gustav Lange ( 13 August 1830 -- 20 July 1889 ) was a German composer known mainly for his melodious salon music for the piano .
Colonel John Mount Batten CB JP ( 7 April 1843 -- 5 March 1916 ) was a British soldier and landowner .
Ralph Knevet ( 1600 - 1671 ) was an English clergyman and poet .
Tunku Abdul Malik ibni Sultan Badlishah ( 24 September 1929 -- 29 November 2015 ) was the heir presumptive to the throne of Kedah .
Surjit Singh Sandhawalia ( 27 July 1925 -- 16 November 2007 ) was a Chief Justice of the Punjab & Haryana High Court from July 1978 to November 1983 .
Hugh Henshall ( 1734 - -1816 ) was an English civil engineer , noted for his work on canals .
William Romaine Callender ( junior ) ( 1825 -- 22 January 1876 ) was a British businessman and Conservative politician .
Fred Longden ( 23 February 1888 -- 5 October 1952 ) was a British Labour Co - operative politician .
Ernst von Rüchel ( 21 July 1754 -- 14 January 1823 ) was a Prussian general who led an army corps in a crushing defeat by Napoleon at the Battle of Jena on 14 October 1806 .
Altamiro Rossato ( 23 June 1925 -- 13 May 2014 ) was a Brazilian Roman Catholic prelate and Archbishop Emeritus of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Porto Alegre .
Harry Wolstenholme ( 21 June 1868 -- 14 October 1930 ) was an Australian lawyer and ornithologist .
Earl Ottir ( Old Norse : Óttar jarl ; Medieval Latin : Oter comes , ' Count Oter ' ; died 918 ) , also known as Ottir the Black ( Old Irish : Ottir Dub ) , was a jarl who occupied a prominent position among the Norse of Britain and Ireland in the early 10th century .
Eliza Fletcher , née Dawson ( 15 January 15 , 1770 -- 5 February 1858 ) was a British autobiographer and early travel writer .
Yemi Ajibade ( 28 July 1929 -- 24 January 2013 ) , also credited as Yemi Goodman Ajibade or Ade - Yemi Ajibade , was a Nigerian playwright and actor who , after settling in England in the 1950s , made significant contributions to the British theatre and the canon of Black drama .
Girim of Silla ( r. 298 - 310 , died 310 ) , whose name is sometimes given as Girip and also as Gigu , was the fifteenth king of Silla .
William Fletcher Burden ( 14 March 1830 -- 7 December 1867 ) was an industrialist born in Troy , New York .
Robert d'Aguiló ( c. 1100 -- c. 1159 ) , also known as Robert Bordet , was a Norman knight who moved from Normandy to Catalonia in the early 12th century .
Jacob Coning or Jacob Koninck II ( c. 1647 -- 16 July 1724 ) was a Dutch - Danish painter who was painter to the Danish Court .
Qian Xuantong ( 1887 - -January 17 , 1939 ) was a Chinese linguist , and along with Gu Jiegang , one of the leaders of the Doubting Antiquity School .
Prince Ernst August of Lippe ( German : Prinz Ernst August Bernhard Alexander Eduard Friedrich Wilhelm zur Lippe ; 1 April 1917 -- 15 June 1990 ) was a claimant to the headship of the House of Lippe .
Andriy II Yuriyevych or Andrew of Galicia ( Ukrainian : Андрій II Юрієвич ) ( unknown -- 1323 ) was the last Rus ' king of Galicia - Volhynia in 1308 - -1323 ( according to other sources since 1315 ) .
Edward Davy ( 16 June 1806 -- 26 January 1885 ) was an English physician , scientist , and inventor who played a prominent role in the development of telegraphy , and invented an electric relay .
John Thomas Jutson ( c. 1885 -- 14 November 1959 ) was an Australian geologist and lawyer .
John Oxlee ( 1779 - -1854 ) was an English cleric , philologist and writer on theology .
James Bermingham was Bishop of Killala from 1344 to 1346 .
Erling Sverdrup ( 23 February 1917 -- 15 March 1994 ) was a Norwegian statistician and actuarial mathematician .
Blessed Liborius Wagner ( 5 December 1593 -- 9 December 1631 ) was a German Roman Catholic priest .
Henry Ainsworth ( 1571 - -1622 ) was an English Nonconformist clergyman and scholar .
Reverend James Osborne Arthur , Sr . ( 1887 - -1971 ) along with his wife Katherine Arthur ( 1883 - -1960 ) were missionaries for the Reformed Church of America .
Muhammad Mueenuddeen I was the sultan of the Maldives from 1798 to 1835 .
Ebenezer Jones ( 1820 - -1860 ) wrote a good deal of poetry of very unequal merit , but at his best shows a true poetic vein .
Joan Bridge ( 13 March 1912 - 8 December 2009 ) was a British costume designer .
Ayatollah Sayyid Muhammad Ali al - Hakim ( 1911 - -2011 ) was a high - ranking Shiite ayatollah .
Donald Larnach ( 17 July 1817 -- 12 May 1896 ) was a banker , financier and High Sheriff of Sussex in 1882 .
Mione Elizabeth George Israel ( died October 14 , 2003 ) , known as Mione `` Minette '' George for much of her life , and as Elizabeth Israel and Ma Pampo later in life , was the focus of one of the most widely publicized longevity claims of recent years .
Xiao Ni ( 蕭嶷 ) ( 444 - -492 ) , courtesy name Xuanyan ( 宣儼 ) , formally Prince Wenxian of Yuzhang ( 豫章文獻王 ) , was an imperial prince during the Chinese dynasty Southern Qi .
Mark Ellidge ( Born 1940 , died 9 January 2010 ) was a British press photographer .
George Compton , 4th Earl of Northampton , PC ( 18 October 1664 -- 15 April 1727 ) , styled Lord Compton from 1664 to 1681 , was a British peer .
José Toribio Aguilera Coello ( 7 March 1941 -- 10 June 2014 ) was a Honduran economist and politician .
Boris Pregel ( Russian : Борис Юльевич Прегель ; 24 January 1893 -- 7 December 1976 ) was a Ukrainian - born Jewish engineer and dealer in uranium and radium .
Robert Forde ( 29 August 1875 -- 13 March 1959 ) was an Antarctic explorer and member of the Terra Nova Expedition under Captain Robert Falcon Scott from 1910 - -1912 .
Doctor Ezekiel Ezra Smith ( also E.E. Smith ; 1852 - -1933 ) was the U.S. Ambassador to Liberia ( 1888 - -1890 ) and President of Fayetteville State University .
William Feinbloom ( born Brooklyn 1904 , died 1985 ) was an American optometrist considered to be a pioneer in the field of low vision , visual rehabilitation , and the development of low vision devices .
Xiao Zisheng ( simplified Chinese : 萧子升 ; traditional Chinese : 蕭子升 ; pinyin : Xiāo Zǐshēng ; 22 August 1894 - 21 November 1976 ) was a Chinese educator and scholar .
Walter Alison Phillips ( 21 October 1864 -- 28 October 1950 ) was an English historian , a specialist in the history of Europe in the 19th century .
Sir Robert Spottiswood , Lord Newabbey ( 1596 - -1646 ) , was a Scottish lawyer .
Charles Andreae ( 16 December 1906 -- 22 June 1970 ) was an English first class cricketer who played all his games for Cambridge University Cricket Club .
Ichirai ( 一来 , died 1180 ) was a Japanese warrior monk who supported the Minamoto clan of samurai against their rivals , the Taira clan .
Sir Thomas Allen , 1st Baronet ( c. 1633 -- 15 December 1690 ) also spelt Aleyn or Alleyn , was an English politician and grocer .
Frederick George Waterhouse ( 25 August 1815 -- 7 September 1898 ) was an English naturalist , zoologist and entomologist who made significant contributions to the study of the natural history of Australia .
Seaton Gales ( 1828 - 1878 ) was editor of the Raleigh Register and a junior editor of the Raleigh Sentinel .
Frances Greville née Macartney ( c 1724 -- 1789 ) was an Irish poet and celebrity in Georgian England .
Johan Bax van Herenthals ( 14 March 1637 ' s - Hertogenbosch -- 29 June 1678 , Cape Town ) , also written as Joan Bax , and van Herentals , was governor of the Dutch Cape Colony from 1676 succeeding the acting interim governor Ijsbrand Godske .
Lord Neill Campbell ( c. 1630 -- April 1692 ) was a Scottish nobleman who served as Deputy Governor of East New Jersey during 1686 , succeeding Gawen Lawrie .
Joseph Herrick ( August 6 , 1645 -- ca . 1710 ) was the principal law enforcement officer in Salem , Massachusetts during the Salem Witchcraft Trials of 1692 .
Gualterus Schneider ( 23 November 1772 - 10 September 1841 ) was the 3rd Surveyor General of Ceylon .
Harold McCracken ( 1894 - 1983 ) was an American author , Alaskan grizzly bear hunter , biplane stunt photographer , cinematographer , producer and museum director .
Daniel C. Cooper ( November 21 , 1773 -- July 13 , 1818 ) was an American surveyor , farmer , miller and political leader .
Charles Edward Beevor ( 12 June 1854 -- 5 December 1908 ) was an English neurologist and anatomist who described Beevor 's sign , the Jaw jerk reflex , and the area of the brain supplied by the anterior choroidal artery .
Sahan Dosova , or Sakhan Dosova ( Kazakh : Сaxaн Дocoвa ; claimed 27 March 1879 ( ? ) -- 9 May 2009 ) was a Kazakhstani woman reputed by some to have been the oldest woman who ever lived .
Godfrey Goodman , also called Hugh ; ( 28 February 1582 or 1583 - -19 January 1656 ) was the Anglican Bishop of Gloucester , and a member of the Protestant Church .
Óengus of Moray ( Oenghus mac inghine Lulaich , ri Moréb ) was the last King of Moray of the native line , ruling Moray in what is now northeastern Scotland from some unknown date until his death in 1130 .
Carl Randau ( 8 August 1893 - April 1969 ) was an American playwright and journalist .
Hermann Knüfken ( 9 February , 1893 - 8 February , 1976 ) was a German trade unionist , communist activist and anti - fascist .
Eleanor McClatchy ( 1895 - 1980 ) was president of the McClatchy newspapers from 1936 until 1978 .
Xu Yuanquan ( 徐源泉 ; Hsü Yüan - ch'üan ; 1885 - -1960 ) was a Kuomintang general from Hubei .
Gisbert Steenwick ( also Gijsbert ) ( baptized 6 January 1642 -- buried 20 August 1679 ) was a Dutch composer , organist , and carillonneur .
August Brentano ( 1829 - November 2 , 1886 ) was a New York City newspaper dealer who was born in Hohenems , Austria .
Eliza Turck ( 1832 - -1891 ) , was an English portrait ( including miniatures ) , genre , bird and landscape painter , illustrator and writer .
Josefine Balluck ( 9 September 1908 -- 1984 ) was an Austrian actress with dwarfism , best known for her role as one of the Munchkins in the 1939 film The Wizard of Oz . Her dwarf brother Franz Balluck also appeared as a Munchkin in that same film .
John Baring , 2nd Baron Revelstoke PC DL ( 7 September 1863 -- 19 April 1929 ) , was senior partner of Barings Bank from the 1890s until his death .
Gugsa of Yejju ( died 23 May 1825 ) was a Ras of Begemder ( circa 1798 until his death ) , and Inderase ( regent ) of the Emperor of Ethiopia .
Sir William Wheler , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1611 -- 6 August 1666 ) of the city of Westminster , was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1640 and 1660 .
After the attempt on Commodus 's life in 182 , Saoterus was implicated in the plot by the praetorian prefect Tigidius Perennis , and was murdered by the freedman Cleander , who succeeded him as chamberlain .
Niels Carlsen ( 8 January 1734 -- 3 May 1809 ) was a Norwegian timber merchant and ship owner .
Qais bin Ahmad ( died May 1808 ) was the third son of Ahmad bin Sa'id Al - Busaidi , the first Sultan of Oman of the Al Said dynasty .
Gabriel Powell ( baptised 1576 - -1611 ) was a Welsh Anglican priest , known for his strident anti - Catholic views .
Frank Silver ( 1896 - -1960 ) , a U.S. songwriter .
Felicula ( died 90 AD ) was an early virgin martyr .
Christine Tamblyn ( July 12 , 1951 -- January 1 , 1998 ) was an American feminist media artist , critic , and educator .
Dora Batty ( 1900 - 1966 ) was a British designer , working in illustration , poster design , pottery and textiles .
John Hastings , 2nd Earl of Pembroke , KG ( 29 August 1347 -- 16 April 1375 ) , was an English nobleman and soldier who also held the title Baron Abergavenny .
Dafydd Benfras ( fl . 1230 - 1260 ) was a Welsh language court poet regarded by Saunders Lewis and others as one of the greatest of the ' Poets of the Princes ' ( Beirdd y Tywysogion ) .
Frederick Rowbottom ( 16 January 1938 -- 12 October 2009 ) was a British logician and mathematician .
Max Margulis ( 1907 - -1996 ) was an American musician , writer , music teacher , voice coach , record producer , copywriter , photographer and left - wing activist .
Sir Hugh Vaughan ( ? -- 28 August 1536 ) was born in Wales as a commoner to unknown parents , who later became Governor of Jersey ( or Captain ) .
Insoo Kim Berg ( 25 July 1934 -- 10 January 2007 ) was a Korean - born American psychotherapist who was a pioneer of solution focused brief therapy .
Bernice Bing ( 1936 - -1998 ) was a Chinese American artist born in San Francisco , California in 1936 .
George Townshend , 2nd Marquess Townshend , PC , FRS ( 18 April 1753 -- 27 July 1811 ) , known as The Lord Ferrers of Chartley from 1770 to 1784 and as The Earl of Leicester from 1784 to 1807 , was a British peer and politician .
Johann Joseph Fritz von Miller , known as Fritz von Miller ( 11 November 1840 - -29 December , 1921 ) was a German bronze caster , goldsmith and sculptor .
Cord Widderich ( alternative spelling : Kort Wiederich ) ( died 1447 ) was a pirate active during political conflicts between Dithmarschen and North Frisia in the early fifteenth century .
The Very Rev Leonard Coulshaw CB , MC , FKC ( 24 February 1896 -- 22 July 1988 ) was Chaplain of the Fleet and Archdeacon of the Royal Navy from 1948 to 1952 .
Handel Cossham ( 31 March 1824 -- 23 April 1890 ) was a British colliery owner , lay preacher and Liberal politician who was active in local government and sat in the House of Commons from 1885 to 1890 .
John Marcum ( 1913 - -1981 ) was the co - founder of ARCA and a NASCAR official from Toledo , Ohio , United States .
Raimondo Epifanio ( 1440 - -1482 ) was an Italian painter of the Renaissance period .
Francisco de Paula Andrade Troconis ( 1840 - -1915 ) was a Venezuelan engineer and journalist .
D'Arcy Rose ( 14 August 1888 -- 17 August 1964 ) was an Australian politician and a member of the New South Wales Legislative Assembly from 1939 until 1959 .
Ezra Danin ( 2 August 1903- 31 May 1984 ) was the head of the Arab section of the SHAI , the intelligence arm of the Haganah , Israeli politician and an orange grower .
George Riddoch ( 10 August 1842 -- 23 April 1919 ) was an Australian pastoralist and politician .
Sir Richard Grobham Howe , 3rd Baronet ( c.1651 - -1730 ) , of Little Compton , Withington and Chedworth , Gloucestershire , and Wishford , Wiltshire , was an English politician .
Arnstein Øverkil ( 29 March 1937 -- 27 February 2014 ) was a Norwegian police chief and civil servant .
Andrei Ivanovici Kliushnikov , real name Vasilii Surov ( commonly known as Nenin or Ninin ; 1892 - 1924 ) , was a Soviet communist who took a very important role in the Tatarbunary Uprising .
Al - Muqtafi ( 1096 -- 12 March 1160 ) ( Arabic : المقتفي لأمر الله‎ ) was the Abbasid Caliph in Baghdad from 1136 to 1160 .
Dorothy Way Eggan ( 1901 - -1965 ) was an American anthropologist noted for her research among the Hopi tribe .
Jesse Pickard Tripp ( 7 May 1883 -- 6 September 1971 ) was a Canadian politician serving in municipal , provincial and federal governments .
Robert Armin ( c. 1563 -- 1615 ) was an English actor , a member of the Lord Chamberlain 's Men .
Paolo Galletti ( 7 March 1937 -- 25 April 2015 ) was an Italian former swimmer .
Rear - Admiral Hans Voss ( 28 April 1894 - 29 May 1973 ) was a German naval officer .
Gebek Janku ibn Muhammad was the Khan ( Nutsal ) of Avaristan 1801 - -1802 .
Otto Wacker ( 1898 - -1970 ) was a German art dealer who became infamous for commissioning and selling forgeries of paintings by Vincent van Gogh .
Inge Steensland ( 26 November 1923 -- 18 September 2010 ) was a Norwegian resistance leader and shipping magnate .
Isaac J. Lansing ( 1846 - 1920 ) was president of Clark Atlanta University from 1874 to 1876 and pastor at Park Street Church in Boston , Massachusetts from 1893 to 1897 .
Joan Woodward ( September 27 , 1916 -- 1971 ) was a British professor in organization sociology
James , Azadanus and Abdicius ( died 380 ) are martyrs of the Christian Church .
John Ton ( born Jan Cornelis Ton ) ( 30 May 1826 , Akersloot , North Holland - 4 June 1896 , Chicago , Illinois ) was a Dutch - born American abolitionist active in the Underground Railroad in Illinois .
Syed Mainul Hossain ( 17 March , 1951 -- 10 November 2014 ) was a Bangladeshi structural engineer and architect .
Alexander Livingstone Bruce ( 24 October 1881 -- 12 February 1954 ) was a capitalist of Scottish origin , a director and major shareholder of A L Bruce Estates Ltd , one of the largest property owning companies in colonial Nyasaland .
Thomas Bardolf , 5th Baron Bardolf ( died 19 February 1408 ) was a baron in the Peerage of England , Lord of Wormegay , Norfolk , of Shelford and Stoke Bardolph in Nottinghamshire , Hallaton ( Hallughton ) , Leicestershire , and others , and was `` a person of especial eminence in his time '' .
Herbert James Draper ( November 1863 ( or 1864)-- 22 September 1920 ) was an English Classicist painter whose career began in the Victorian era and extended through the first two decades of the 20th century .
Robert Francis Walker ( 1789 - -1854 ) was an English cleric and author , known as a translator of works of German evangelical writers .
Richard Marquand ( 22 September 1937 -- 4 September 1987 ) was a Welsh film director , best known for directing Return of the Jedi .
Edward McNiven ( 21 June 1827 -- 4 January 1858 ) was an English lawyer and cricketer who played first - class cricket for Cambridge University , Surrey and various amateur sides between 1846 and 1851 .
Nicholas Boson ( 1624 - -1708 ) was a writer in , and preserver of , the Cornish language .
John Mason Peck ( 1789 - -1858 ) was an American Baptist missionary to the western frontier of the United States , especially in Missouri and Illinois .
Geoffrey de Clinton ( died c. 1134 ) was an Anglo - Norman noble , chamberlain and treasurer to King Henry I of England .
Sir Henry Francis Herbert Thompson , 2nd Baronet ( 2 April 1859 -- 26 May 1944 ) was a British Egyptologist .
Archie Grigg ( 15 February 1895 -- 15 October 1983 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John F. Hamilton ( 1893 - -1967 ) was an American - born film actor who worked for many years in Britain .
William Bulkeley Hughes ( 26 July 1797 -- 8 March 1882 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons as a Conservative from 1837 to 1859 , and as a Liberal from 1865 to 1882 .
Cosimo Lotti ( 1571 - -1643 ) was an Italian engineer , scenographer , and landscape designer .
Élisabeth Alexandrine de Bourbon ( Élisabeth Thérèse Alexandrine ; 5 September 1705 -- 15 April 1765 ) was a French princess of the blood and a daughter of Monsieur le Duc .
Norman Leslie Smith , also known by his pseudonym `` Wizard '' , ( 13 July 1890 -- 1 October 1958 ) was an Australian professional motor racing driver , known for his speed racing records .
Ivar Waller ( 11 June 1898 - 12 April 1991 ) was a Swedish professor of theoretical physics at Uppsala University .
Antoinette Feuerwerker ( 24 November 1912 -- 10 February 2003 ) was a French jurist and an active fighter in the French Resistance during the Second World War .
Dean Chapman ( 2 January 1931 -- 22 March 1965 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Joos de Beer ( died 1591 ) was an Early Netherlandish painter from Utrecht .
Jan Rajewski ( 1857 - -1906 ) was a Polish mathematician and prominent professor of the University of Lviv .
Juan Carlos Castillo ( 19 August 1964 -- 25 November 1993 ) was a Colombian racing cyclist .
George Engleheart ( 1750 - -1829 ) was one of the greatest English painters of portrait miniatures , and a contemporary of Richard Cosway , John Smart , William Wood , and Richard Crosse .
Guillaume - Jean - Noël de Lavillegris ( Saint - Malo , 20 July 1752 -- Paris , 21 January 1807 ) was a French Navy officer .
Dankwart Danckwerts ( 14 March 1933 ; Hamburg -- 11 May 2012 ; Hamburg ) was a German sociologist .
Joseph Franz , Prince of Dietrichstein ( 28 March 1798 -- 10 July 1858 ) , was a German prince member of the House of Dietrichstein , Major general , 9th Prince ( Fürst ) of Dietrichstein zu Nikolsburg , Count of Proskau - Leslie , Baron ( Freiherr ) of Hollenburg , Finkenstein and Thalberg .
George Brown Goode ( 13 February 1851 -- 6 September 1896 ) , was an ichthyologist , although most of his time was spent as a museum administrator and he was very interested in the history of science , especially the history of the development of science in America .
Sir Bysshe Shelley , 1st Baronet of Castle Goring ( 21 June 1731 -- 6 January 1815 ) was the grandfather of Romantic poet Percy Bysshe Shelley .
Kapitänleutnant Diether von Roeder ( died 10 July 1918 ) was a German naval officer killed during World War I. He was commander of the 13th Torpedo Boat Flotilla and died aboard Torpedo Boat S66 .
Paul J. Reinman , born Joseph Paul Reinmann , ( 2 September 1910 , Germany--27 September 1988 ) was an American comic book artist best known as one of Jack Kirby 's frequent inkers during the period comics fans and historians call the Silver Age of Comic Books .
Claus Fasting ( 29 October 1746 -- 25 December 1791 ) was a Norwegian playwright , literary critic , editor and civil servant .
Maurice Banide ( 20 May 1905 -- 20 May 1995 ) was a professional French football player and manager .
Mašo Vrbica ( 1833 in Vrba - 10 May 1898 in Banja Luka ) was a Montenegrin duke and military commander .
Bernard Ato V ( died 1163 ) was the Viscount of Nîmes of the Trencavel family from 1129 to his death .
Sir Thomas Neville or Nevill ( by 1484 -- 29 May 1542 ) was a younger son of George Neville , 4th Baron Bergavenny .
Noton Osborne ( 1844 -- 10 December 1878 ) was an Australian cricketer .
Herbert Claude Barnard ( 16 October 1890 -- 6 December 1957 ) was an Australian politician and government minister .
Giorgio Mangiamele ( 13 August 1926 -- 13 May 2001 ) was an Italian / Australian photographer and filmmaker who made a unique contribution to the production of Australian art cinema in the 1950s and 1960s .
Umberto Masetti ( 4 May 1926 - 28 May 2006 ) was an Italian two - time World Champion Grand Prix motorcycle road racer .
Thomas Evans ( Tomos Glyn Cothi ) ( 20 June 1764 -- 29 January 1833 ) , was a Welsh poet .
Wang Donglei ( Simplified Chinese : 王冬雷 ) ( 1 January 1985 -- 5 April 2008 ) was a Chinese footballer .
Stanisław Ignacy Witkiewicz ( Polish : ( staˈɲiswaf iɡˈnat͡sɨ vitˈkʲɛvit͡ʂ ) ; 24 February 1885 -- 18 September 1939 ) , commonly known as Witkacy , was a Polish writer , painter , philosopher , playwright , novelist , and photographer active in the interwar period .
Muhammad ibn Munkadir ( died 747 ) , also known as Ibn al - Munkadir or Muhammad al - Taymi , was a prominent tabi'i ( plural : taba'een ) and reciter of the Qur'an , who transmitted a number of hadith .
Henry II of Leez ( died 4 September 1164 ) was prince - bishop of Liège from 1145 until his death .
François Devouassoud ( September 1831 -- 1905 ) was a French mountain guide who made many first ascents in the Alps , notably as guide to Douglas William Freshfield , who claimed that Devouassoud `` was the first Alpine guide to carry his ice - axe to the snows of a distant range '' .
The Reverend George Andrew Jacob DD ( 16 December 1807 -- 7 May 1896 ) was an English clergyman and schoolmaster and author of many books about education and Christianity .
Danny McAllister ( 1919 - -2008 ) was a famous Irish sportsperson .
Sir Pryce Pryce - Jones ( 16 October 1834 -- 11 January 1920 ) was a Welsh entrepreneur who was one of the first to succeed in the mail order business .
John Cabess ( also written as John Kabes or John Cabes ) ( c. 1640s-1722 ) was a prominent African trader in the port city of Komenda , part of the Eguafo Kingdom , in modern - day Ghana .
Hans Ritter von Hemmer , ( 26 June 1869 -- 15 December 1931 ) , son of Colonel Anthony Hemmer , was an officer in the Royal Bavarian Army and Knight Commander of the Military Order of Max Joseph .
Zorawar Singh Kahluria ( 1786 - 1841 ) was born in Kahlur State in Bilaspur , Kahlur , Sikh Misl .
Josef Labor ( 29 June 1842 -- 26 April 1924 ) was an Austrian pianist , organist , and composer of the late Romantic era .
Johann Christian Köpping ( 1704 -- 1772 ) was a German curator , best known as an assistant of J. S. Bach .
Dirk van Bleiswijk , or Dirck van Bleyswijck ( 28 December 1639 in Delft -- 11 September 1681 in Middelburg ) , was a Delft politician and writer .
Robert Orr , Jr. ( 5 March 1786 at Hannastown , Westmoreland County , Pennsylvania -- 22 May 1876 at Kittanning , Pennsylvania ) was a Pennsylvania political figure .
Johann Theodor de Bry ( 1561 -- 31 January 1623 ) was an engraver and publisher .
David Neil MacKenzie FBA ( 8 April 1926 -- 13 October 2001 ) was a scholar of Iranian languages .
Gerald FitzGerald , 11th Earl of Kildare ( 1525 - -1585 ) , also known as the `` Wizard Earl '' ( a sobriquet also given to Henry Percy , 9th Earl of Northumberland ) , was an Irish peer .
Alice Grant Rosman ( 18 July 1882 -- 20 August 1961 ) - also known as Alice Trevenen Rosman - was an Australian novelist .
Jeremiah N. Reynolds ( 1799 - -1858 ) , also known as J.N. Reynolds , was an American newspaper editor , lecturer , explorer and author who became an influential advocate for scientific expeditions .
Ines Fančović ( née Nikolić ; 5 October 1925 -- 21 August 2011 ) was a Bosnian actress of film , television and theater .
John Leo Travers ( 20 October 1899 -- 23 February 1979 ) was an Australian politician who represented the South Australian House of Assembly seat of Torrens from 1953 to 1956 for the Liberal and Country League .
Bernice Tannenbaum ( 6 November 1913 -- 6 April 2015 ) was an activist with Hadassah .
Akha Bhagat ( or commonly known as Akho ) ( Gujarati : અખા ભગત , અખો ) ( 1591 - -1656 ) was a medieval Gujarati poet who wrote in the tradition of the Bhakti movement .
John Alexander Gunn ( 1896 - -1975 ) was an author of philosophy books who earned his Ph.D. from the University of Liverpool and worked there as a fellow .
Hans Monderman ( 19 November 1945 -- 7 January 2008 ) was a Dutch road traffic engineer and innovator .
Rochus Misch ( 29 July 1917 -- 5 September 2013 ) was a German Oberscharführer ( sergeant ) in the 1st SS Panzer Division Leibstandarte SS Adolf Hitler ( LSSAH ) .
David Jenks SSM ( 1866 - -1935 ) was a priest of the Church of England and member of the Society of the Sacred Mission ( SSM ) .
Arthur Rosebery ( 1904 - 1986 ) was an English pianist and singer .
Harold Clarke Goddard ( 1878 - 1950 ) was a professor in the English Department of Swarthmore College .
Roop Singh Bais ( 8 September 1908 -- 16 December 1977 ) was a legendary Indian hockey player .
Miltiadis Goulimis ( Greek : Μιλτιάδης Γουλιμής ) ( 1844 - -1896 ) was a Greek politician from Missolonghi .
George Teasdale ( 8 December 1831 -- 9 June 1907 ) was a Mormon missionary and a member of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter - day Saints ( LDS Church ) .
Don McKillop ( 14 November 1929 -- 19 December 2005 ) was an English actor born in Carlisle , Cumberland .
Marc Krasner ( 1912 -- 13 May 1985 , Paris ) was a Russian - born French mathematician , who worked on algebraic number theory .
Admiral Sir Colin Richard Keppel GCVO KCIE CB DSO ( 3 December 1862 -- 6 July 1947 ) was a British sailor and Extra Equerry to four kings .
Gregorius Sickinger ( 1558 - -1631 ) was a Swiss painter , draughtsman , and engraver .
Stephen Poyntz Denning ( 1795 -- 8 June 1864 ) was an English portrait painter and gallery curator .
Johann Nepomuk Sepp ( 7 August 1816 -- 5 June 1909 ) was a German historian and politician , and a native of Bavaria .
Ashot the Swift ( died in 939 ) ( Georgian : აშოტ კისკასი ) was a Georgian prince of the Bagrationi dynasty from Tao - Klarjeti .
John Horvat ( Croatian : Ivan Horvat ; Hungarian : János Horváti ; died on 15 August 1394 ) was a Croatian nobleman in the Kingdom of Hungary - Croatia who served as Ban of Macsó from 1376 to 1381 , and again between 1385 and 1386 .
Wilbur Kitchener Jordan ( also known as W. K. Jordan ) , ( 1902 - 1980 ) was an American historian , specializing in sixteenth and seventeenth century Britain .
Leopold Endel - Ragis ( 1894 - -1943 ) was soldier of the Polish Legions in World War I and the Austro - Hungarian Army , and colonel of infantry of the Polish Army in the Second Polish Republic ( 1918 - 1939 ) .
Thomas de Ringstead ( died 1366 ) was an English Dominican who became Bishop of Bangor .
Ernie Sellars ( 20 June 1890 -- 8 November 1955 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Henry Sloughter ( died 1691 ) was briefly colonial governor of New York and Massachusetts in 1691 .
Eddie Bevan ( c. 1925 - -1988 ) was a Canadian football player who played for the Hamilton Tiger - Cats .
Ravi Shankar Vyas ( 1884 - -1984 ) was an Indian freedom fighter born at Radhu ( Kheda district , Gujarat , India ) and social reformer , hailing from and working in the state of Gujarat .
William de Spynie ( died 1406 ) was a Scottish prelate .
Satyananda Stokes ( 16 August 1882 - 14 May 1946 ) was an American who settled in India and participated in the Indian Independence Movement .
Jacopo Colonna ( died 1540 ) was an Italian sculptor active in the Renaissance .
Jack Carmody ( 7 June 1911 -- 28 March 1982 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Hosack ( baptised 1813 -- 1887 ) was a Scottish lawyer and historical writer .
Fridugisus , also known as Fredegisus or Fredegis of Tours ( born in England towards the end of the eighth century ; died in Tours around 834 ) , was a monk , teacher , and writer .
Nelson Boyd ( February 6 , 1928 , Camden , New Jersey -- October 1985 ) was an American bebop jazz bassist .
Mary Ellaline Terriss , Lady Hicks ( 13 April 1871 -- 16 June 1971 ) , known professionally as Ellaline Terriss , was a popular English actress and singer , best known for her performances in Edwardian musical comedies .
Jakob van Domselaer ( 15 April 1890 in Nijkerk , Gelderland -- 5 January 1960 ) was a Dutch composer .
Baldwin de Redvers , 7th Earl of Devon ( 1 January 1236 -- 1262 ) , feudal baron of Plympton in Devon and Lord of the Isle of Wight , was the son of Baldwin de Redvers , 6th Earl of Devon and Amice de Clare , daughter of Gilbert de Clare , 5th Earl of Hertford .
Ayyub Musallam Ya'qub Musallam ( 1905 - -2001 ) was a public speaker , author and politician .
Costanza d'Avalos Piccolomini ( died 1560 ) was a duchess of Amalfi .
Sir John Henry Birchenough , 1st Baronet , GCMG ( 7 March 1853 -- 12 May 1937 ) was an English businessman and public servant .
Joseph Wattmann von Maëlcamp - Beaulieu ( 6 March 1789 , Oberlangbath -- 14 September 1866 ) was an Austrian surgeon .
Jack O'Newbury ( 1489 - 1557 ) was the much - used nickname of John Winchcombe II . Jack was one of the richest and most influential English cloth merchants of the early 16th century .
Lucien Massart ( 1908 -- 1988 ) was a specialist in the animal and plant enzymology .
Kurt Oscar Weber ( 26 July 1938 -- 29 October 2011 ) was a Swiss - American fine artist , primarily working in sculpture and painting .
Stanisław Gabriel Worcell ( 26 March 1799 in Stepań / Volhynia -- 3 February 1857 in London ) was a socialist Polish revolutionary .
Marianne Breslauer ( married surname Feilchenfeldt , 20 November 1909 -- 7 February 2001 ) was a German photographer during the Weimar Republic .
Ross Graves ( August 27 , 1874 in Albany , New York -- 1940 ) was an American businessman and politician from New York .
John Griswold White ( 10 Aug 1845 - - 26 Aug 1928 ) was a prominent Cleveland attorney , a chess connoisseur , and a bibliophile .
Brigadier Cecil Arthur Harrop Chadwick CBE ( 13 August 1901 - -3 September 1970 ) , was a British soldier and briefly a Liberal Party politician .
Mastan Haider Mirza , popularly known as Haji Mastan , Bawa /Sultan Mirza ( 1 March 1926 - 9 May 1994 ) was an Indian mobster and filmmaker .
Gilbert Horal or Erail ( died December 1200 ) was the 12th Grand Master of the Knights Templar from 1193 to 1200 .
Bronwen Wallace ( 26 May 1945 -- 25 August 1989 ) was a Canadian poet and short story writer .
Bruno Radicioni ( 10 December 1933 -- 17 April 1997 ) was an Italian painter , sculptor and ceramist , lived for a decade in Canada .
May Wright Sewall ( May 27 , 1844 -- July 22 , 1920 ) was an American reformer , who was known for her service to the causes of education , women 's rights , and world peace .
Sir Francis Philip Cunliffe - Owen KCB KCMG CIE FRSA ( 8 June 1828 -- 23 March 1894 ) was an exhibition organizer and the Director of the South Kensington Museum in London .
Ulrich Ensingen ( or Ensinger ) ( 1350/60 -- February 10 , 1419 ) was a medieval German architect .
Margaret Nowell Graham ( 1867 - 1942 ) was an American artist who painted watercolors of flowers and landscapes .
William Cheselden ( /ˈtʃɛsəldən/ ; 19 October 1688 -- 10 April 1752 ) was an English surgeon and teacher of anatomy and surgery , who was influential in establishing surgery as a scientific medical profession .
Arthur Chesters ( 14 February 1910 -- 23 March 1963 ) was an English footballer .
Prof Sir Bernard Crossland CBE , FRS ( 20 October 1923 -- 17 January 2011 ) was a professor of engineering with a career spanning some seven decades .
Bernat Calbó ( or Calvó ) ( c. 1180 -- 26 October 1243 ) , sometimes called Bernard of Calvo , was a Catalan jurist , bureaucrat , monk , bishop , and soldier .
Henry Savage ( 1604?--1672 ) was an English clergyman , academic and controversialist , Master of Balliol College , Oxford from 1651 .
Karl von Luxburg ( 10 May 1872 in Würzburg -- 2 April 1956 in Ramos Mejía , Argentina ) was German chargé d'affaires at Buenos Aires , Argentina , in 1917 , during World War I.
Elizabeth Bradford Holbrook , CM , O.Ont ( 7 November 1913 -- 23 February 2009 ) was a Canadian portrait sculptor , medal designer and liturgical artist .
Jianzhi Sengcan ( Chinese : 鑑智僧璨 ; Hànyǔ Pīnyīn : Jiànzhì Sēngcàn ; Wade -- Giles : Chien - chih Seng - ts'an ; Japanese : Kanchi Sōsan , died 606 ) is known as the Third Chinese Patriarch of Chán after Bodhidharma and thirtieth Patriarch after Siddhārtha Gautama Buddha .
Ganesh Ghosh ( Bengali : গণেশ ঘোষ ) ( 22 June 1900 -- 16 October 1994 ) was a Bengali Indian independence activist , revolutionary and politician .
Princess Augusta of Saxe - Weimar - Eisenach ( Augusta Marie Luise Katharina ; 30 September 1811 -- 7 January 1890 ) was the Queen of Prussia and the first German Empress as the consort of William I , German Emperor .
James Milo Griffith ( 11 June 1843 -- 8 September 1897 ) was a Welsh sculptor , who after originally training as an artisan mason , became notable for his memorial statues .
Archibald McDowall ( 2 December 1841 -- 13 May 1918 ) was a Surveyor General of Queensland , ( then a colony , now a state of Australia ) .
George Shepheard ( 26 January 1770 -- 7 September 1842 ) was an English professional cricketer who made 10 known appearances in major cricket matches from 1794 to 1799 .
Madge Ryan ( 8 January 1919 -- 9 January 1994 ) was an Australian - born film , theatre and television actress , best known for her stage roles in the United Kingdom
Dr Conn McCluskey ( 1914 - 16 December 2013 ) was an Irish civil rights activist in the 1960s , and a medical doctor .
Henry Moxley ( 1809 - 1878 ) was an African - American businessman , religious leader and activist in Buffalo , New York .
Richard A. Compton ( July 9 , 1926 -- 1993 ) of Ithaca , New York was an American educator , hotelman and expert in the facilities management within resort and entertainment industry .
George Way Harley ( 8 August 1894 -- 7 November 1966 ) was an American Methodist medical missionary .
John Bois ( sometimes spelled Boys or `` Boyse '' ) ( 3 January 1560 -- 14 January 1643 ) was an English scholar , remembered mainly as one of the members of the translating committee for the Authorized Version of the Bible .
Thomas Newcomen Archibald Grove ( 1855 -- 4 June 1920 ) , commonly known as Archibald Grove , was a British magazine editor and Liberal Party politician .
Ferdinand Praeger ( 22 January 1815 -- 2 September 1891 ) ( aka Ferdinand Christian Wilhelm Praeger ) was a composer , music teacher , pianist and writer .
Arne Skaug ( 6 November 1906 -- 4 March 1974 ) was a Norwegian economist , civil servant , diplomat and politician for the Labour Party .
Pietro Gualdi aka Pedro Gualdi ( 22 July 1808 Carpi , Emilia - Romagna - 4 January 1857 New Orleans ) , was an Italian - born artist , panorama painter , architect and lithographer who was active in Mexico City from 1838 to about 1851 , and in New Orleans from about 1851 to 1857 .
Louis - Henri de Baugy , Chevalier de Baugy ( died 1720 ) was from a noble family of France and came to New France as a member of the party of Joseph - Antoine de La Barre , who was replacing Buade de Frontenac as Governor General .
József Haubrich ( 9 November 1883 , Deta -- 1939 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Defence twice in 1919 .
Robert Reasoner Nevin ( 2 August 1875 , in Dayton , Ohio -- 31 December 1952 ) was a United States federal judge .
Edward Arthur Wilson , better known as Brother XII , ( July 25 , 1878 - -November 7 , 1934 ? ) was an English mystic who , in the late 1920s , founded a spiritual community located just south of the city of Nanaimo on Vancouver Island , off the west coast of British Columbia , Canada .
Alan of Beccles ( ca . 1195 -- 1240 ) was official secretary to Bishops Pandulf and Thomas de Blundeville of Norwich between the years 1217 and 1236 .
John Urpeth Rastrick ( 26 January 1780 -- 1 November 1856 ) was one of the first English steam locomotive builders .
Ibnu Parna ( died 1965 ) was an Indonesian communist politician and leader of the Acoma Party ( Partai Acoma ) , and trade unionist .
Yuchi Jiong ( 尉遲迥 ) ( died 580 ) , courtesy name Bojuluo ( 薄居羅 ) , was a general of the Chinese / Xianbei states Western Wei and Northern Zhou .
Georgette de Montenay ( 1540 - -1581 ) was the French author of Emblemes ou devises chrestiennes , published in Lyon between 1567 and 1571 .
Lady Ida Beasley Elliott ( December 25 , 1864 - -1948 ) was a missionary to Burma and one of the first women to own a business in Winchester , Tennessee .
Heinrich Christian Macklot ( 20 October 1799 , Frankfurt am Main -- 12 May 1832 ) was a German naturalist .
Jean - Antoine Auguste Metz ( 8 August 1812 -- 22 June 1854 ) was a Luxembourgian entrepreneur , politician , and lawyer .
Henry Warwick Braithwaite ( 9 January 1896 -- 19 January 1971 ) was a New Zealand - born orchestral conductor .
Ken Herbert ( 27 December 1924 -- 3 March 2011 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Roderigo Lopez ( also called Ruy Lopes or Roger Lopez ; c. 1517 -- 7 June 1594 ) served as physician - in - chief to Queen Elizabeth I of England from 1581 until his death by execution , having been found guilty of plotting to poison the Queen .
Agilbert died at some time after 10 March 673 , on which date he witnessed Clotilde 's foundation charter for the Abbey of Bruyères - le - Châtel , and probably between 679 and 690 .
Thomas Bewes Strangways ( 23 July 1809 -- 23 February 1859 ) , generally called `` Bewes Strangways '' or `` T. Bewes Strangways '' , was an explorer , early settler and Colonial Secretary of South Australia .
Pan Tianshou ( Chinese : 潘天寿 ; pinyin : Pān Tiānshòu ; 1897 - -1971 ) was a Chinese painter and art educator .
Jorge Pires Ferreira ( 12 December 1920 -- 6 November 2013 ) , known professionally as Jorge Dória , was a Brazilian actor and humorist .
Allan Mullen , M.D. ( also Mullin , Molines ) ( died 1690 ) was an eminent Irish anatomist .
Basil LeFlore ( born near Carrollton , Mississippi , in 1811 ; died in Goodland , Indian Territory , 15 October 1886 ) was governor of the Choctaw nation from 1860 to 1875 , and later was auditor until his death .
Martha Walker Freer ( 1822 -- 1888 ) was an English writer on French history .
Jacques Brunel ( Brumel , Brumello , Brunello , Giaches Brumel , etc . ) ( died 1564 ) was a French organist and composer , active mostly in Italy .
Leo Steiner ( c. 1939 -- December 31 , 1987 ) was a Jewish American restaurateur who was co - owner of the Carnegie Deli , located next to Carnegie Hall at 55th Street and Seventh Avenue in the New York City borough of Manhattan .
Kariel Gardosh ( 15 April 1921 -- 28 February 2000 ) was an Israeli cartoonist and illustrator known by his nickname Dosh .
Andrew Broughton ( 1602/3 - -1687 ) was Clerk of the Court at the High Court of Justice for the trial King Charles I of England .
Blasco de Grañén ( ca . 1400 , Zaragoza , Spain - October 1459 , Zaragoza ) ( known as : `` Master of Lanaja '' ) was a Gothic painter active in Aragon from 1422 .
Sir Robert Rawlinson KCB ( 28 February 1810 -- 31 May 1898 ) was an English engineer and sanitarian .
Sergei Mikhailovich Golitsyn ( Russian : Серге́й Михайлович Голицын ; 14 March ( O.S. 1 March ) 1909 -- 7 November 1989 ) was a Russian writer .
Karl von Mansfeld ( 1543 -- 24 August 1595 ) was a German general during the Cologne War and the Ottoman - Habsburg wars .
Xavier Zequeira ( 2 May 1907 -- September 1976 ) was a Puerto Rican sports shooter .
Jeremiah Garnett ( 1793 - -1870 ) was an English journalist , active in the politics of Lancashire and the founding of The Guardian .
Lala Ram Ken ( Hindi : लाला राम केन ; 24 November 1931 − 5 October 2007 ) was a political leader who was elected Member of Parliament twice from Bayana Constituency for 7th and 8th Lok Sabha(Parliament ) .
Jenny Gilbertson ( born Jenny Brown ; October 28 , 1902 - January 8 1990 ) was a Scottish documentary and educational filmmaker .
Nalini Prava Deka ( 11 March 1944 -- 15 June 2014 ) was a prominent Assamese lady author , poet , storyteller , essayist , actress and radio playwright from Assam , a state encompassing the Brahmaputra valley in India .
Wong Ho Leng ( simplified Chinese : 黄和联 ; traditional Chinese : 黃和聯 ; pinyin : Huáng Hé Lián ; 21 December 1959 -- 21 June 2014 ) was a Malaysian politician .
Henry English ( died 1393 ) , of Wood Ditton , Cambridgeshire , was an English politician .
Menachem Yedid ( Hebrew : מנחם ידיד‎ ; 15 January 1918 -- 5 May 2013 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Gahal and Likud between 1965 and 1977 .
William Dollard ( baptized 29 November 1789 -- 29 August 1851 ) was an Irish born Canadian Roman Catholic priest and Bishop of Saint John in America , New Brunswick from 1842 to 1851 .
Henry Simms ( c. 1717 -- 17 June 1747 ) , known as Young Gentlemen Harry , was a thief and highwayman in 18th - century England who was transported to Maryland for theft , but escaped and returned to England , where he was eventually executed for highway robbery .
Barral of Baux ( died 1268 ) was Viscount of Marseilles and Lord of Baux .
Harriet Duncan Hobart ( 1825 - -1898 ) was an American schoolteacher and women 's rights advocate .
Robert Monteith ( 1812 -- 31 March 1884 ) , DL , JP , was a Scottish politician and philanthropist , Deputy Lieutenant for the County of Lanark .
Joshua Harold Burn FRS ( 6 March 1892 -- 13 July 1981 ) was an English pharmacologist and Emeritus Professor of Pharmacology at Oxford University .
K. R. Ramsingh ( c. 1915 - d. 18 October 1985 ) was a Tamil theatre artist , film actor and voice actor .
Joseph Bryant Rotherham ( 1828 - -1910 ) was a British biblical scholar and minister of the Churches of Christ .
Robert Plumptre ( 1723 - -1788 ) was an English churchman and academic , President of Queens ' College , Cambridge from 1760 .
Otto III , Duke of Pomerania ( 29 May 1444 -- 7 September 1464 ) was a member of the House of Griffins and a Duke of Pomerania - Stettin .
Zoltán Baló ( 23 January 1883 -- 10 December 1966 ) was a Hungarian military officer and a Colonel of the Royal Hungarian Home Defence Force and its successor , the Royal Hungarian Home Defence Force .
Sébastien René Lenormand ( 2 April 1796 in Condé - sur - Noireau -- 10 December 1871 ) was a French lawyer and botanist who specialized in the field of phycology .
Fredrik Møller ( 21 March 1906 -- 11 March 1971 ) was a Norwegian engineer , research administrator , entrepreneur and industrialist .
Rochunga Pudaite ( 4 December 1927 -- 10 October 2015 ) was an Indian minister of Hmar descent who translated the Bible into the Hmar language and founded Bibles for the World .
Ephraim Deinard ( 1846 - -1930 ) was one of the greatest Hebrew `` bookmen '' of all time .
João de Sá , knight ( fl . 1497 -- 1514 ) was a Portuguese explorer , who accompanied Vasco da Gama on the voyage that of the first ships to sail directly from Europe to India .
Eadwig , also spelled Edwy ( died 1 October 959 ) , usually called the All - Fair , was King of England from 955 until his premature death in 959 .
John Hodges Benwell ( 1764 - -1785 ) was an English genre painter , some of whose works became well - known through engravings .
Nathaniel Emmons ( April 20 , 1745 -- 1840 ) was a noted New England divine .
Robert Preston , 1st Baron Gormanston ( died 1396 ) was an Anglo - Irish nobleman , statesman and judge .
Myra Kinch ( 1904-November 20 , 1981 ) was a choreographer and dancer who appeared in several Hollywood motion pictures .
Stefano Madia ( 31 December 1954 -- 16 December 2004 ) was an Italian film actor .
Byrd Lockhart ( 1782 - -1839 ) , was a 19th - century Texas surveyor , Alamo defender , courier , and Texian officer during the Texas Revolution .
Ida de Tosny , Countess of Norfolk was very likely a daughter of Ralph V de Tosny ( died 1162 ) and his wife Margaret ( born circa 1125 and living in 1185 ) , a daughter of Robert de Beaumont , 2nd Earl of Leicester .
Abbas - Ali Amid Zanjani ( 30 March 1937 -- 30 October 2011 ) was an Iranian politician and cleric .
