George Richard Marek ( 13 July 1902 -- 7 January 1987 ) was an American music executive and author of biographies of classical composers .
Susanna Montgomery , Countess of Eglinton ( 1690 -- 18 March 1780 ) was the third wife of Alexander Montgomerie , 9th Earl of Eglinton .
Margaret Fiennes , 11th Baroness Dacre ( 1541 -- 16 March 1612 ) was a suo jure peeress having been created Baroness Dacre by King James I of England in 1604 .
Ramón Allende Padín ( 19 March 1845 -- 14 October 1884 ) , nicknamed El Rojo ( `` The Red '' ) , was a Chilean physician and political figure .
Pino Massara ( 24 April 1931 - 23 July 2013 ) was an Italian musician , composer , record producer and conductor .
Mgr Anselm Bourke , born Nicholas Bourke , ( Dublin , 10 September 1835 -- West Perth , 2 June 1924 ) was a Roman Catholic priest of Irish origins .
Sidney Maiden ( 1923 -- 1970 ) was an American country blues musician .
Luz Jiménez or Luciana ( born Julia Jiménez González ; 1897 - -1965 ) was an indigenous Mexican model and Nahuatl - language storyteller and linguistic informant from Milpa Alta , D.F. As a young woman she witnessed the Mexican Revolution , and was present when Emiliano Zapata and his revolutionary army entered Milpa Alta in 1911 .
Nic Potter ( 18 October 1951 -- 16 January 2013 ) was a British bassist , composer and painter , best known for his work with the group Van der Graaf Generator in the 1970s .
Archibald Edward Glover ( 1859 - 1954 ) was a British Protestant Christian missionary in China .
Christian Gottlob Hubert ( 1714 - -1793 ) was a famous builder of keyboard instruments .
Nino Aleksi - Meskhishvili ( 1896 , Tbilisi -- 16 May 1956 , Moscow ) was a Georgian stage actor .
Edwin Eugene Bagley ( May 29 , 1857 -- January 29 , 1922 ) was an American composer , most famous for composing the march National Emblem .
Bert Boromeo ( 10 May 1892 -- 19 April 1971 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Richmond in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Karol Józef Krótki , FRSC ( 15 May 1922 -- 6 July 2007 ) was a renowned Polish Canadian demographer who , at various times , lived and worked in Poland , the United Kingdom , Sudan , Pakistan , Morocco and Canada .
Francisco Viana ( 1895 -- 1945 in Lisbon ) was a Portuguese guitarist and composer of fados .
George I Šubić of Bribir ( Croatian : Juraj I Šubić Bribirski ) ( c. 1277 -- 1302 ) was the Count of Trogir , and a member of the Croatian Šubić noble family .
Francis Hamilton Stuart ( 20 July 1912 -- 1 February 2007 ) is a former Australian public servant and diplomat .
Kazimierz Laskowski ( 7 November 1899 -- 20 October 1961 ) was a Polish fencer and military officer .
Noah Young Jr. ( 2 February 1887 - 18 April 1958 ) was a former champion weightlifter and actor .
Maximilian Elisäus Alexander von Hanstein , Count of Pölzig and Beiersdorf ( 9 June 1804 , Burghaig , Kulmbach -- 18 April 1884 , Schmölln ) was a Thuringian count .
Baltasar Barreira ( Balthasar ) ( 1531 - -1612 ) , born at Lisbon , was a Portuguese Jesuit missionary to Africa .
Ivan Prasko ( 1 May 1914 -- 28 January 2001 ) was the eparch of Australia , New Zealand and Oceania for the Ukrainian Catholic Church .
In Luo Guanzhong 's historical novel Romance of the Three Kingdoms , Cao Xing played a greater role in the events preceding the Battle of Xiapi in 198 .
Julius Klein ( 1901 - -1984 ) was an American , journalist , spy , business executive and United States Army general .
Eric Enstrom ( 1875 , in Mora parrish , Sweden -- 1968 , in Coleraine , Minnesota , USA ) was famous for his 1918 photograph of Charles Wilden in Bovey , Minnesota .
Gangadhar Appa Burande ( Marathi : गंगाधर अप्पा बुरांडे , 29 December 1919 in Moha -- 1 October 2008 ) was an Indian politician .
Johan Gadolin ( 5 June 1760 -- 15 August 1852 ) was a Finnish chemist , physicist and mineralogist .
Revd Dr Frederick Charles Plumptre ( 1796 - -1870 ) was a Victorian academic and administrator .
J. Fred Helf ( 1870 ? -- 1915 ? ) was an American composer and sheet music publisher during the early 20th century .
Owain ap Cadwgan ( died 1116 ) was a prince of Powys in eastern Wales .
Robert fitz Martin ( c. 10 ? ? -- c. 1159 ) was a Norman knight from the west of England who supported Henry I in his campaigns in Wales .
Syed Ijlal Haider Zaidi died on the morning of 23 March 2013 in Lahore after a 2 year battle with cancer .
John Corrin ( 10 September 1934 -- 30 November 2005 ) was a former Minister in the Isle of Man Government and Member of the House of Keys .
Sir Richard Elyot , SL ( died 1522 ) was an English landowner and judge .
Anton Karas ( 7 July 1906 -- 10 January 1985 ) was a Viennese zither player and composer , best known for his internationally famous 1948 soundtrack to Carol Reed 's The Third Man , which came about as a result of a chance meeting .
John Murray Bliss ( 22 February 1771 -- 22 August 1834 ) was a Canadian jurist , politician and administrator .
Erling Persson ( 21 January 1917 -- 28 October 2002 ) was the founder of H&M ( Hennes&Mauritz ) .
Patrick Denis O'Donnell ( 9 January 1922 -- 1 January 2005 ) was an Irish military historian , writer , former UN peace - keeper , and Commandant of the Irish Defence Forces .
Heinrich Ritter von Wittek ( 29 January 1844 -- 9 April 1930 ) was an Austrian politician and statesman .
Cees Heerschop ( 14 February 1935 -- 24 July 2014 ) was a Dutch professional footballer who played for PSV as a right back , making 191 appearances for the club in all competitions , between 1956 and 1964 .
Eleanor Mayo ( 1920 - -1981 ) was an American novelist of the mid twentieth century .
Alicia Adélaide Needham ( 31 October 1863 -- 24 December 1945 ) was an Irish composer of songs and ballads .
Bill Tarmey ( born William Piddington ; 4 April 1941 -- 9 November 2012 ) was an English actor , singer and author , best known for playing Jack Duckworth in the soap opera Coronation Street .
John Reily ( 1763 - 1850 ) was a soldier in the American Revolution who later held a number of civic positions including helping draft the Ohio State Constitution .
Alexander Selkirk ( 1676 -- 13 December 1721 ) , also known as Alexander Selcraig , was a Scottish sailor who spent more than four years as a castaway after being marooned on an uninhabited island in the South Pacific Ocean , also known as the South Sea .
Eberhard Fraas ( 26 June 1862 -- 6 March 1915 ) was a German scientist , geologist and paleontologist .
Sámuel Literáti Nemes ( 1796 - -1842 ) , Transylvanian - Hungarian antiquarian , co - founder of the National Széchényi Library in Budapest , infamous for many forgeries which even deceived some of the most renowned Hungarian scholars of the time .
Professor John Selwyn Bromley died in Southampton on 17 April 1985 , aged 71 .
Gustaf Arokallio ( 10 June 1854 , Sotkamo - 11 December 1939 : surname until 1906 Petterson ) was a Finnish Lutheran clergyman and politician .
William Augustine O'Carroll ( 1831 - -1885 ) was an Irish nationalist , radical liberal , journalist and Queensland newspaper editor .
Harold Arthur Prichard ( 1871 - -1947 ) , usually cited as H. A. Pritchard , was an English philosopher .
Nicholas If - Jesus - Christ - Had - Not - Died - For - Thee - Thou - Hadst - Been - Damned Barebone who traded as Nicholas Barbon ( c. 1640 -- c. 1698 ) was an English economist , physician , and financial speculator .
Joe Elvin ( real name Joseph Peter Keegan ) ( 29 November 1862 -- 3 March 1935 ) was a Cockney comedian and music hall entertainer and a Founder of the Grand Order of Water Rats , a show business charity .
Niccolò Granello , also Nicholas Granello and Granelo Nicolao ( 1553 - 30 November 1593 ) , was an Italian painter established in Spain , specialized in frescos decorative painting grotesques .
Alexander Kardin , ( 1917 - -1994 ) born Alexander Maria Indrak , was a German painter and film artist known for his landscapes .
Darsie Japp ( 17 February 1883 - -1973 ) was an English painter and soldier .
Carl Kaufmann ( 25 March 1936 -- 1 September 2008 ) was a West German sprint runner .
Joe Talirunili ( ca . 1893 - -1976 ) was an Inuit printmaker and sculptor , who would sometimes draw .
Henry Ommaney ( April 1805 -- 21 May 1829 ) was an English cricketer who played for Kent .
Theodore Lidz ( 1 April 1910 -- 16 February 2001 ) was an American psychiatrist best known for his articles and books on the causes of schizophrenia and on psychotherapy with schizophrenic patients .
Terence Lucy Greenidge ( 14 January 1902 -- 18 December 1970 ) was an English author and actor .
James Stuart McKnight ( November 15 , 1884 -- December 25 , 1950 ) was a National Guard officer who served in World War I , an attorney and a member of the City Council in Los Angeles , California , in 1931 and 1932 .
Felipe Songsong ( 1611 - -1685 ) was a Philippine Jesuit .
Marcelle de Lacour ( 6 November 1896 -- 24 March 1997 ) was a French harpsichordist and teacher .
Arthur Kreindler ( 15 May 1900 -- 28 May 1988 ) was a Romanian neurologist of Jewish origin , academic , professor of neurology at the Institute of Medicine and Pharmacy in Bucharest and director of the Institute of Neurology Research of the Romanian Academy .
Hamar Alfred Bass ( 30 July 1842 -- 8 April 1898 ) was a British brewer , race horse breeder and a Liberal Party politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1878 to 1898 .
Arthur W. V. Reeve MBE ( Born 1913-date of death unknown - approx . 1994 ) , was an author and scout from New Zealand .
John Murray Easton ( 30 January 1889 - 19 August 1975 ) was a Scottish architect and the winner of the Royal Gold Medal for architecture awarded by the Royal Institute of British Architects .
Aziz Dowlatabadi ( 1922 , Tabriz - 30 April 2009 , Tabriz ) also known by the pen name Darvish was Iranian poet .
Donald MacCrimmon MacKay ( 9 August 1922 - 6 February 1987 ) was a British physicist , and Professor at the Department of Communication and Neuroscience at the Keele University in Staffordshire , England , known for his contributions to information theory and the theory of brain organisation .
Sinéad de Valera , also known as Sinéad Ní Fhlannagáin and Sinéad Bean de Valera ( Irish pronunciation : ( ɕɪnʲeːdʲ bʲeːn̪ˠ dʲɛ vʲalʲɛrˠa ) ; 3 June 1878 -- 7 January 1975 ) , was an author and the wife of the Irish republican leader and third President of Ireland , Éamon de Valera .
Evelyn Tooley Hunt ( 1904 - -1997 ) , also known as Tao - Li , was a poet who was famous for writing the poem `` Taught Me Purple '' which inspired the novel The Color Purple by Alice Walker .
Maria van Lommen ( 1688 - -1742 ) , was a Dutch gold- and silversmith and guildmember .
Arthur Ernest Bishop AM ( 1917 -- 2006 ) was a noted Australian engineer and inventor .
Jacobus Pamelius ( Jacob van Pamele ) ( 13 May 1536 -- 19 September 1587 ) was a Flemish theologian .
Christian Ulrik Hansen ( 26 May 1921 -- 23 June 1944 ) was a student of theology and member of the Danish resistance executed by the German occupying power .
Leo Holub ( 25 November 1916 -- 27 April 2010 ) was an American photographer famous for his landscapes and architectural images of San Francisco , and photographs of Yosemite .
Guy David ( 25 July 1947 -- 30 August 2008 ) was a French footballer and coach .
Phyllis Matthewman ( 1896 - -1979 ) , British writer of children 's books , mostly boarding school stories .
Carl Frederik Tietgen ( 19 March 1829 -- 19 October 1901 ) was a Danish financier and industrialist .
Aquino de Bragança died on 19 October 1986 in a much - publicized plane crash in the Lebombo Mountains , near the border between Mozambique and South Africa .
Sir Richard Arches ( died 1417 ) , of Eythrope , in the parish of Waddesdon , Buckinghamshire , was MP for Buckinghamshire in 1402 .
Lieutenant - Colonel George Rodney , 2nd Baron Rodney ( 25 December 1753 -- 2 January 1802 ) , was a British soldier and politician .
Chen Wen - chen ( Chinese : 陳文成 ; pinyin : Chén Wénchéng , sometimes romanized as Chen Wen - cheng ) was an assistant professor of mathematics ( specializing in probability and statistics ) at Carnegie Mellon University who died on 3 July 1981 ( aged 31 ) under mysterious circumstances .
Francis Close ( 11 July 1797 -- 18 December 1882 ) was the Anglican rector of Cheltenham ( 1826 - -1856 ) and Dean of Carlisle ( 1856 - -1881 ) .
Gene Gerrard ( 31 August 1892 -- 1 June 1971 ) was an English film and stage actor , and occasional film director .
Lupus Servatus , also Servatus Lupus ( c. 805 -- c. 862 ) , in French Loup , was a Benedictine monk and Abbot of Ferrières Abbey during the Carolingian dynasty , who was also a member of Charles the Bald 's court and a noted theological author of the 9th century .
Steve Condos ( October 12 , 1918 -- September 16 , 1990 ) was an American tap dancer .
Mammy Lou ( born c. 1804 - died after 1918 ) claimed an age which would have made her one of the earliest - born people to appear in a motion picture .
Sir William Dunch ( 1578 - -1611 ) was an English politician during the reign of King James I. Dunch represented Wallingford in Berkshire ( now Oxfordshire ) as an MP in 1603 .
James Smith Turner ( 1832 - -1904 ) was a Scottish dentist , known for his role in dental surgery regulation .
Dušan Mugoša ( Serbian Cyrillic : Душан Мугоша fl . 7 January 1914 -- 8 August 1973 ) , nicknamed Duć ( Дућ ) , was a Yugoslav Partisan .
Carlile Pollock Patterson ( August 24 , 1816 - -August 15 , 1881 ) was the fourth superintendent of the United States Coast Survey .
Sam Hignett ( 1885 - ca . 1933 ) was an English footballer who played for Liverpool between 1906 and 1908 .
Gabriel Ruotsalainen ( 13 March 1893 -- 1 January 1984 ) was a Finnish long - distance runner .
Charles Fotherby ( ca . 1549 -- 1619 ) was a Church of England clergyman who became Dean of Canterbury Cathedral ( 1615 - -1619 ) .
Alessio Spani or Lekë Shpani ( 1442 - 1495 ) was an Albanian nobleman .
Walter Robert McAlister ( Ontario , 13 August 1931 -- Rio de Janeiro , 13 November 1993 ) was a Canadian Pentecostal minister who founded the New life Christian church ( Portuguese : Igreja Cristã de Nova Vida ) in Brazil .
Marie Angélique de Scorailles ( July 1661 -- 28 June 1681 ) was a French noblewoman and one of the many mistresses of Louis XIV .
Lajos Hencsey ( Szentpéterúr 1814 - Zürich 1844 ) was a Hungarian locksmith or blacksmith who became leader of Samuel Heinrich Fröhlich 's Nazarener Church in Transylvania which continues in Romania with around 1,000 members .
Sir John Carew , 3rd Baronet ( 6 November 1635 -- 1 August 1692 ) of Antony , Cornwall , was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1660 and 1692 .
Lyubomir Miletich ( Bulgarian : Любомир Милетич ) ( 14 January 1863 -- 1 June 1937 ) was a leading Bulgarian linguist , ethnographer , dialectologist and historian , as well as the chairman of the Bulgarian Academy of Sciences from 1926 to his death .
Isaac Johannes Lamotius ( bapt . 29 May 1646 in Beverwijk - 1718 ) or ( 1653 - -1710 ) was governor of Mauritius from 1677 to 1692 .
David Cowan Dobson ( 1894 - -1980 ) , referred to as ' Cowan ' Dobson ARBA ( 1919 ) , RBA ( 1922 ) , was a leading Scottish portrait artist .
Elizabeth Hoffman Honness McKaughan ( June 29 , 1904 -- 2003 ) , better known as Elizabeth Honness , was an American author , poet , and writer .
Friedrich Sigmund Merkel ( 5 April 1845 -- 28 May 1919 ) was a leading German anatomist and histopathologist of the late 19th century .
Ray Gilbert ( 5 September 1912 , Hartford , Connecticut -- 3 March 1976 , Los Angeles , California ) was an American lyricist .
Constanza Hool ( 6 December 1925 -- 20 July 2008 ) was a dancer , actress and choreographer .
David Sanjek ( 3 September 1952 - 29 November 2011 ) was a Professor of Popular Music and Director of the University of Salford Music Research Centre in Salford , Greater Manchester , England .
Otto Christian Blandow ( 5 August 1778 , Waren -- 15 March 1810 , Waren ) was a German apothecary and botanist , specializing in the field of bryology .
Gary Wiggins ( 20 November 1952 -- 25 January 2008 ) was an Australian professional cyclist , who specialised in six - day racing .
Ivor Warne - Smith ( 29 October 1897 -- 4 March 1960 ) , was an Australian footballer , who played for the Melbourne Football Club in the Victorian Football League and for the Latrobe Football Club in the North - Western Football Union in Tasmania .
Duncan McLaren ( 12 January 1800 -- 26 April 1886 ) was a Scottish Liberal Party politician and political writer .
Air Commodore Iswahyudi ( 15 July 1918 -- 14 December 1947 ) was an Indonesian airman and National Hero .
Heinrich Hetsch ( born 2 July 1873 in Mainz , died 3 December 1947 in Bad Homburg ) was a German physician and microbiologist .
Radoslav Hlapen ( Serbian : Радослав Хлапен ; fl . 1350 - -1383 ) was a Serbian magnate who served Serbian Emperor Stefan Dušan ( r. 1331 - 1355 ) and Stefan Uroš V ( r. 1355 - -71 ) as vojvoda ( military commander ) .
Paul Feasey ( 4 May 1933 -- January 2012 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a centre half .
Sidney Oldall Addy ( 9 January 1848 -- 15 November 1933 ) was an English author of books on folklore and history .
Rhys Gethin ( died in 1405 ) was a key figure in the revolt of Owain Glyndŵr .
Miklós Hasznos ( 27 May 1931 -- 23 June 2014 ) was a Hungarian politician , Member of Parliament ( MP ) between 1990 and 1998 .
Heinrich Klebahn ( 20 February 1859 , Bremen -- 5 October 1942 , Hamburg ) was a German mycologist and phytopathologist .
Scipio Kennedy ( c. 1694 - -1774 ) was a slave taken as a child from Guinea in West Africa .
Kid Norfolk ( 10 July 1893 -- 15 April 1968 ) was an African American boxer who fought as a light heavyweight and heavyweight from 1910 through 1926 .
Walter Prideaux ( 1806 - 1889 ) was a poet and lawyer .
Nicholas Conaty ( 1820 - -1886 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic bishop for the Diocese of Kilmore .
Marcello Lante della Rovere ( 1561 -- 19 April 1652 ) was an Italian people Catholic Cardinal appointed Dean and Camerlengo of the College of Cardinals .
John Henry Bufford ( 1810 - 1870 ) was a lithographer in 19th - century Boston , Massachusetts .
Gour Govinda Swami ( 2 September 1929 -- 9 February 1996 ) was a Vaishnava religious leader .
Helena Rutherfurd Ely ( born Helena Rutherfurd : 28 September 1858 -- 18 May 1920 ) was an American author , amateur gardener and founding member of the Garden Club of America whose three books influenced American and British gardeners to avoid Victorian formal gardens in favor of plantings that embodied an `` informal and sensual style . ''
Alois Heldmann died on 1 November 1983 in his native Grevenbruck .
Josef Václav Myslbek ( 20 June 1848 -- 2 June 1922 ) was a Czech sculptor and medalist credited with founding the modern Czech sculpting style .
Cledwyn Hughes , Baron Cledwyn of Penrhos CH PC ( 14 September 1916 -- 22 February 2001 ) was a moderate Welsh Labour politician .
François Sterchele ( 14 March 1982 -- 8 May 2008 ) was a Belgian footballer who played for Germinal Beerschot and Club Brugge .
Pedro Otto Bumbel ( 6 July 1914 -- 2 August 1998 ) was a Brazilian professional football manager who coached a number of Spanish club sides , including Sabadell , Valencia , Racing de Santander , Elche , Sevilla , Atlético Madrid and Málaga .
Martha E. Bernal was a clinical psychologist who was born on April 13 , 1931 , in San Antonio , Texas , and she died of cancer at the age of 70 in 2001 .
Alonso de Fonseca y Acevedo ( died 1512 ) was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as Archbishop of Santiago de Compostela ( 1460 - 1565 and 1469 - 1507 ) , and Archbishop of Seville ( 1465 - 1469 ) .
Sallam ibn Mishkam ( died 628 ) was a Jewish warrior , rabbi and poet who lived in Medina , Arabia , in the early seventh century .
Pallathadka Keshava Bhat ( 3 January 1940 - 25 July 2010 ) ( also known as Dr. P. Keshava Bhat ) was a retired professor , prominent ethnobotanist , botanist , naturalist , proponent of herbalism , scientist and a well known personality in Venezuela .
John Bromfield , Jr. ( 11 April 1779 -- 9 December 1849 ) was a Boston merchant and benefactor of the Boston Athenæum .
Elton Hayes ( 16 February 1915 -- 23 September 2001 ) was a British actor and guitarist .
John Wheeley Gough Gutch ( 1809 - -1862 ) was a British surgeon and editor .
Gunnar Gunnarson ( 1918 -- 2002 ) was a Swedish socialist , marxist historian , writer and publicist .
Sir Leonard Chamberlain or Chamberlayne ( died 1561 ) was an English soldier and politician , the Governor of Guernsey from 1553 .
Nihâl Chand ( 1710 - -1782 ) was an Indian artist who produced some of the best known examples of Rajput painting .
François Peccatte ( born Mirecourt , 10 March 1821 ; died Paris , 30 October 1855 ) was a very talented archetier .
The Blessed Margareta Ebner , O.P. , ( 1291 -- 20 June 1351 ) was a German nun who is considered part of the tradition of German mysticism and a visionary .
Armen Dorian ( Armenian : Արմէն Տօրեան ; 28 January 1892 -- 1915 ) was a renowned Armenian poet , teacher , and editor who lived in the Ottoman Empire .
Beatrice Kean Seymour ( 1 September 1886 -- 31 October 1955 ) was a prolific British novelist and short story writer .
Richard Woodville , 3rd Earl Rivers ( 1453 -- 6 March 1491 ) succeeded his brother , Anthony Woodville , as the third Earl Rivers .
Dwight Shepler ( 1905 - 1974 ) was an American naval officer and painter .
Nathan Porges ( 21 December 1848 -- 27 August 1924 ) was a Bohemian German rabbi .
Ture Cailo ( died 23 October 2009 ) was a Vanuatuan politician and member of Parliament .
Fritz Koselka ( 24 July 1905 Graz in Austria Hungary - 1978 ) was an Austrian screenwriter and writer .
Heinrich Bach ( 26 September ( O.S. 16 September ) 1615 -- 20 July ( O.S. 10 July ) 1692 ) was a German organist , composer and a member of the Bach family .
Joseph Romilly ( 1791 - -1864 ) was an English academic administrator , known as a diarist .
John I , Count of Foix also known as Jean de Foix - Grailly ( 1382 -- 4 May 1436 ) was Count of Foix from 1428 until his death in 1436 .
June Morrall ( 1947 - 2010 ) was a writer and San Mateo County ( northern California ) historian .
Henry Holbeach ( c. 1477 -- 2 August 1551 ) was an English clergyman who served as the last Prior and first Dean of Worcester , a suffragan bishop , and diocesan bishop of two Church of England dioceses .
Vardan Areveltsi ( Armenian : Վարդան Արևելցի ; Vardan the Easterner , circa 1198 -- 1271 AD ) was a thirteenth - century Armenian historian , geographer , philosopher and translator .
Emil Riebeck ( 11 June 1853 -- 22 June 1885 ) was a German explorer , mineralogist , ethnologist , and naturalist .
John Bysse ( c.1602 - -1680 ) was a member of the Parliament of Ireland during the 1630s and 1640s : he was excluded from office during the Interregnum and was one of the leading Irish judges after the restoration of the monarchy .
Sixten Larsson ( 31 July 1918 -- 3 February 1995 ) was a Swedish athlete who competed mainly in the 400 m hurdles .
T. S. Murugesan Pillai ( 1870 - 1930 ) was a Telugu writer , poet and translator who is known for translating Tamil classical works into Telugu .
Torrington Blatchford ( 1871 - -1938 ) was an Australian geologist and was Government Geologist in Western Australia from 1929 until 1934 .
Augustus Dayton Clark ( died 1990 ) , a 1922 graduate of the United States Naval Academy and a United States Naval captain , was Commanding Officer of Force Mulberry A ( a Mulberry harbour ) at Omaha Beach during the Invasion of Normandy on June 6 , 1944 .
Léonin ( also Leoninus , Leonius , Leo ) ( fl . 1150s -- d. ? 1201 ) was the first known significant composer of polyphonic organum .
Margo Oliver ( 1923 -- 4 June 2010 ) was a Canadian writer on cooking .
Seán Mac Giollarnáth , Irish folklorist , 1880 - 29 January 1970 .
Shamoke ( died 222 ) was the king of the tribal people of the five valleys in Wuling during the late Eastern Han Dynasty and Three Kingdoms period of Chinese history .
John Allan Broun FRS ( 21 September 1817 -- 22 November 1879 ) was a Scottish scientist with interests in magnetism , particularly of the earth , and meteorology .
Hedvig Elisabet Strömfelt , née Wrangel ( 1687 - 8 March 1751 ) , was a Swedish courtier .
Charles Pierre Melly ( born Tuebrook , Liverpool , England ; 25 May 1829 -- 1888 ) was a philanthropist mostly known today for his drinking fountains , which he created to make drinking water available to the public .
Illa Martin ( born Sybilla Kesselburg ; 25 February 1900 -- 6 August 1988 ) was a German dendrologist , botanist , conservationist and dentist .
Vũ Giáng Hương ( Hanoi , 23 January 1930 -- 20 August 2011 ) was a Vietnamese woman painter .
David Shiffman ( Hebrew : דוד שיפמן‎ ; 14 April 1923 -- 18 October 1982 ) was an Israeli politician who served as Deputy Minister of Transport and as a member of the Knesset between 1981 and his death in 1982 .
James Gillespie Graham ( 1776 - -1855 ) was a Scottish architect , prominent in the early 19th century .
William Nicholas Willis ( 3 August 1858 -- 3 April 1922 ) was an Australian politician and newspaper proprietor .
Alexander Kolb ( 12 . May 1891 -- 4 April 1963 ) was a German Generalleutnant during World War II .
Major Davis ( 27 March 1882 -- 27 April 1959 ) was an English cricketer who played one first - class match , for Worcestershire against Oxford University in 1911 .
John Quinton Pringle ( 13 December 1864 -- 25 April 1925 ) ( Age 60 ) was a Scottish painter , influenced by Jules Bastien - Lepage and associated with the Glasgow Boys .
Martin Baum ( 15 June 1765 in Hagerstown , Maryland -- 14 December 1831 in Cincinnati , Ohio ) was an American businessman and politician .
Richard Estcourt ( 1668 - -1712 ) was an English actor , who began by playing comedy parts in Dublin .
Tadjou Salou ( 24 December 1974 -- 2 April 2007 ) was a Togolese football player who captained the national side .
Owen Oglethorpe ( died 1559 ) was an English academic and Roman Catholic Bishop of Carlisle , 1557 - -1559 .
Jean Dorey , ( 27 January 1831 of Ville - ès - Nouaux in Saint - Hélier-23 August 1872 ) , was a Norman language writer from Jersey .
Raymund Schwager ( 11 November 1935 -- 27 February 2004 ) was a Swiss Roman Catholic priest and theologian .
Charles James Patrick Mahon , known as the O'Gorman Mahon or James Patrick Mahon ( 17 March 1800 -- 15 June 1891 ) was an Irish nationalist journalist , barrister , parliamentarian and international mercenary .
Alexander Handyside Ritchie ( 15 April 1804 -- 24 April 1870 ) was a Scottish sculptor born in Musselburgh in 1804 , the son of James Ritchie , a local brickmaker and ornamental plasterer , and his wife Euphemia .
David Tebele Scheuer ( 1712 - -1782 ) was a German rabbi .
Hellmut Lange ( 19 January 1923 -- 13 January 2011 ) was an actor and journalist who became famous as action hero on TV and eventually succeeded as presenter of his popular TV show `` Kennen Sie Kino ? '' ( `` Are you a cinema connoisseur ? '' )
Vehib Pasha also known as Wehib Pasha , Vehip Pasha , Mehmed Wehib Pasha , Mehmet Vehip Pasha ( modern Turkish : Kaçı Vehip Paşa or Mehmet Vehip ( Kaçı ) , 1877 - -1940 ) , was a general in the Ottoman Army .
John Welcome ( before 1523 - -1580 ) , of the High Street , Lincoln , was an English politician .
Jack Sher ( 16 March 1913 - 23 August 1988 ) was an American director , writer and producer .
Alojzy Wir - Konas ( Maków Podhalański , 1894 -- 1940 ) was a Polish military commander and the Colonel in the Polish Army .
George Guest CBE FRCO ( February 9 , 1924 - November 20 , 2002 ) was a Welsh organist and choral conductor .
Robert Tanner Freeman ( 1846 - -1873 ) was the first African - American to graduate from the Harvard School of Dental Medicine and may have been the first African - American awarded a dental degree in the United States .
Ambrose Dyson ( 1876 -- 3 June 1913 ) , often known as Amb Dyson was an Australian illustrator and political cartoonist , born at Alfredton , near Ballarat , Victoria , Australia , the son of George Dyson , then a hawker and later a mining engineer , and his wife Jane , née Mayall .
William Marshall Inge ( 1802 - 1846 ) was an American politician that represented Tennessee 's tenth district in the United States House of Representatives .
Solomon Hardy ( 18 May 1863 -- 5 July 1931 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Derbyshire in 1898 .
Arthur Cheetham ( 1864 -- 15 January 1937 ) was an English - born Welsh filmmaker , who became the first of his profession to be based in Wales .
Giulio Cybo ( or Cibo ) ( died 18 May 1548 ) was an Italian noble from Genoa .
Jean - Claude Bajeux ( 17 September 1931 -- 5 August 2011 ) was a Haitian political activist and professor of Caribbean literature .
Brigid Lyons Thornton ( 1896 -- 15 November 1987 ) was a member of Cumann na mBan , an officer in the Irish Free State Army and a physician .
Zhang Guoliang ( traditional Chinese : 張國樑 ; simplified Chinese : 张国梁 ; pinyin : Zhāng Guóliáng ; 1810 - April 1860 ) , born in Guangdong , was a Field Marshal for the Qing dynasty .
Andrzej Ciołkosz ( 1929 - -1952 ) , nom de plume Joseph Marek , was a young Polish language writer , literary critic and translator .
Andrew Bisset ( 20 January 1953 -- 14 April 2005 ) was an Australian author , music educator and singer , based in Canberra .
Bantwal Vaikunta Baliga ( 1895 - -1968 ) was a lawyer who played an active role in Indian governance and politics .
Leo Kelly died on 22 August 2007 after a long illness .
Edgar Dunbar ( 12 April 1902 -- 5 July 1985 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Frederick William Haddon ( 8 February 1839 -- 7 March 1906 ) , was an Australian journalist and newspaper editor .
John Strettell of London , England , was one of the most important merchants providing trade goods to the Canadian fur trade in the period between the Conquest of Canada and his death in 1786 .
Jean Simeon Rousseau de la Rottière ( 1747 - -1820 ) was a French decorative painter .
Clyde Troutt ( August 23 , 1901 - October , 1979 ) was an American trainer of Thoroughbred racehorses .
R. Gundu Rao ( 8 April 1937 - -22 August 1993 ) was the Chief Minister of Karnataka state from 1980 to 1983 .
Barry Fitzgerald ( 10 March 1888 -- 14 January 1961 ) was an Irish stage , film and television actor .
Mireya Véliz ( 1915 - 5 September 2013 ) was a Chilean actress with a career of more than 50 years , retiring at the age of 96 .
Samuel Moss ( 13 Dec. 1858 -- 14 May 1918 ) , was a Welsh Liberal politician and Judge .
Gongsun Zan ( died 199 ) , courtesy name Bogui , was a warlord who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
Anne Macaulay ( 11 March 1924 -- 1998 ) was a British musicologist , author and lecturer .
William Neville , 1st Earl of Kent KG ( c. 1405 -- 9 January 1463 ) and jure uxoris 6th Baron Fauconberg , was an English nobleman and soldier .
Laura de Noves ( 1310 - -1348 ) was the wife of Count Hugues de Sade ( ancestor of Marquis de Sade ) .
Clive Exton ( 11 April 1930 -- 16 August 2007 ) was a British television and film screenwriter , sometime playwright , and former actor .
Stephen Bamford ( December 1770 -- 14 August 1848 ) was a minister and Canadian soldier .
Rodolfo Pio da Carpi ( 22 February 1500 -- 2 May 1564 ) was an Italian Cardinal , humanist and patron of the arts .
Roger Sablonier ( 16 April 1943 -- 8 June 2010 ) was a Swiss historian and writer of non - fiction publications , and Emeritus ( Prof . Dr. ) of the faculty of the University of Zürich .
Maria Quisling , born Maria Vasilyevna Pasek / Pasetchnikova , ( 10 October 1900 -- 17 January 1980 ) , was known as the wife of Vidkun Quisling , though historians have doubts about whether the couple were legally married .
Frank John Powell ( 15 March 1891 -- 31 October 1971 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician and magistrate .
Charles Henry McKiernan ( 1825 - -1892 ) , known popularly as `` Mountain Charley , '' was one of the first European settlers in the Santa Cruz Mountains region of California .
Martin Charles Reddington ( 15 November 1919 -- 1 March 2015 ) , better known as Tony Reddin , was an Irish hurler who played as a goalkeeper for the Galway and Tipperary senior teams .
Ludwik Skumin Tyszkiewicz ( born 1748 in Wilno -- 26 June 1808 ) was a Polish--
Peter Deriabin ( 1921 - 1992 ) ( Петр Дерябин ) was a Russian Communist Party member , World War II veteran , SMERSH agent , and KGB agent who later defected to the United States .
William Maccall ( 1812 - -1888 ) was a Scottish author and Unitarian minister .
Henry Herbert , 4th Baron Herbert of Chirbury ( died 1691 ) was an English aristocrat , soldier and politician .
Charles Bucke ( 16 April 1781 -- 31 July 1846 ) was an English writer who , despite being poor most of his life , still managed to produce roughly eleven different works , each varying in number of volumes and topics .
Mehrdad Avesta ( Persian : مهرداد اوستا‎ ; 8 August 1930 -- 6 May 1991 ) was an Iranian contemporary poet .
Marsinah ( 10 April 1969 -- 8 May 1993 ) was a worker activist at an Indonesian company , PT Catur Putra Surya in Porong , Sidoarjo , East Java province , whose rape and murder drew international attention to the practices of the Suharto dictatorship and the suppression of workers .
Ambrogio Preda ( Milan , December 25 , 1839 - Davesco Soragno , Lugano , June 5 , 1906 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of landscapes of the alpine mountains and valleys .
Lu Rong ( Chinese : 陆容 ; pinyin : Lù Róng ; 1436 - -1494 ) was a Chinese scholar .
Sylvia Hahn ( 2 May 1911 -- 2 January 2001 ) was a Canadian artist and head of the art department at the Royal Ontario Museum .
Abby Whiteside ( 1881 - -1956 ) was an influential American piano teacher .
Dr Charles Alexander MacMunn ( 11 April 1852 - 18 February 1911 ) was the first to describe the respiratory pigment in blood , known today as Cytochrome1 .
Joseph Irving ( 1830 - -1891 ) was a Scottish journalist , historian and annalist .
Melattur Venkatarama Sastry ( 1770 - 1830 ) was a Telugu poet and playwright who is credited with founding the Bhagavatha Melas .
Jenő Kalmár ( 21 March 1908 - 13 January 1990 ) , also referred to as János Kalmar or Kálmár Jenő , is a former Hungarian footballer and coach .
Iris du Pré ( 6 June 1914 -- 27 September 1985 ) was an English pianist , composer , conductor and educator .
David Marshall Lang ( 6 May 1924 -- 20 March 1991 ) , was a Professor of Caucasian Studies , School of Oriental and African Studies , University of London .
Saint Alexander of Comana ( died c. 251 ) , known as `` the charcoal burner '' , was Bishop of Comana in Pontus .
Biman Mukhopadhyay ( September 1930 -- 16 March 2011 ) was a famous Bengali singer and trainer .
Kevin Danaher ( Irish , Caoimhín Ó Danachair ) ( 30 January 1913 -- 14 March 2002 ) was a prominent Irish folklorist with a special interest in ethnography and military history .
Samuel Bellin ( 13 May 1799 - 29 April 1893 ) was an English printmaker and engraver .
William Timothy Cape ( 25 October 1806 -- 4 June 1863 ) was an early school master in Sydney , Australia ; several of the Premiers of New South Wales attended his school .
Francis Meres ( 1565/6 -- 29 January 1647 ) was an English churchman and author .
Donald Powell Distinguished Service Order ( 1896 - -1942 ) was an officer in the British Indian Army during World War I and World War II
Eugène Boullet ( 1 July 1847 , in Acheux -- 1923 ) full name Eugène Anatole Auguste Victor Boullet was a French naturalist , entomologist and collector .
Solène Coulot ( 21 March 1989 -- 20 February 2010 ) was a French curler .
Shi Kefa ( 4 February 1601 -- 20 May 1645 ) , courtesy names Xianzhi and Daolin , was a government official and calligrapher who lived in the late Ming dynasty .
Azmi Nassar ( Arabic : عزمي نصار‎ , Hebrew : עזמי נסאר‎ ; 3 October 1957 -- 26 March 2007 ) was an Arab - Israeli football manager and served as manager of the Palestinian national football team .
Myrtle Devenish ( 1913 -- 21 January 2007 ) was a film actor .
General Charles Cadogan , 2nd Baron Cadogan ( 1685 -- 24 September 1776 ) was a British peer , soldier and Whig politician .
Boccaccio Boccaccino ( c. 1467 -- c. 1525 ) was a painter of the early Italian Renaissance , belonging to the Emilian school .
Lupau Ratna Tuladhar ( Devanagari : लुपौ रत्न तुलाधर ) ( 22 June 1918 -- 2 June 1993 ) was a Nepalese trader and transport pioneer .
Anjali Devi ( pronunciation ; 24 August 1927 -- 13 January 2014 ) was an Indian actress , former model and producer in Telugu and Tamil .
Charles Barter ( died 1859 ) was a British gardener and botanist who trained at Kew Gardens in London from 1849 to 1851 .
William W. Lockwood ( William Wirt or Bill ) ( 1906 - 1978 ) was a noted academic who was Research Secretary ( 1935 - 1940 ) and Executive Secretary ( 1941 - 1943 ) at the Institute of Pacific Relations .
Alexandro Alves do Nascimento ( 30 December 1974 -- 14 November 2012 ) was a Brazilian footballer who has played for Kavala in Greece .
Sir ( John ) Henry Morris - Jones MC , DL ( 2 November 1884 -- 9 July 1972 ) was a Welsh doctor , soldier and Liberal , later Liberal National politician .
Joseph Barney ( Wolverhampton 1753 -- 13 April 1832 London ) , was an English artist and engraver .
William of St Paul , also William de Paul ( died 1349 ) was an English Carmelite , bishop of Meath in Ireland from 1327 .
Henry Clifford , 10th Baron de Clifford , also 10th feudal baron of Skipton ( ca . 1454 -- 23 April 1523 ) was a member of the Clifford family which was seared at Skipton Castle from 1310 to 1676 .
Lieutenant - General Henry Wilmot , 1st Earl of Rochester ( 26 October 1612 -- 19 February 1658 ) , known as The Lord Wilmot between 1643 and 1644 and as The Viscount Wilmot between 1644 and 1652 , was an English Cavalier who fought for the Royalist cause during the Wars of the Three Kingdoms .
Saridey Varalakshmi ( 13 August 1925 -- 22 September 2009 ) , popularly known as S. Varalakshmi , was a veteran Telugu and Tamil actress and singer .
Loreta Janeta Velázquez is said to have died in 1897 , but historian Richard Hall asserts that the place and date of her death are unknown .
Andrew of Carniola ( 1399 -- November 13 , 1484 ) was a Roman Catholic archbishop from Carniola , in present - day Slovenia .
Jan Kalenec ( 1490 - -1546 ) was a Prague cutler who took up the leadership of the Amosites , a radical branch of the Czech Brethren after the death of their elderly figurehead Amos .
Mushail Mushailov ( Russian : Мушаилов Мушаил Ханухович ; Hebrew : ; מושאיל מושאילוב‎ born July 10 , 1941 -- January 4 , 2007 ) was a Soviet /Russian artist and teacher of Mountain Jewish descent . He was a member of the USSR Union of Artists and Israel .
Norah Isaac ( 1915 -- 3 August 2003 ) was a Welsh author , drama producer and campaigner for Welsh - language education .
Gaston Hamelin ( 27 May 1884 -- 8 September 1951 ) was a French clarinetist and teacher .
Major - General Harold Percy Waller Barrow , CB CMG DSO OBE ( 30 June 1876 -- 20 December 1957 ) was Colonel Commandant , Royal Army Medical Corps ( 1941 - -46 ) and an Honorary Surgeon to King George V.
Emil Grallert ( 1848 - 1923 ) was German Consul in Zanzibar from 1877 to 1884 .
Jack Tripp MBE ( 4 February 1922 -- 10 July 2005 ) was an English comic actor , singer and dancer who appeared in seaside variety shows and revues and became best known for his many performances as a pantomime dame .
Harry Pelling Gill ( 9 March 1855 -- 25 May 1916 ) was an English - born Australian art curator , teacher and painter .
Dr. Ho Sai - chuen ( circa 1891 -- 29 April 1938 ) was a Hong Kong doctor from the influential Hotung family and member of the Sanitary Board .
Zhang Jingda ( 張敬達 ) ( d. December 25 , 936 ) , courtesy name Zhitong ( 志通 ) , nickname Shengtie ( 生鐵 , `` raw iron '' ) , was a general of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms Period state Later Tang .
Walter Klimmek ( 14 March 1919 -- 13 May 2010 ) was a German football defender , coal miner and firefighter .
Felice Lattuada ( Italian pronunciation : ( feˈliːtʃe lattuˈaːda ; latˈtwaːda ) ; 5 February 1882 - 2 November 1962 ) was an Italian composer .
Edwin Randolph Oakes ( March 25 , 1818 in Pleasant Valley , Nova Scotia -- 1889 ) was a Canadian and Nova Scotian politician and merchant .
K. T. Achaya ( Oct 6 , 1923 -Sep 5 , 2002 ) was an eminent oil chemist , food scientist , nutritionist and food historian .
Robert Wilson Hamilton ( 1819 - 9 August 1904 ) was an American - born lawyer and judge who was the inaugural Attorney General of Fiji .
William G. Distin ( 1884 - -1970 ) , an architect of Saranac Lake , New York , was an early associate of Great Camp designer William L. Coulter who went on to design a number of Adirondack Great Camps .
Abiezer Coppe ( 1619 -- 1672 ) was one of the English Ranters and a writer of prophetic religious pamphlets .
Munatia Plancina ( died 33 AD ) was a Roman noblewoman who lived in the early times of the Empire founded by Augustus .
Samuel Sanders Teulon ( 2 March 1812 -- 2 May 1873 ) was a 19th - century English Gothic Revival architect , noted for his use of polychrome brickwork , and the complex planning of his buildings .
Brian Bromley ( 20 March 1946 -- 9 March 2012 ) was an English footballer who played for Bolton Wanderers , Portsmouth , Brighton and Hove Albion , Reading and Darlington in the Football League and Wigan Athletic in the Northern Premier League .
Sherlock Yarde ( unknown -- 21 June 2012 ) was a football administrator and former manager of the Barbados national football team .
Tadeusz Breyer ( 15 October 1874 in Mielec -- 15 May 1952 in Warsaw ) - Polish sculptor and medallic artist .
Thomas Yale ( 1525/6 - -1577 ) was an English civil lawyer .
Jekuthiel Ginsburg ( 1889 - -1957 ) was professor of mathematics at Yeshiva University .
Tsipön Lungshar born Dorje Tsegyal ( 1880 - -1938 ) was a noted Tibetan politician who was accused by conservative political opponents of attempting to become the paramount figure of the Tibetan government in the 1930s , by planning a communist coup following the death of the 13th Dalai Lama .
Edmund Concanon , Irish solicitor and town commissioner , 1816 - -1902 .
Philip Cogan ( 1750 -- 3 February 1833 ) was an Irish composer , pianist , and conductor -- the most important Irish piano composer before Field .
Arthur Catterall ( 25 May 1883 -- 28 November 1943 ) was an English concert violinist , orchestral leader and conductor , one of the best - known English classical violinists of the first half of the twentieth century .
John Poulett , 1st Earl Poulett KG ( c.1668 -- 28 May 1743 ) was an English peer .
Jacob Worm Skjelderup ( 3 December 1804 -- 2 September 1863 ) was Norwegian state secretary from 1859 to 1863 , appointed Minister of the Navy in 1860 , and temporary councillor of state 1861 .
Agathangjel Mbrica ( 1883 - 1957 ) was an Albanian artist and goldsmith .
Anarawd ap Gruffydd ( died 1143 ) was a Prince of Deheubarth in Southwest Wales .
Adolfo Ibáñez Boggiano ( 1880 - -1949 ) was a Chilean businessman and former Minister of Foment .
Pedro Correia da Cunha ( 1440 -- Lisbon , 1497 ) , was a Portuguese nobleman who was the Second Donatary - Captain of Porto Santo , and the 1st Donatary - Captain of the island of Graciosa , in the Portuguese archipelago of the Azores .
Seonjong of Goryeo ( 9 October 1049 -- 17 June 1094 ) ( r. 1083 - -1094 ) was the 13th king of Goryeo .
Shiina Yasutane ( 椎名 康胤 died March , 1576 ) was a Japanese daimyo of the Sengoku period , who was lord of the Shiina clan of Etchu Province .
David Caminer , OBE ( 26 June 1915 -- 19 June 2008 ) has been called the World 's First Corporate Electronic Systems Analyst & The World 's First Software Engineer .
David Lichine ( Russian : Дэвид ( Давид ) Лишин ; 25 October 1910 -- 26 June 1972 ) was a Russian - American ballet dancer and choreographer .
Galal Keraitam ( Arabic : جلال قريطم‎ ) ( January 1913 - -30 October 1961 ) , was an Egyptian former footballer who played as a Defender for Zamalek .
Johan Fredrik Feyer ( 16 July 1821 -- 26 June 1880 ) was a Norwegian industrial pioneer and factory owner .
Huo Yanwei ( 霍彥威 ) ( 872 - 928 ) , known as Li Shaozhen ( 李紹真 ) from 924 to 926 , courtesy name Zizhong ( 子重 ) , formally Duke Zhongwu of Jin ( 晉忠武公 ) , was a general of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period states Later Liang and Later Tang .
Guo Yingqiu ( Chinese : 郭影秋 ; 1909 - -1985 ) was a Chinese politician and educator .
Harold Avery ( 1867 - -1943 ) was an English author of children 's literature .
Sir Coplestone Bampfylde , 2nd Baronet ( ca . 1633 -- 9 February 1692 ) of Poltimore and North Molton and Warleigh , Tamerton Foliot , in Devon , was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1659 and 1689 .
Georgios Streit ( Greek : Γεώργιος Στρέιτ ; 1868 - -1948 ) was a Greek lawyer and professor .
John Alen ( 1476 - -1534 ) was an English canon lawyer , Archbishop of Dublin , and Lord Chancellor of Ireland , who was murdered during the Rebellion of `` Silken Thomas '' Fitzgerald .
Geoffrey Plumpton Wilson ( 21 February 1878 -- 30 July 1934 ) was an English amateur footballer who played at inside left .
Frederick Taylor Gates ( 1853 - -1929 ) was an American Baptist clergyman , educator , and the principal business and philanthropic advisor to the major oil industrialist and philanthropist John D. Rockefeller , Sr . , from 1891 to 1923 .
Sir James Montgomery , 1st Baronet Stanhope FRSE ( 1721 -- 2 April 1803 ) was a Scottish advocate , judge , politician , agriculturalist and landowner .
Arthur West Haddan ( 1816 - -1873 ) was an English churchman and academic , of High Church Anglican views , now remembered as an ecclesiastical historian , particularly for Councils and Ecclesiastical Documents relating to Great Britain and Ireland , written with William Stubbs .
Hong Jong - u ( 홍종우 , 洪鍾宇 , 1850 ~ 1913 ) was a Korean , assassin , reformer , activist and statesman during the Korean Empire .
Hilde Zimmermann , born Hilde Wundsam , ( 12 September 1920 -- 25 March 2002 ) was an Austrian resistance fighter against nazism and survivor of the KZ Ravensbrück ( also known as the deathmarch ) .
William Barons ( also Barnes ; died 1505 ) was the Bishop of London from 1504 to 1505 .
Asad Ali Khan ( Hindi : असद अली खान ) ( 1937 -- 14 June 2011 ) was an Indian musician who played the plucked string instrument rudra veena .
