Al - Mundhir IV ibn al - Mundhir ( Arabic : المنذر بن المنذر‎ ) was the king of the Lakhmid Arabs in 574 - -580 .
Philip I , Count of Waldeck ( 1445 - -1475 ) was briefly Count of Waldeck - Waldeck in Germany in 1475 .
Lord Francis Hervey JP ( 16 October 1846 -- 10 January 1931 ) was a British barrister and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons in two periods between 1874 and 1892 .
Baron Béla Tallián de Vizek ( 1851 -- 23 November 1921 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Agriculture between 1903 and 1905 .
Florence Sarah Lees ( 31 March 1840 -- 19 October 1922 ) was one of the English pioneers of district nursing .
John Eddowes Bowman the Younger ( 1819 - -1854 ) was an English chemist .
Calle Lindström ( 1868 - 1955 ) was a Swedish singer and comedian from Östergötland .
Sir Harold Baxter Kittermaster KCMG , KBE ( 14 May 1879 -- 20 March 1939 ) was governor of British Somaliland ( now Somalia ) , British Honduras ( now Belize ) , and then of the Nyasaland protectorate ( now Malawi ) in the period before the Second World War .
Władysław Franciszek Jabłonowski ( 25 October 1769 -- 29 September 1802 ) was a Black Polish and French general .
Joseph Carew ( c1820 - 1870 ) was a sculptor in Boston , Massachusetts , active between 1840 - -1870 , and collaborated with Thomas A. Carew as the firm Carew & Brother .
Kang Shi'en ( Chinese : 康世恩 ; 20 April 1915 -- 21 April 1995 ) was a Chinese Communist revolutionary who participated in the December 9th Movement and a politician who served as China 's Vice Premier and Minister of Petroleum .
Walter J. Carr ( 1896 -- 1970 ) was an American pilot and aircraft promoter .
Jerome de Angelis ( 1567 -- 4 December 1623 ) was an Italian Jesuit missionary to Japan .
Sir Miles Partridge ( died 26 February 1552 ) was an English courtier during the reigns of Henry VIII and Edward VI .
John Herbert Long FRCO ( 1 July 1908 - 1985 ) was an English music teacher and organist .
Waller Rodwell Wright ( died 1826 ) , author of `` Horæ Ionicæ , '' was British consul - general for the republic of the Seven Islands ( Ionian Islands ) from 1800 to 1804 .
Willoughby Williams , Jr. ( 1798 - 1882 ) was an American banker and sheriff from Tennessee .
Dr. Fred E. Luborsky ( 1923 - -2010 ) was an American physical chemist noted for his contributions to the field of permanent magnetism and amorphous metals .
Schlombs was initiated Erzdiözesanbaumeister the Diocesan Building Authority until his retirement in 1985th Prof . Dr. Wilhelm Schlombs died on 25 August 1993 .
Marten Schagen ( 24 October 1700 , Alkmaar -- 20 October 1770 , Utrecht ) was a Dutch Mennonite bookseller , translator , journal editor and historian .
Fay Godwin ( 17 February 1931 -- 27 May 2005 ) was a British photographer known for her black - and - white landscapes of the British countryside and coast .
Wilson Follett ( 1887 - -1963 ) was an American writer who is known now almost exclusively for his book Follett 's Modern American Usage , which was unfinished at his death and was therefore completed and edited by his friend Jacques Barzun ( in collaboration with six other people who helped with the editing ) and published posthumously .
Robert Eyres Landor ( 10 May 1781 -- 26 January 1869 ) was an English writer , dramatist , poet , and Anglican clergyman .
Henry Sulley ( 1845 - -1940 ) was an English architect and writer on the temples of Jerusalem .
Paul Auloge - Duvivier known as Paul Duvivier ( 19 July 1869 - 1956 ) , was a French journalist at Lyon .
John Chalmers Morton ( 1821 - -1888 ) was a Scottish agriculturist and writer .
Wang Xiaotong ( 王孝通 ) ( AD 580 - -640 ) , also known as Wang Hs'iao - t'ung , was a Chinese mathematician and calendarist .
Leon Carnovsky ( November 28 , 1903 - -December 6 , 1975 ) was a librarian and educator who focused much of his time to the survey of libraries in the United States and around the globe .
Earl Armstrong ( 1900 - 1986 ) was an Ontario farmer and politician .
Radič Božić ( Serbian : Радич Божић ; fl . 1502 - September 1528 ) was the Despot of Serbia in 1527 until his death in September 1528 .
Ernst Otto Stalinski ( 1944 -- 2005 ) was a German humanist and entrepreneur .
Lale Oraloğlu ( 15 August 1924 -- 15 January 2007 ) was a Turkish actress and screenwriter .
Percy Edward Pinkerton ( 19 June 1855 -- 31 August 1946 ) was an English translator and poet .
Johann Gottfried Rosenberg ( late 1709 - 4 June 1776 ) was a German - Danish architect working in the Rococo style .
Dimitrie Ghica or Ghika ( 31 May 1816 - - 15 February 1897 ) was a Romanian politician .
Daniel Bremer Juell ( 1 January 1808 -- 26 May 1855 ) was a Norwegian clergyman and politician .
Sirpa Lane , born Sirpa Salo ( 1952 - -1999 ) was a Finnish actress known for her work in B - movies of the 1970s , primarily erotic and exploitation films .
Virginie Bovie ( 1821 - -1888 ) , full name Joséphine - Louise - Virginie Bovie , was a Belgian painter and arts patron .
Romany Bain ( 22 March 1924 -- 29 March 2015 ) was a British journalist and showbusiness interviewer .
Frederic Adolph Hoefer ( 14 April 1850 -- 7 October 1938 ) was a Dutch lieutenant - general , militaria collector and archivist .
Hector Abhayavardhana ( 5 January 1919 -- 22 September 2012 ) was a Sri Lankan Trotskyist theoretician , a long - standing member of the Lanka Sama Samaja Party ( LSSP ) and a founder - member of the Bolshevik - Leninist Party of India , Ceylon and Burma .
Procopio Cutò , or Francesco Procopio Cutò or Francesco Procopio dei Coltelli ( 9 February 1651 - 10 February 1727 ) was an Italian chef from Sicily .
George Colville ( 1876 - -1928 ) was a Scottish professional footballer .
Sir Isaac Lowthian Bell , 1st Baronet , FRS ( 18 February 1816 -- 20 December 1904 ) was a Victorian ironmaster and Liberal Party politician from Washington , County Durham , in the north of England .
Alexander Mantashev ( Armenian : Ալեքսանդր Մանթաշյան , Aleksandr Mantashian ; Russian : Александр Иванович Манташев , Aleksandr Ivanovich Mantashev ; 3 March 1842 -- 19 April 1911 and was buried on 30 April in the Armenian Pantheon of Tbilisi ) was a prominent Armenian oil magnate , industrialist , financier , and a philanthropist .
Gopalaswamy Mahendraraja ( 1956 -- 28 December 1994 ) , also known as Mahattaya was a member of Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam who was killed for leaking secrets to India 's RAW .
Tom Waye ( 28 December 1909 -- 10 February 1992 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Port Adelaide in the South Australian National Football League ( SANFL ) and Footscray in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Vincent Yorke ( 21 May 1869 -- 27 November 1957 ) was an English cricketer who played for Gloucestershire .
Senator Shehu Usman Albishir ( 15 June 1945 -- 2 July 2012 ) was a Nigerian member of the business family of Alhaji Albishir Abdullahi and Late Hajiya Fatima Albishir .
Bootsmannsmaat Anton Schmitt ( died 31 May 1916 ) was a German sailor killed during World War I. He was a gunner aboard the light cruiser SMS Frauenlob during the Battle of Jutland and stuck by his gun despite grave injury and died when his ship was sunk .
Mahmud Shaterian ( 1944 - -2006 ) was a famous Iranian Azerbaijani composer , musician and Tar master .
Rosemarie Castoro ( born in Brooklyn , New York , United States ; 1939 -- 2015 ) was an American artist associated with the New York Minimalists .
Fu Honglie ( Chinese : 傅弘烈 ; Wade -- Giles : Fu Hung - lieh ) ( died AD 1680 ) was a native of Jiangxi , who gave his allegiance to the Manchus in 1657 and was employed as a Prefect .
Vinnie Roslin ( 1947 - 2012 ) was an American bassist who was an original member of Steel Mill , an early Bruce Springsteen band .
Bill Churchyard ( 2 February 1878 -- 31 August 1957 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ralph Van Deman Magoffin ( 1874 - -1942 ) was an American Classical scholar and archaeologist .
Ellen Lucy or Nelly O'Brien ( 4 June 1864 -- 1 April 1925 ) was an Irish miniaturist , landscape artist , and Gaelic League activist .
Iraj Soleimani ( 15 December 1946 -- 23 February 2009 ) was an Iranian professional footballer .
Bryant Haliday ( 7 April 1928 -- 28 July 1996 ) was an American actor , as well as producer , of film and stage , who was instrumental in providing a showcase for international film titles in the United States by co - founding Janus Films with his partner Cyrus Harvey , Jr.
Agnes Fleischer ( 6 February 1865 -- 15 September 1909 ) was a Norwegian pioneering teacher for disabled persons .
Migettuwatte Gunananda Thera or Mohottiwatte Gunananda Thera ( Sinhala : පූජ්‍ය මිගෙට්ටුවත්තේ ගුණානන්ද හිමි ) ( February 9 , 1823 , Balapitiya -- 21 September 1890 , Colombo ) was a Sri Lankan Buddhist orator .
Johann Georg Mozart ( 4 May 1679 -- 19 February 1736 ) was a bookbinder who lived in Augsburg , Germany , in the 17th and 18th centuries .
John Michael ' Rab ' Rabinovich , later known as J. M. Robson ( 1900 - -1982 ) was a geneticist and physicist who co - founded the science of mutagenesis by mutations in fruit flies exposed to mustard gas , and who first observed neutron beta decay .
Garth Webb ( 1918 -- 8 May 2012 ) was a Canadian soldier who founded the Juno Beach Centre .
Frederik Christian Kielsen ( 7 February 1774 Copenhagen - 18 January 1850 Frederiksberg ) was a Danish schoolmaster noted for editing and publishing a series of copiously illustrated books on natural history - Icones amphibiorum , Icones avium , Icones piscium , Icones vermium , Icones mammalium , Icones insectorum .
Bert Casey ( died 1903 ) was one of the most violent of the outlaws to operate out of Oklahoma Territory .
Maryse Holder ( October 19 , 1940 -- September 1977 ) was an American memoirist and feminist writer , who was the author of Give Sorrow Words .
Anna Rajecka ( 1762 - -1832 ) , was a Polish painter and drawing artist .
Jim Burchill ( 25 October 1897 -- 18 December 1940 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William Roseland ( April 18 , 1892 -- 1946 ) was an American - born farmer and political figure in Saskatchewan .
Smith Wigglesworth ( 8 June 1859 -- 12 March 1947 ) , was a British evangelist and faith healer who was important in the early history of Pentecostalism .
William Dexter ( 1818 - -1860 ) was an English - Australian painter .
Jimmy Seddon ( born 20 May 1895 in Bolton , died October 1971 ) , was a footballer who played most famously in the centre of defence for Bolton Wanderers during the 1920s .
Edward Montagu , 2nd Earl of Sandwich ( 3 January 1647/48 -- 29 November 1688 ) was born in Hinchinbrooke , Huntingdonshire , England to Edward Montagu , 1st Earl of Sandwich and Jemima Crew .
Margaret Nicholl Laird ( 31 July 1897 -- June 1983 ) was an American missionary of the Baptist Mid - Missions who worked in the French colony of Ubangi - Shari and independent Central African Republic ( CAR ) from 1922 until the 1960s .
Manouk Avedissian ( 1841 - 1925 ) , more commonly known as Bechara Effendi ( or Bechara Effendi al - Muhandis , Bechara Afandi , also Bechara Effendi el - Dob `` the bear '' ) was an Ottoman administrator and the chief engineer of the Vilayet of Syria and later of the Vilayet of Beirut .
Freda Meissner - Blau ( 11 March 1927 -- 22 December 2015 ) was an Austrian politician , activist , and prominent figurehead in the Austrian environmental movement .
Raúl Orlandini ( 1952 - -2006 ) was a Peruvian racecar driver .
Bruce K. Reid ( 17 March 1950 -- 15 June 1970 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Tommy Downs ( 22 May 1901 - 11 August 1981 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Robert Aim Lennie ( 6 April 1889 -- 26 March 1961 ) was Regius Professor of Midwifery at the University of Glasgow from 1946 to 1955 .
Arthur Argo ( 1935 - -1981 ) was a Scottish traditional folk musician , promoter and collector and the great grandson of Gavin Greig .
E. Grey Lewis ( died 2005 ) was a United States lawyer who served as General Counsel of the Navy from 1973 to 1977 .
Carl Pontus Gahn ( 1759 - -1825 ) was a Swedish military officer who participated in the Russo - Swedish War in Finland in 1788 - 1789 , the Finnish War campaign in Norway in 1808 and the unsuccessful invasion of Norway at Eidskog in 1814 where he was imprisoned .
Peter of Zittau ( Czech : Petr Žitavský ; c. 1275 - -1339 ) was a Bohemian churchman and historian .
George Douglas of Pittendreich ( died 1552 ) was a member of the powerful Red Douglas family who struggled for control of the young James V of Scotland in 1528 .
Magdalena of Saxony ( 7 March 1507 -- 25 January 1534 ) was Margravine of Brandenburg , its `` Electoral Princess '' , the Electoral equivalent of a crown princess .
Enrico Tarenghi ( April 14 , 1848 -- 1938 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of genre and orientalist paintings .
Nazario Chávez Aliaga ( 1891 - -1978 ) was a Peruvian journalist , politician and poet .
Lieutenant - General Sir Thomas McMahon , 2nd Baronet ( 1779 - -1860 ) was a British Army officer .
Te Pēhi Kupe ( c1795 - 1828 ) was a Māori rangatira and war leader of Ngāti Toa and the uncle of Te Rauparaha .
Doctor Joseph Ritchie ( c. 1788 -- 20 November 1819 ) was an English surgeon , explorer and naturalist .
Leif Johansen ( 11 May 1930 -- 29 December 1982 ) was a Norwegian economist who made a substantial contribution to economic science .
Sir Thomas Dingley ( executed 9 or 10 July 1539 ) was an English prior of the Knights of St. John of Jerusalem .
Ephraim C. Dawes ( 1840 - 1895 ) was an American Civil War soldier , military historian , and businessman .
Philipp Emanuel von Fellenberg ( 27 June 1771 -- 21 November 1844 ) was a Swiss educationalist and agronomist .
Thomas Quiddington ( christened 21 January 1743 , Coulsdon , Surrey -- buried 6 December 1804 , Coulsdon ) was a noted English cricketer of the mid-18th century who played for Surrey .
Emily Grace Barnsley ( 3 October 1896 -- 6 March 1975 ) , known as Grace Barnsley or by her married name , Grace Davies , was an English pottery decorator .
Blagoje Vidinić ( Macedonian : Благоја Видиниќ ; 11 June 1934 -- 29 December 2006 ) was a Macedonian football coach , former player , and former Olympic participant of Serbian origin .
Morgan Kornmo ( 17 April 1925 -- 26 March 2010 ) was a Norwegian evangelist and politician for the Christian Democratic Party .
Simon Ockley ( 1678 -- 9 August 1720 ) was a British Orientalist .
Elgin English Crull ( July 17 , 1908 - -1976 ) was the city manager of Dallas , Texas from 1952 to 1966 .
Grzegorz of Stawiszyn ( Polish : Grzegorz ze Stawiszyna ; 1481 - -1540 ) , was a Polish philosopher and theologian of the mid 16th century , Rector of the University of Krakow in the years 1538 - 1540 .
Raman Raghav ( 1929 -- 1995 ) , also known as Psycho Raman was a psychopathic serial killer who operated in the city of Mumbai , India in the mid-1960s .
Sir Richard Allibond or Allibone ( 1636 - -1688 ) was an English judge and justice of the King 's Bench .
Sidney William Jackson ( 12 June 1873 -- 30 September 1946 ) was an Australian naturalist and field ornithologist with a special interest in oology , who was also a skilled photographer and taxidermist .
Michael Dormer died at home in Ocean Beach , San Diego , California on 10 September 2012 .
Simon Waley Waley ( 23 August 1827 , Stockwell , London -- 30 December 1875 , Marylebone , London ) was one of the leading members of Anglo - Jewry in the 19th century .
Miriam Karlin , OBE ( 23 June 1925 -- 3 June 2011 ) was an English actress whose career lasted for more than 60 years .
Herman Darewski ( 17 April 1883 -- 2 June 1947 ) was a British composer and conductor of light music .
Carl Axel Fredrik Ivar Holmquist ( 22 February 1879 -- 24 September 1954 ) was a Swedish officer and sports official .
Joan Winston ( 19 June 1931 -- 11 September 2008 ) was an American Trekker who helped organize the first Star Trek fan convention and became a key figure in the subculture .
Ralph Weldon ( baptised 1606 -- 1676 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1654 to 1656 .
John Jumper ( 1820 - -1896 ) was Principal Chief of the Seminole Nation from 1849 to 1865 , and again from 1882 to 1885 .
Francis Joseph Huchet ( 1927 - 9 October 1959 ) was the last convicted criminal to be executed by hanging in the Channel Islands .
Edmondo Fabbri ( 16 November 1921 -- 8 July 1995 ) was an Italian football ( soccer ) player and coach ; a fast player , he mainly played as a winger .
George Weidenfeld , Baron Weidenfeld , GBE ( 13 September 1919 -- 20 January 2016 ) was a British publisher , philanthropist , and newspaper columnist .
Chang Man - yong ( January 25 , 1914 -- 1977 ) was a Korean poet and journalist associated with the modernist movement of the 1930s .
Edward Teschemacher ( 1876 - -1940 ) also known as Edward Frederick Lockton was an American lyricist , translator , arranger , librettist , and popular music composer responsible for writing and co - writing a number of well - known pieces , including `` Because''(1902 ) and co - writing `` I 'll Walk Beside You''(1939 ) .
Georg Fugger von der Lilie ( 1453 - -1506 ) was a German merchant of the Fugger dynasty .
Arthur Swift ( 1812 - -1855 ) was a 19th - century Texas merchant , surveyor , political and military figure .
Edwin F. Leonard ( July 15 , 1862 -- November 1931 ) was an American druggist and politician who served in the Massachusetts House of Representatives and as the 37th Mayor of Springfield , Massachusetts .
Nicolò Bonito ( died 1740 in Naples ) was an Italian painter , depicting mainly landscapes .
Robert Bamford ( 1883 - -1942 ) was a British engineer , who with Lionel Walker Birch Martin ( 1878 - - 21 October 1945 ) , founded a company in January 1913 that became Aston Martin .
Alexander McLeod - Lindsay , ( 24 December 1934 -- 17 September 2009 ) was a Scots - born Australian who is noted for having served nine years in jail for attempting to murder his wife , but who was later exonerated .
William Milligan ( 15 March 1821 -- 11 December 1892 ) was a renowned Scottish theologian .
Peter Henry Rolfs ( 1865 - -1944 ) was a prominent Florida agronomist in the early 20th century .
Johann Rudolf Suter ( 29 March 1766 , Zofingen -- 24 February 1827 , Bern ) was a Swiss physician , botanist and philologist .
William Maclure ( 27 October 1763 -- 23 March 1840 ) was an Americanized Scottish geologist , cartographer and philanthropist .
Edward Backwell ( ca . 1618 - -1683 ) was an English goldsmith - banker , and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1673 and 1683 .
Carlo Urbani died on 29 March 2003 at 11:45 AM , after 18 days of intensive care only .
Humphrey Edwards ( 1582 - -1658 ) was one of the regicides of King Charles I of England .
Tillie Baldwin ( 1888 - 1958 ) , born Anna Mathilda Winger , was an early cowgirl and buckaroo in the United States .
Ethel Maude Proffitt Stephenson ( née Ethel Maude Proffitt ) 1895 - 1982 was an American lawyer who practiced in Okemah and Tulsa specialising in the field of Native American civil rights .
George Robb ( 1 June 1926 -- 25 December 2011 ) was a footballer who played outside left for Tottenham Hotspur and England .
Hjálmar Jónsson ( 29 September 1796 -- 25 July 1875 ) , better known as Bólu - Hjálmar ( after his homestead in Bóla ) , was a 19th - century Icelandic farmer and poet , known for his sharp style and biting wit and for his mastery of the short Icelandic poetic narrative style known as Rímur .
Andrew Macfarlane ( died 1819 ) was an Anglican clergyman who served as a bishop in the Scottish Episcopal Church in the late 18th and early 19th - century .
Yuri Nikolayevich Jobbers ( born on 13 August 1892 - died on 3 April 1969 ) was a Russian teacher and a Catholic convert from Russian Orthodoxy .
Ryan McHenry ( 13 December 1987 -- 2 May 2015 ) was a Scottish film director best known for the film Zombie Musical in which he received a nomination for the Best Director accolade at the 2011 British Academy Scotland New Talent Awards .
Bruce Duncan Guimaraens ( 27 October 1935 -- 22 August 2002 ) was a port wine maker Born in Vila Nova de Gaia , Portugal on 27 October 1935 , Bruce Guimaraens was the great - great - grandson of Manuel Pedro Guimaraens founder of the London house of the famous Fonseca Port firm in 1822 .
Narritjin Maymuru ( died 1981 ) was a Yolngu people artist and activist noted for Bark painting .
Jonas King ( born in Hawley , Massachusetts , 29 July 1792 ; died in Athens , Greece , 22 May 1869 ) was a Congregational clergyman from the United States who worked as a missionary , mainly in Greece .
Otto Michael ( 1859 - 1934 ) was a German explorer , zoologist and entomologist .
Lucien Sabourin ( 1904 - -1987 ) was a French botanist best known for his work with the City of Paris parks department .
Giulio Roma ( 16 September 1584 -- 16 September 1652 ) was an Italian Catholic Cardinal and Bishop of Recanati and Loreto .
Vidyabati Kansakar ( Devanagari : विद्याबति कंसकार ) ( 1906 -- 31 January 1976 ) was a pioneer of nursing in Nepal .
David Alexander Mulholland ( 1938 -- 10 December 2003 ) was a Northern Irish loyalist paramilitary , known to the security forces for his alleged involvement in bombing attacks .
William Conolly ( 9 April 1662 -- 30 October 1729 ) , also known as Speaker Conolly , was an Irish politician , Commissioner of Revenue , lawyer and landowner .
Yu Xiwei 于希谓(1909 - 1980 ) was a Chinese middle - distance runner .
Bobby Ewer ( 2 July 1904 -- 11 March 1995 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Daniel Auster ( Hebrew : דניאל אוסטר‎ ‎ , 7 May 1893 -- 15 January 1963 ) was Mayor of Jerusalem in the final years of Mandatory Palestine , the first Jewish mayor of the city , and the first mayor of Jerusalem after Israeli independence .
Reserve Constable Albert Alexander ( c. 1897 -- 15 March 1941 ) was the fourth patient to be treated with injections of penicillin .
Mary Davys ( 1674?--1732 ) was a novelist and playwright .
Margaret Cecil , Countess of Ranelagh ( 1672/1673 -- 21 February 1728 ) was a British courtier .
Lu Xiangxian ( 陸象先 ) ( 665 - -736 ) , né Lu Jingchu ( 陸景初 ) , formally Duke Wenzhen of Yan ( 兗文貞公 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty and Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Ruizong and Emperor Xuanzong .
Samuel Danforth ( 1626 - -1674 ) was a Puritan minister , preacher , poet , and astronomer , the second pastor of The First Church in Roxbury and an associate of the Rev. John Eliot of Roxbury , Massachusetts , known as the `` Apostle to the Indians . ''
Serafia Fredrika Schaeffer ( 1800 - 1887 ) , known as `` Sheffer 's Madam '' , was a Finnish cunning woman and herbalist .
Takla Maryam ( Ge'ez : ተክለ ማርያም takla māryām `` Plant of Mary , '' Amh . tekle māryām , throne name Hezba Nañ ህዝበ ናኝ hizba nāñ ) was Emperor ( nəgusä nägäst ) ( 1430 - -1433 ) of Ethiopia .
Nicholas of Poland , also known as Nicholas of Montpellier ( Polish : Mikołaj z Polski ) ( b. c. 1235 , Silesia ; d. Kraków , c. 1316 ) , was a medieval Polish - German friar and healer of Silesian origin .
David Richmond ( 1748 - -1818 ) was an American commissioned officer who served in the American Revolutionary War .
Arthur Asahel Shurcliff ( 1870 - -1957 ) was a noted American landscape architect .
Asbjørn Osnes ( 21 April 1932 -- 22 September 2011 ) was a Norwegian ski jumper .
Wadsworth A. Parker ( b. 1864 -- d. 1938 , Petersburg , Virginia ) was an American printer and typeface designer .
Summers Burkhart ( 26 June 1859 -- 14 May 1932 ) was an American lawyer and the United States Attorney for New Mexico from 1913 to 1921 .
Francis Graham Crookshank ( 1873 , Wimbledon -- 27 October 1933 , Wimpole Street ) was a British epidemiologist , and a medical and psychological writer .
Renato De Riva ( 7 May 1937 -- 10 May 1983 ) was an Italian speed skater who was active internationally between 1958 and 1968 .
Thomas Acton ( 1662 -- 21 March 1721 ) , real name Thomas Dupuy , was an English Jesuit .
Matthew Sullivan ( 1868 - -1948 ) was an American architect whose practice specialized in ecclesiastical design .
Festus Walters ( 1849 - -1922 ) was an Ohio jurist and advocate for Gubernatorial judicial independence known for the controversial decision to try an Ohio National Guard commander for murder following the Washington County Courthouse riots of 1895 .
George Maltby ( 1 October 1876 -- 30 July 1924 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Derbyshire in 1905 .
Daif Abdul - kareem Al - Ghazal ( 1976 - -2005 ) was a prominent Libyan journalist and writer who was murdered in Libya in May 2005 .
Jean - Pol Vigneron ( 5 March 1950 - 24 June 2013 ) was a Belgian physics professor .
Theodor Spieker ( 8 August 1823 -- 9 April 1913 ) was a German mathematician , a teacher at a gymnasium in Potsdam .
Ruben Rausing ( 17 June 1895 -- 8 October 1983 ) was the founder of the liquid food packaging company Tetra Pak .
Jean - Pierre - Antoine Rey ( 21 December 1767 - 12 January 1842 ) commanded a famous French infantry regiment during the Napoleonic Wars and became a general officer in 1808 .
Frederico de Freitas ( born Lisbon , 15 November 1902 - died there 12 January 1980 ) was a Portuguese composer , conductor , musicologist and pedagogue .
Bertram Ashburnham , 5th Earl of Ashburnham ( 28 October 1840 -- 15 January 1913 ) was a British peer .
Hugo von Montfort ( 1357 -- 4 April 1423 ) was an Austrian minstrel of the Late Middle Ages .
Óscar Únzaga de la Vega ( 19 April 1916 -- 19 April 1959 ) was a Bolivian political figure and rebel .
Henry George Lamond ( 13 June 1885 -- 12 July 1969 ) was an Australian farmer and writer , notable for his novels about the land , people and animals of outback Queensland .
( George ) Leighton Seager , 1st Baron Leighton of St Mellons CBE ( 11 January 1896 -- 17 October 1963 ) , known as Sir George Leighton Seager , 1st Baronet , from 1952 to 1962 , was a Welsh shipping magnate .
Thomas Touchet - Jesson , 23rd Baron Audley MBE ( 15 September 1913 -- 3 July 1963 ) was born in Herefordshire , England , to Thomas Touchet Tuchet - Jesson and Annie Rosina Hammacott - Osler and educated at Lancing College .
Percy Brooke ( May 1893 -- 1971 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Aberdare Athletic , Accrington Stanley , Stoke , Swindon Town .
Sir Henry Blount ( 1602 - -1682 ) was a 17th - century English landowner , traveller and author .
William B. Pettit ( October 10 , 1825 - 1905 ) was a Virginia lawyer who served a term as president of The Virginia Bar Association , and was a delegate to the Virginia Constitutional Convention of 1901 .
Almahmoud ( 1947 - -1971 ) was an American Thoroughbred racemare that was best known as an influential broodmare who produced Natalma and Cosmah .
Pope Clement IX ( Latin : Clemens IX ; 28 January 1600 -- 9 December 1669 ) , born Giulio Rospigliosi , was Pope from 20 June 1667 to his death in 1669 .
Susan Newell ( 1893 - -1923 ) was the last woman to be hanged in Scotland .
Major Ludwig Albrecht von Rohr ( 1796 - -1815 ) was a Prussian officer during the Napoleonic Wars who was killed during the Waterloo Campaign .
Fernando Manuel de Bustillo Bustamante y Rueda ( died 1719 ) served as the 37th Governor General of Spanish Philippines from 1717 until his death .
Hadamar III of Laber ( ca 1300 -- 1360 ) was one of the Lords of Laber ( now Laaber ) in the Upper Palatinate , and an important courtly poet ( Minnesänger ) .
According to Amnesty International , Thongsouk Saysangkhi died in prison in February 1998 .
Hugh MacColl ( 1831 - -1909 ) was a Scottish mathematician , logician and novelist .
Bagindo Azizchan ( 30 September 1910 -- 19 July 1947 ) , is the Mayor of Padang second after independence , which was inaugurated on August 15 , 1946 replacing Mr. Abubakar Jaar .
Teobaldo II Ordelaffi ( also known as Tebaldo , 1413 - -1425 ) was briefly lord of Forlì from 1422 to 1424 .
William Ellis Tucker ( died 1832 ) was the first person to successfully produce hard paste porcelain for the home market made entirely in the United States of purely domestic materials .
Bojang of Goguryeo ( died 682 ) ( r. 642 - -668 ) was the 28th and last king of Goguryeo the northernmost of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Vinod Mishra ( Hindi : विनोद मिश्रा ; 24 March 1947 -- 18 December 1998 ) was an Indian communist politician .
George Digby , 2nd Earl of Bristol ( bapt . 5 November 1612 -- 20 March 1677 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 until 1641 when he was raised to the House of Lords .
Zuleika Alambert ( Santos , 23 December 1922 - Rio de Janeiro , 27 December 2012 ) was a Brazilian writer , feminist , and politician .
Adam of Usk ( Welsh : Adda o Frynbuga ) ( c. 1352 -- 1430 ) was a Welsh priest , canonist , and late medieval historian and chronicler .
Lloyd Davies ( 23 February 1877 -- 10 October 1957 ) was a Welsh footballer who played in the Football League for Stoke and had a long career in the Southern League with Northampton Town .
Serafino Porrecta ( b. 1536 ; d. at Bologna , 2 January 1614 ) was an Italian Dominican theologian .
Cathal mac Domhnall Ó Conchobair ( died 1324 ) was King of Connacht from 1318 to 1324 .
' Abd al - Hayy ( c. 1374 - Samarkand , 1405 ) was a Persian illustrator and painter .
Stanley Roy Badmin ( 1906 - -1989 ) was an English painter and etcher particularly noted for his book illustrations and landscapes .
Vaidila ( Woidiło , Voydiło , Woydylo ; executed in 1381 ) was a favorite and brother - in - law of Jogaila , Grand Duke of Lithuania .
Otto Muehl ( 16 June 1925 -- 26 May 2013 ) was an Austrian artist , who was known as one of the co - founders as well as a main participant of Viennese Actionism and for founding the Friedrichshof Commune .
Sir Eric Teichman , born Erik Teichmann ( 16 January 1884 -- 3 December 1944 , in Norfolk , England ) was a British diplomat and orientalist .
Sulejman Zalla ( 1892 - -1966 ) was an Albanian teacher , patriot and activist of the Rilindja Kombëtare of the early 20th century .
Sophie d'Artois ( 5 August 1776 -- 5 December 1783 ) was a French princess of the House of Bourbon .
Wilhelm Crisolli ( 20 January 1895 -- 12 September 1944 ) was a German general and member of the Nazi Party in World War II . He was Commander of 13 .
Paul Langerhans ( 25 July 1847 -- 20 July 1888 ) was a German pathologist , physiologist and biologist .
Rev. Jerome Alley ( 1760 - -1826 ) was an Irish poet and author .
Rokneddin Mokhtari ( 1887 - -1970 ) was an Iranian musician and violinist .
Mahbub Alam Chashi ( Bengali : মাহবুব আলম চাষী ) ( 1927 - -1983 ) was a renowned public official and social worker from Bangladesh .
Charles Magnus ( 16 March 1826 - 3 May 1900 ) was a printing entrepreneur , whose business was based in New York , NY .
Clive Hale ( 1937 -- 5 June 2005 ) was an Australian television news and current affairs presenter on the Australian Broadcasting Corporation ( ABC ) for 38 years .
Gu Hongzhong ( simplified Chinese : 顾闳中 ; traditional Chinese : 顧閎中 ; pinyin : Gù Hóngzhōng ; 937 - -975 ) was a Chinese painter during the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period of Chinese history .
Philipp Jarnach ( 26 July 1892 -- 17 December 1982 ) was a composer of modern music .
Eduardo Prieto ( 15 April 1912 -- 8 July 2003 ) was a Mexican fencer and sailor .
Clara Pontoppidan ( 23 April 1883 -- 22 January 1975 ) , also known as Clara Wieth , was a Danish actress .
Aref El Rayess ( or Aref Rayess ) ( 1928 in Aley , Lebanon -- 2005 ) was a Lebanese painter .
Mohammad Daoud Oudeh ( Arabic : محمد داود عودة‎ ) , commonly known by his nom de guerre Abu Daoud or Abu Dawud ( Arabic : أبو داود‎ ) 1937 , -- 3 July 2010 ) was a Palestinian known as the planner , architect and mastermind of the Munich massacre .
Christina Onassis ( Greek : Χριστίνα Ωνάση ; 11 December 1950 -- 19 November 1988 ) was an American - born Greek / Argentine businesswoman , socialite , and heiress to the Onassis fortune .
Peter Racine Fricker ( 5 September 1920 -- 1 February 1990 ) was an English composer who lived in the US for the last thirty years of his life .
Sir Edgar Bonham - Carter , KCMG , CIE ( 2 April 1870 -- 24 April 1956 ) was a British barrister and administrator in the Sudan and Iraq .
Carl - August Petersen ( 26 May 1912 -- 23 November 1980 ) was a highly decorated Major in the Luftwaffe .
Czesław Młot - Fijałkowski ( 1892 - -1944 ) was a Polish military officer and a brigadier general of the Polish Army .
Dr. Frederic John Poynton M.D. , F.R.C.P. ( 26 June 1869 -- 29 October 1943 ) was an English physician who studied rheumatism in children while practising at Great Ormond Street Hospital and University College Hospital .
Clive Scott ( 24 February 1945 -- 10 May 2009 ) was a keyboard player of the British 1970s pop / rock group , Jigsaw , as well as the composer of most of the group 's recordings , together with the singer , Des Dyer .
Oğuz Yorulmaz ( - May 2005 ) was a Turkish policeman convicted of involvement in the Susurluk scandal ; he was a bodyguard of Sedat Bucak .
Samuel Goodenough ( 1743 -- 12 August 1827 ) was the Bishop of Carlisle from 1808 until his death in 1827 , and an amateur botanist and collector .
Fred Hawking ( 22 September 1909 -- 8 September 1988 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the VFL during the 1930s .
( Joseph ) Rupert Balfe ( 9 March 1890 -- 25 April 1915 ) was an Australian rules footballer .
Roger Brett Kebble ( 19 February 1964 -- 27 September 2005 ) was a South African mining magnate with close links to factions in the ruling political party , the African National Congress .
Emile Riachi ( November 2 , 1926 -- 15 June 2014 ) was a renowned orthopaedic surgeon in Lebanon .
Debbie Purdy ( 4 May 1963 -- 23 December 2014 ) was a British music journalist and political activist from Bradford , West Yorkshire , with primary progressive multiple sclerosis , notable for her challenge to the law in England and Wales as relates to assisted suicide .
Beryl Cook , OBE ( 10 September 1926 -- 28 May 2008 ) was an English artist best known for her original and instantly recognisable paintings .
Åke Strömmer ( born 10 June 1936 in Härnösand , died 22 February 2005 ) was a Swedish sports journalist , radio presenter and television host .
Jan Standonck ( or Jean Standonk ; 16 August 1453 -- 5 February 1504 ) was a Flemish priest , Scholastic , and reformer .
Braja Sundar Mitra ( Bengali : ব্রজ সুন্দর মিত্র Brojo Shundor Mitro ) ( 1227 - 1282 Bengali Era ) , son of Bhabani Prasad Mitra , was founder of Dhaka Brahmo Samaj .
Leo J. Volpe ( 1916 - -13 April 2000 ) was a draft resister and conscientious objector as a Jehovah 's Witness during World War II . In the Month of February 1940 Leo Volpe begin reading the first of a set of three books titled Vindication .
Johannes Adam Simon Oertel ( born Fürth , Bavaria , 3 November 1823 ; died 9 December 1909 ) was a German - American Episcopal clergyman and artist .
Verita Bouvaire - Thompson ( b.1918 , d. 2011 ) was an American actress turned hairdresser best known for her 14-year reputed affair with actor Humphrey Bogart .
Erzhu Zhao ( 爾朱兆 ) ( died 533 ) , courtesy name Wanren ( 萬仁 ) , was a general of the Chinese / Xianbei dynasty Northern Wei .
Kristin Brooks Rossell ( 16 November 1969 -- 7 April 1998 ) became the face of the National Hopeline Network after she committed suicide after suffering from postpartum depression .
John Wheeler Bunton ( 22 February 1807 -- 24 August 1879 ) was a Texas settler and signer of the Texas Declaration of Independence ( 1836 ) , which declared independence from Mexico .
Bhai Lal Mohammad Amritsari ( died 1962 ) was a singer of the Kapurthala Gharana trained in the Gwalior style of singing .
Julia Pirotte ( née Diament ; 1 January 1908 -- 25 July 2000 ) was a photojournalist known for her work in Marseille during the Second World War when she documented the French Resistance , and for photographs taken in the aftermath of the Kielce Pogrom of 1946 .
Charlotta Aurora De Geer later Gyldenstolpe and Wetterstedt ( 1779 - -1834 ) , was a Swedish salonist , lady - in - waiting and noble .
Air Vice - Marshal Sir Arthur Vyell Vyvyan KCB DSO ( 12 March 1875 -- 30 September 1935 ) , usually given as Sir Vyell Vyvyan , was an officer in the Royal Navy in the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Archbishop Gaetano Alibrandi ( 14 January 1914 -- 3 July 2003 ) of the Roman Catholic Church was a senior papal diplomat and former Personal Secretary to Giovanni Battista Cardinal Montini ( later Pope Paul VI ) .
Daniel Pedreira Senna Pellegrine ( 30 October 1992 -- 7 July 2013 ) , better known by his stage name MC Daleste was a Brazilian funk paulista singer , songwriter and rapper .
Lewis Radcliffe ( 1880 - 1950 ) was a naturalist , malacologist , and ichthyologist .
Martin Friedrich Rudolf von Delbrück ( 16 April 1817 -- 1 February 1903 ) was a Prussian statesman at the time of Otto von Bismarck .
José de Jesus Medrano , better known as Chuchín , was a Mexican clown and star attraction of many circuses in Mexico from the late 1960s to 1984 , when he died while on tour in Africa .
Charles Brandon , 1st Duke of Suffolk , 1st Viscount Lisle , KG ( c.1484 -- 22 August 1545 ) was the son of Sir William Brandon and Elizabeth Bruyn .
Lojze Zupanc ( 21 September 1906 -- 2 June 1973 ) was a Slovene writer , poet , playwright and journalist best known for his short stories based on folktales and other traditional stories .
Fred Lowen AM ( 1919 - -2005 ) , born Fritz Karl Heinz Lowenstein , was a German - Australian designer and an inductee into the Design Institute of Australia Hall of Fame .
Hakija Turajlić ( 1936 -- 8 January 1993 ) was a Bosniak politician , economist and businessman who served as the Deputy Prime Minister of Bosnia and Herzegovina until he was murdered in 1993 .
Bill Burnett was born in Koffiefontein on 31 May 1917 and died in Grahamstown , South Africa on 23 August 1994 was archbishop of Cape Town from 1974 to 1981 .
William Joseph Chamberlain ( died 1945 ) was an English journalist and pacifist .
Gyeon Hwon ( 867 - 27 September 936 , reigned 892 - 935 ) was the king and founder of Hubaekje , one of the Later Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Robert Noel Douglas ( Norwood Green , Middlesex 9 November 1868 - Colyton , Devon 27 February 1957 ) was an English cricketer teacher , and priest .
Giovanni Angelo Testagrossa ( 9 April 1470 -- December 1530 ) was an Italian lutenist and singer .
Charles George Male ( 8 May 1910 -- 19 February 1998 ) was an English footballer .
John William Cameron ( 2 October 1841 - 28 December 1896 ) was an English brewer who owned Camerons Brewery of Hartlepool , County Durham .
Bob Block ( 20 July 1921 -- 17 April 2011 ) was a British radio , television and film comedy scriptwriter .
Agar Wynne ( 15 July 1850 -- 12 May 1934 ) was an Australian politician .
Sir Arnold Savage II ( ca . 1382 -- 1420 ) , of Bobbing , Kent , was an English politician .
Brigadier Daniel Austin died on 29 December 2013 .
David Godwin Burchell BEM ( 23 September 1924 -- 20 September 2009 ) was a South Australian business man , a recreational scuba diver and a football administrator .
Henry Stephen Kemble ( 15 September 1789 -- 22 June 1836 ) was a British actor and son of Stephen Kemble .
Karl Höchberg ( 8 September 1853 -- 21 June 1885 ) was a German social - reformist writer , publisher and economist , who acted under the pseudonyms Dr. Ludwig Richter e R.F. Seifert .
Hugh Willoughby , 12th Baron Willoughby of Parham ( c.1637 - -1712 ) was an English peer of the House of Lords .
Audvar Os ( 8 September 1920 -- 25 June 2014 ) was a Norwegian barrister and civil servant .
Alonzo Conant ( 8 October 1914 - 4 January 1962 ) was a lawyer and political activist from Maine .
Chrysaphius ( Greek : Χρυσάφιος ) was a eunuch at the Eastern Roman court , who became the chief minister of Theodosius II ( r. 408 - -450 ) .
Sir William Llewelyn Davies ( born William Davies , and adding `` Llewelyn '' after marrying Gwen Llewelyn ) ( 11 October 1887 -- 11 November 1952 ) was chief librarian of the National Library of Wales , Aberystwyth from 1930 until his death .
Brahma Pala ( 900 - 920 ) was founder of Pala Dynasty ( 900 - -1100 ) of Kamarupa Kingdom .
Tomaso Porcacchi Castilione ( 1530 - -1585 ) was an author and cartographer .
Dr. Vala Chakradhar Rao ( 28 March 1928 -- 27 September 1991 ) was a doctor and politician .
Marie Howet ( 24 March 1897 -- 24 March 1984 ) was a Belgian expressionist painter and illustrator .
Giorgio Matteo Aicardi ( 18 September 1891 -- 30 December 1984 ) was an Italian painter , who also specialised in drawings , frescos , restorations and illustrations .
Blessed Conor O'Devany ( c. 1532 -- 1 ( O.S.)/11 ( N.S. ) February 1612 ; Cornelius O'Devany , Irish : Concobhar Ó Duibheannaigh ) was an Irish Roman Catholic bishop and martyr .
Vetle Vislie ( 21 September 1858 -- 7 February 1933 ) was a Norwegian educationalist and writer .
Hickman Price Jr. , ( 1911 - -1989 ) was an assistant secretary in the United States Department of Commerce and a business executive .
Samuel Larsson Stjerneld ( 1637 - -1716 ) was son of Lars Gustafsson Vasa and Brita Törnros .
Herbert Standing ( 13 November 1846 -- 5 December 1923 ) was a British stage and screen actor and the patriarch of the Standing family of actors .
Ramón Atiles y Pérez ( 1804 - -1875 ) , who was born in Ponce , Puerto Rico , was a notable painter known for his miniature portraits of bourgeois sitters .
Teodor Filipović ( 1778 - -1807 ) , Serbian writer , jurist and educator , is also known by his pseudonym Božidar Grujović .
David Pacher ( 5 September 1816 , Obervellach -- 29 May 1902 , Obervellach ) was an Austrian priest and botanist .
Joseph Marcoux ( 16 March 1791 -- 29 May 1855 ) was a Canadian Catholic missionary among the Iroquois .
Henry Lane Eno was born in New York City on July 8 , 1871 ; he died at Montacute House , Somerset , on September 28 , 1928 .
Ida Bagus Mantra ( 8 May 1928 - 10 July 1995 ) was the Governor of Bali from 1978 to 1988 .
Togha Temür ( died late 1353 ) , also known as Taghaytimur , was a claimant to the throne of the Ilkhanate in the mid-14th century .
Franc Gubenšek ( 31 October 1937 -- 17 August 2010 ) was a Slovene biochemist and academic , notable for his work on toxins in snake venom .
Herman Husband ( 1724 - -1795 ) , also known as Harmon Husband , was a farmer , radical , pamphleteer , and preacher .
P. C. Sorcar ( Bengali : পি সি সরকার ) ( 23 February 1913 -- 6 January 1971 ) was the stage name of Protul Chandra Sorcar ( Bengali : প্রতুলচন্দ্র সরকার ) , a famous magician .
Arthur Jones , pen name Tristan Jones ( 8 May 1929 -- 21 June 1995 ) was a British mariner and author .
Carl Jularbo , well known as Calle Jularbo and born as Karl Karlsson ( 6 June 1893 - 13 February 1966 ) was the most famous Swedish accordionist of his time .
Otto Porsch 12 September 1875 -- 2 January 1959 ) was an Austrian biologist .
William Brouncker , 2nd Viscount Brouncker , PRS ( 1620 -- 5 April 1684 ) was an English mathematician who introduced Brouncker 's formula , and was the first President of the Royal Society .
Captain Harold Thomas Cawley ( 12 June 1878 -- 23 September 1915 ) was a British barrister , Liberal Party politician and soldier .
Andrea Ossoinack ( 1876 - 1965 ) was a businessman and politician who became notable in the process of creating the Free State of Fiume .
Townsend Cromwell ( November 3 , 1922 -- June 2 , 1958 ) was an oceanographer who discovered the Cromwell current whilst researching drifting in the equatorial region of the Pacific Ocean .
Tato ( died 510 ) was an early 6th century king of the Lombards .
Dietmar von Aist ( c. 1115 -- c. 1171 ) was a Minnesinger from a baronial family in the Duchy of Austria , whose work is representative of the lyric poetry in the Danube region .
Grace Livingston Hill ( April 16 , 1865 -- 1947 ) was an early 20th - century novelist and wrote both under her real name and the pseudonym Marcia Macdonald .
Joseph Dutton ( born 27 April 1843 , Stowe , Vermont -- died on 26 March 1931 , Honolulu , Hawaii ) , was a Civil War veteran , Union Army Lieutenant , who converted to Catholicism and later worked as a missionary with Father Damien .
Johan Fredrik Eykman or Johann Frederik Eijkman ( 19 January 1851 -- 7 January 1915 ) was a Dutch chemist .
Jules Richomme ( 9 September 1818 -- 16 October 1903 ) was a French portrait , landscape , genre and history painter .
Polymelus ( 1902 - -1924 ) was a British Thoroughbred racehorse who was the leading sire of racehorses in Great Britain and Ireland for five years ( 1914 , 1915 , 1916 , 1920 , 1921 ) .
James Batchelder ( 1830 - -1854 ) was the second United States Marshal to be killed in the line of duty .
Robbie France ( 5 December 1959 -- 14 January 2012 ) was an English drummer , producer , arranger , journalist , music educator , and broadcaster .
Yujiulü Hulü ( Chinese : 郁久閭斛律 ; pinyin : Yùjiǔlǘ Húlǜ ) ( died 414 ) was an early 5th century Aikugai Khan ( 藹苦蓋可汗 ) ( ruler ) of the Rouran , a confederation of nomadic tribes in Mongolia .
McKinley Burnett ( 1897 - 1968 ) played a pivotal role in the landmark Brown v. Board of Education of Topeka school desegregation case as President of the Topeka NAACP by recruiting 13 Topeka families to participate in the court action .
Bryan Patrick Beirne ( 22 January 1918 -- 31 March 1998 ) was an Irish entomologist who emigrated to Canada in 1949 .
Rudolf Sanzin ( 4 June 1874 - 2 June 1922 ) was an Austrian engineer and locomotive designer .
Pieter Claesz ( c. 1597 - -1 January 1660 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter of still lifes .
Daham Miro ( Kurdish : Deham Mîro ; Arabic : دهام ميرو ) ( January 1921-November 2010 ) was a Kurdish political leader and former chairman of the Kurdistan Democratic Party of Syria ( KDPS ) .
Aurora Miranda da Cunha Richaid ( 20 April 1915 -- 22 December 2005 ) was a Brazilian entertainer .
Joseph Werner ( 22 June 1637 -- 21 September 1710 ) , known as the Younger to distinguish him from his painter father of the same name , was a Swiss painter , known for miniatures .
Edward Cresset ( 1910 - -2001 ) was a Dean of Hereford and a Bishop of Llandaff .
Euphémie Daguilh ( died in Les Cayes , Haiti , 1834 ) , was a Haitian composer and choreographer , royal mistress of emperor Jean - Jacques Dessalines and famed for her fearless care of the wounded during the campaign of 1805 .
Angadrisma ( Angadrême , Angadresima , Angadreme , Angradesma , Andragasyna ) ( d. ca . 695 ) was a seventh - century abbess and saint .
Francis Cuggy ( 16 June 1889 -- 27 March 1965 ) was an English footballer who played at right half .
Morris Schaff ( 1840 - -1929 ) , was a native of Etna Township , Ohio , USA .
Sophie Elisabeth of Schleswig - Holstein - Sonderburg - Wiesenburg ( 4 May 1653 - 19 August 1684 ) , was a German noblewoman member of the House of Oldenburg and by marriage Duchess of Saxe - Zeitz .
George Edward Dering ( 1831 - -1911 ) was a British inventor and eccentric .
Henry FitzAlan , 19th Earl of Arundel KG ( 23 April 1512 -- 24 February 1580 ) was an English nobleman , who over his long life assumed a prominent place at the court of all the later Tudor sovereigns , probably the only person to do so .
Colette Ritz , real name Benitte Colette ( Paris , 8 May 1932 - Proisy , 9 September 2007 ) was a French pop singer of the 1960s .
Harold Gresley ( 1892 - 1967 ) was a British artist , following his father and grandfather .
Alexander Sahinian ( Armenian : Ալեքսանդր Սահինյան ; 1910 - -1982 ) was a Soviet Armenian architectural historian , who headed the Architecture Department of the Institute of Arts of the Armenian Academy of Sciences between 1958 and 1982 .
Luigi Bellardi ( 18 May 1818 -- 17 September 1889 ) was an Italian malacologist and entomologist who specialised in Diptera .
Armin Schlieps ( 1931 - -2005 ) , son of George Schlieps , was an illustrious bow maker ( Archetier ) as well as a violin maker ( Luthier ) .
John II , Duke of Mecklenburg - Stargard ( before 1370 - 6 July/9 October 1416 ) was a titular Duke of Mecklenburg .
Thomas Klestil ( 4 November 1932 -- 6 July 2004 ) was an Austrian diplomat and politician .
Jan Walenty Węgierski ( 1755 - -1796 ) , of Wieniawa Coat of Arms , was a Deputy Chancellor ( podkanclerz ) and Chamberlain of last king of Poland , Stanisław August Poniatowski .
Austin Leslie Farnen ( better known as Les Farnen , 17 September 1919 -- January 1985 ) was an English professional footballer .
Christian Swartz ( June 15 , 1846 -- 1932 ) was a two - term mayor of South Norwalk , Connecticut , United States in 1880 , and 1882 .
Thomas Francis Dillon Croker FSA FRGS ( 1831 - -1912 ) was a British antiquary and poet .
Laurence Gross ( 1931 - 2003 ) was a television and radio broadcaster in San Diego .
Joseph Liberman ( 1917 , Henichesk -- August 1941 , Russian : Иосиф Меерович Либерман ) was a Soviet mathematician , a student of Aleksandrov , best known for Liberman 's lemma .
Ramachandra Raya ( 1422 CE ) was an emperor of the Vijayanagara Empire from the Sangama Dynasty .
Saw Bwe Hmu ( Burmese : စောဘွဲ့မှူး died 24 July 1993 ) was a co - founder and the bandleader of the Burmese band Iron Cross and a well known songwriter .
Radu Irimescu ( December 9 , 1890 -- May 1975 ) was a Romanian businessman , politician , and diplomat .
Emil Veesenmeyer ( 1857 -- 1944 ) was a German theologian , minister of the Bergkirche in Wiesbaden , the capital of Hesse , and later a dean .
James Frye ( b. in Andover , Massachusetts , in 1709 ; d. 8 January 1776 ) was a colonial soldier .
Sima Yong ( 司馬顒 ) ( died 306 ) , courtesy name Wenzai ( 文載 ) , was a Jin Dynasty ( 265 - 420 ) imperial prince and briefly a regent for Emperor Hui .
Robert John Halliburton ( 23 March 1935 -- 26 September 2004 ) was an English priest and theologian within the Church of England , who served as a Canon and Chancellor of St Paul 's Cathedral between 1989 and 2003 .
Ruth Spalding ( 30 November 1913 -- 26 February 2009 ) was an actor , director and author .
Geoffrey Font , Irish centenarian , ( 1709 - -1814 ) According to James Hardiman , Font 's family - one of the Tribes of Galway - `` settled in Galway in the beginning of the fifteenth century , they sprung from an ancient English family of Leicestershire '' ( p. 13 ) .
Oberst Helmut Lent ( 13 June 1918 -- 7 October 1944 ) was a German night - fighter ace in World War II . Lent shot down 110 aircraft , 102 of them at night , far more than the minimum of five enemy aircraft required for the title of `` ace '' .
Johann Wilhelm Adolf Hansemann ( 14 May 1784 , Finkenwerder Hamburg-- 26 July 1862 , Diepholz ) was a German entomologist and insect dealer .
Ma Sui ( 馬燧 ) ( 726 -- September 4 , 795 ) , courtesy name Xunmei ( 洵美 ) , formally Prince Zhuangwu of Beiping ( 北平莊武王 ) , was a Chinese general who served during the Tang dynasty .

Christopher Henrik Holfeldt Tostrup ( born 20 September 1804 in Hjelmeland , died 17 October 1881 in Christiania ) was a Norwegian timber merchant and land - owner .
Claudio Angelini ( 29 March 1943 -- 2 June 2015 ) was president of the Dante Alighieri Society in New York , U.S. political correspondent for RAI , the Italian national television network and was President Emeritus of RAI Corporation .
Peter Sedgwick ( 1934 - -1983 ) was a translator of Victor Serge , author of a number of books including PsychoPolitics and a revolutionary socialist activist .
José Gerson da Cunha ( 2 February 1844 -- 3 August 1900 ) was a Goan physician who achieved international renown as an orientalist , historian , linguist and numismatist .
Stanisław Rehman ( 1838 - -1899 ) , was a city councillor in Kraków , Poland .
William Mackintire Salter ( 1853 - -1931 ) was the author of several books on philosophy and a critical and enduring major classic on Nietzsche .
Kostas Lazaridis ( 1900 - -1943 ) was a famous Greek trade unionist .
John Gordon , 1st Viscount of Kenmure ( 1599 - -1634 ) was a Scottish nobleman , renowned Presbyterian , and founder of the town of New Galloway .
Gilbert de Clare , 8th Earl of Gloucester , 7th Earl of Hertford , 10th Lord of Clare , 5th Lord of Glamorgan ( c. 10 May 1291 -- 24 June 1314 ) was an English nobleman and a military commander in the Scottish Wars .
Victor - Amédée Lebesgue , sometimes written Le Besgue , ( 2 October 1791 , Grandvilliers ( Oise ) -- 10 June 1875 , Bordeaux ( Gironde ) ) was a mathematician working on number theory .
Federico José María Ronstadt ( 1868 - 1954 ) was a business and cultural leader in Tucson , Arizona , USA , in the early 20th century .
Thomas P. Rona ( 1923 - -1997 ) was a 1980s era science advisor to the Defense Department and the White House under Presidents Reagan and Bush .
Sir Thomas Whorwood ( 1544 - -1616 ) was a Staffordshire landowner , Member of the English Parliament and High Sheriff of Staffordshire .
On 17 December 1917 , in the early hours , Ernst Leman was shot in the head .
Lars Magnus Ericsson ( 5 May 1846 -- 17 December 1926 ) was a Swedish inventor , entrepreneur and founder of telephone equipment manufacturer Ericsson ( incorporated as Telefonaktiebolaget LM Ericsson ) .
Norman Cameron ( 1905 - -1953 ) was a Scottish poet , distantly related to Thomas Babington , Lord Macaulay who , between the two world wars , associated on Majorca with Robert Graves and Laura Riding .
Dan Patch lived in Minnesota from 1902 until his death on 11 July 1916 .
Paul Thiene ( 1880 - -1971 ) was a German - born American landscape architect .
Ayhan Şahenk ( 11 June 1929 , Niğde -- 1 April 2001 , İstanbul ) founder of Doğuş Holding , Turkish businessman .
Albert II , Count of Hoya ( 1526 -- 18 March 1563 ) was the ruling Count of Hoya from 1545 until his death .
Colin Ireland ( 16 March 1954 -- 21 February 2012 ) was a British serial killer known as the Gay Slayer because his victims were homosexual men .
Sir William Bellingham , 1st Baronet ( c. 1756 -- 27 October 1826 ) was an Irish - born British politician and the controller of the storekeepers ' accounts for the Royal Navy .
Lord William Campbell ( ca . 1731 -- 4 September 1778 ) was from a Scottish family loyal to the British Crown .
Muiris Ó Rócháin ( Dingle , 1944 -- Milltown Malbay , 17 October 2011 ) was a teacher , director of the Willie Clancy Summer School , president of Oireachtas na Gaeilge and folk collector .
Julius Nicolaysen ( 31 July 1831 -- 25 December 1909 ) was a Norwegian professor of medicine .
Gwilym Ellis Lane Owen ( 18 May 1922 -- 10 July 1982 ) , who published as G. E. L. Owen , was a Welsh philosopher , concerned with the history of Ancient Greek philosophy .
Yizhar Harari ( Hebrew : יזהר הררי‎ , 16 July 1908 -- 1 February 1978 ) was a Zionist activist and Israeli politician .
Proculus ( died c. 281 ) was a Roman usurper , one of the `` minor pretenders '' according to Historia Augusta ; he took the purple against Emperor Probus in 280 .
Dr. Raymond McClean ( c. 1932 -- 29 January 2011 ) was an Irish nationalist politician and physician .
Alexander Malcolm Jacob ( 1849 in Izmir , Turkey -- 1921 ) was a diamond and gemstone trader in Shimla .
Louis Leo Snyder ( 4 July 1907 -- 25 November 1993 ) was an American - born German scholar who witnessed the Nazi mass meetings and wrote about them in Hitlerism :
Irving Underhill ( 1872 - -1960 ) was one of the most notable commercial photographers in New York City during the first half of the 20th century .
Julius Klengel ( 24 September 1859 -- 27 October 1933 ) was a German cellist who is most famous for his etudes and solo pieces written for the instrument .
Gallus Guggumos , probably Guggenmoos or Guggenmoser , ( c. 1590 -- c. 1666 ) was a German composer .
Michel de Sèvre or de Seurre ( active 1539 - -1593 ) , Knight of St John , was a French courtier and diplomat , Grand Master of the Order of Saint Lazarus 1564 - -1578 and 1586 - -1593 .
Jagadhekamalla III ( r. 1164 - -1183 CE ) succeeded Tailapa III to the highly diminished Western Chalukya empire .
John Thomson Mason ( 15 March 1765 -- 10 December 1824 ) was an American jurist and Attorney General of Maryland in 1806 .
Eve Garnett ( 9 January 1900 -- 5 April 1991 ) was an English writer and illustrator .
Blessed Pietro Pettinaio ( c. 1189 - 4 December 1289 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic who worked as a comb - maker .
Radamés Gnattali ( 27 January 1906 -- 3 February 1988 ) was a Brazilian composer of both classical and popular music , as well as a conductor , orchestrator , and arranger .
John Joseph Saunders ( 17 June 1910 -- 25 November 1972 ) was a British historian whose work focused on medieval Islamic and Asian history .
Peder Hjermann ( 1 December 1754 -- 25 December 1834 ) was a farmer and elected official who served as a representative at the Norwegian Constitutional Assembly .
Gerald Howat ( 12 June 1928 -- 10 October 2007 ) , born Gerald Malcolm David Howat , was a British writer on cricket , a historian and a schoolmaster .
Martín Casimiro Martínez Fagalde , usually known as Martín C. Martínez ( 22 February 1859 - 21 January 1946 ) was a Uruguayan lawyer and politician .
John Newdigate ( 1600 - 29 November 1642 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1628 to 1629 .
Gnaeus Cornelius Lentulus Augur ( c. 54 BC -- 25 AD ) was a politician and general of the early Roman Empire , who became consul in 14 BC . Enormously wealthy , he was reputedly forced by the emperor Tiberius to commit suicide in 25 AD .
Major General Liam Tobin ( born William Joseph Tobin ; 1895 - 30 April 1963 ) was an officer in the Irish Army and the instigator of an Army Mutiny in March 1924 .
Harald Julius von Bosse ( 1812 - -1894 ; Гаральд Юлиус Боссе ) was a 19th - century architect and painter .
Brigitte Varangot ( 1 May 1940 -- 12 October 2007 ) was a French amateur golfer .
Nat Riddles ( 4 February 1952 -- 11 August 1991 ) was a blues harmonica player who played an important role in the New York blues scene during the late 1970s to mid-1980s .
Yeruham Meshel ( Hebrew : ירוחם משל‎‎ , born 24 November 1912 , died 27 November 2002 ) was an Israeli union leader and politician who served as head of the Histadrut from 1973 until 1984 , and as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment between 1977 and 1984 .
Evarts Boutell Greene ( 1870 - -1947 ) was an American historian , born in Kobe , Japan , where his parents were missionaries .
Hans Wendlandt ( 18 January 1918 - 20 February 1978 ) is a German former football player and manager .
Elihu Phinney ( 1756 - -1813 ) was the first printer in Cooperstown , New York .
Grgur Branković ( 1415 -- 16 October 1459 ) was a 15th - century Serbian nobleman .
Antipope Paschal III ( or Paschal III ) was Antipope from 1164 to 20 September 1168 .
Jacques Gilles Henri Goguet ( 11 March 1767 -- 21 April 1794 ) rose to command a French division during the French Revolutionary Wars before he was assassinated by his own soldiers after a defeat .
Sir James Alfred Jacoby ( 1852 - -1909 ) was a Nottingham lace manufacturer and Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1885 to 1909 .
Colonel Sir Edward Rossiter ( 1618 - -1669 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1646 and 1660 .
Mary Dendy ( 28 January 1855 - 9 May 1933 ) was a promoter of residential schools for mentally handicapped people , i.e. institutionalisation .
Cyril Andresen ( 1929 -- 1977 ) was a Danish competitive sailor and Olympic medalist .
Daniel Featley , also called Fairclough and sometimes called Richard Fairclough / Featley ( 15 March 1582 -- 17 April 1645 ) , was an English theologian and controversialist .
Maria Antonietta Beluzzi ( 26 July 1930 -- 9 August 1997 ) was an Italian actress who appeared in a number of films in her native country .
Euphemia Stewart , Countess of Strathearn ( died c. 1434 ) was a medieval Scottish noblewoman , the daughter of David Stewart , Earl Palatine of Strathearn and Caithness .
Guy Carleton Phinney ( 1851 - -1893 ) was a real estate developer in Seattle .
Richard Baynard ( ca . 1371 - -7 January 1434 ) was an English administrator , MP and Speaker of the House of Commons of England in 1421 .
Alexandre Denguet Atiki ( 1937 ? -- 30 January 2013 ) was a Congolese politician .
Justice T Paramasiva Iyer ( 1863 - -1943 ) was an Indian vedic scholar , writer and a District and Sessions Judge of Bangalore during the period of Maharaja Chamarajendra Wadiyar X and later went on to become the Chief Justice of the Mysore High Court .
István Bató ( 1812 - -1890 ) was a prominent citizen of the Northern Hungarian city of Miskolc in the 19th century .
Abraham Chazan ( 1849 -- 1917 ) was a rabbi and key figure in the transmission of Breslover Hasidut at the turn of the 20th century .
Friedrich - Wilhelm von Chappuis ( 13 September 1886 -- 27 August 1942 ) was a General der Infanterie who commanded the XXXVIII .
Ivar Huitfeldt ( 5 December 1665 -- 4 October 1710 ) was a Dano - Norwegian naval officer who was killed in action , when he commanded the ship Dannebroge during Great Northern War 1700 - -1721 .
Gao Xu ( Chinese : 高旭 ; pinyin : Gāo Xù ; Wade -- Giles : Kao Hsü / Kao Hsu ; 1877－1925 ) , was a Chinese poet , writer , revolutionary , political activist .
David Mannes ( 16 February 1866 -- 25 April 1959 ) was an American violinist , conductor , educator , and community organizer .
Horace Pitt - Rivers , 6th Baron Rivers ( 12 April 1814 -- 3 March 1880 ) , known as Horace Beckford until 1828 and Hon . Horace Pitt from 1828 until 1867 , was a British peer and army officer .
Ricardo Sepúlveda ( 19 May 1941 -- 3 February 2014 ) was a Chilean football ( soccer ) manager and player .
Cassian Sakowicz , also known as Kasjan Sakowicz , ( born 1578 in Podteliszu near Lubaczów , d. 1647 in Krakow ) was an Orthodox activist and , later , a Catholic theologian , writer , and polemicist .
Alfred Meeson ( 1808 -- 12 January 1885 ) was a British architect and surveyor .
John T. Power ( 1883 -- 1 February 1982 ) was an Irish hurler who played as a goalkeeper for the Kilkenny senior team .
Pedro Ignacio de Castro Barros ( 31 July 1777 -- 7 April 1849 ) was an Argentine statesman and priest .
Kristine Miller ( June 13 , 1925 -- 2015 ) was an American film actress , known for her appearances in film noir and Westerns .
Stephen Codman ( c. 1796 -- 6 October 1852 ) was a Canadian composer of English descent .
Cal Chamberlain ( April 21 , 1968 -- c. July 25 , 2008 ) , born Mark Chamberlain , was an artist and Internet pioneer based out of New York City .
Jim McCoy ( 29 August 1875 -- 8 February 1913 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Gualberto José Antonio Rodríguez Larreta Ferreira ( 14 December 1922 -- 19 August 2015 ) , better known as Antonio Larreta or Taco Larreta , was a Uruguayan writer , critic and actor .
Avraham Tiar ( Hebrew : אברהם טיאר‎‎ 29 January 1924 -- 25 April 2011 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Herut , Gahal and the Free Centre between 1961 and 1969 .
Sir Edward Morgan , 1st Baronet of Llantarnam ( died 24 June 1653 ) was a Roman Catholic supporter of Charles I during the Bishops ' War and the English Civil War .
Josef Erber ( birth name : Josef Houstek ) ( 16 October 1897 in Ottendorf -- 1987 ) was an SS - Oberscharführer at Auschwitz concentration camp .
Corrado Bafile ( 4 July 1903 -- 3 February 2005 ) was an Italian Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church who served as Prefect of the Congregation for the Causes of Saints from 1975 to 1980 , and was elevated to the cardinalate in 1976 .
Iago ab Idwal was a King of Gwynedd ( r. 950 -- 979 ) and possibly Powys .
Oberleutnant zur See Reinhold Saltzwedel ( 23 November 1889 -- 2 December 1917 ) was a successful and highly decorated German U - boat commander in the Kaiserliche Marine during World War I. Saltzwedel sank a total of 111 merchant vessels for 170,526 gross register tons ( GRT ) .
Jean - Baptiste Stahl ( German : Johann Baptist Stahl ) ( 20 June 1869 -- 31 January 1932 ) was the inventor and designer of the Phanolith .
Amrit Keshav Nayak ( 1877 -- 18 July 1907 ) was a theatre actor , director of Parsi theatre , lyricist and Gujarati author .
Gertrude of Sulzbach ( German : Gertrud von Sulzbach ; c. 1110 -- 14 April 1146 ) was Queen consort of Germany from 1138 until her death , as second wife of the Hohenstaufen king Conrad III .
Julio César Grauert ( 1902 - -1933 ) was a Uruguayan journalist and political figure .
Christian Friedrich von Kahlbutz ( 1651 in Kampehl , Brandenburg -- 1702 in Kampehl ) was a German knight , who is today most famous because of the state of preservation of his body ; no noticeable mummification process was used upon his death .
Raj Singh I ( 24 September 1629 - 22 October 1680 ) , was the Maharana of Mewar Kingdom ( r. 1652 - 1680 ) .
Werner Streib ( 13 June 1911 -- 15 June 1986 ) was a German Luftwaffe fighter ace during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves and Swords ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub und Schwertern ) .
Richard Bingham , 2nd Earl of Lucan ( 4 December 1764 -- 30 June 1839 ) , styled The Honourable from 1776 to 1795 and subsequently Lord Bingham until 1799 , was an Irish peer and Tory politician .
William B. Van Ingen ( 1858 - -1955 ) was a stained glass artist and painter perhaps best known for his Panama Canal murals .
Gustav Steinbrecht ( 1808 - -1885 ) is considered one of the masters of dressage .
Henry Grey , 1st Duke of Kent , KG PC ( 1671 -- 5 June 1740 ) was a British politician and courtier .
Maurice Christopher Hollis , known as Christopher Hollis ( 2 December 1902 -- 5 May 1977 ) was a British schoolmaster , university teacher , author and Conservative politician .
Norman Hampson ( 8 April 1922 in Manchester , England -- 8 July 2011 in York ) was the Professor of History at the University of York from 1974 to 1989 .
Roland Godin ( 11 October 1926 -- 22 June 2009 ) was a Ralliement créditiste and Social Credit party member of the Canadian House of Commons .
Johann Rudolf , Count Chotek of Chotkow and Wognin ( German : Johann Nepomuk Rudolph Graf Chotek von Chotkow und Wognin ; 18 May 1748 -- 26 August 1824 ) was an Austrian finance minister and Government President ( Gubernialpräsident ) in the Kingdom of Bohemia .
Liu Dongsheng ( Chinese : 劉東生 , 刘东生 ; 1917 - -2008 ) was a Chinese geologist and archaeologist .
Brian Morgan Edwards ( August 1934 -- December 2002 ) was an expert computer salesman , a prominent supporter of Plaid Cymru and a Welsh businessman who sponsored the first Welsh - language recording studio for popular music .
Benjamín Herrera ( 1853 - 1924 ) was a Colombian politician and general .
Raden Agustinus Suhardi ( 1899 - -1988 ) was a professor at Gadjah Mada University and first Agrarian Minister of Indonesia .
The Hero of the Hour is a 1917 American silent Western film directed by Raymond Wells .
Broken Vessels is a 1998 medical drama film directed by Scott Ziehl and written by Ziehl along with David Baer and John McMahon .
No Trees in the Street is a 1959 British crime thriller directed by J. Lee Thompson and written by Ted Willis , from his 1948 stage play of the same name .
Chandamama Kathalu Volume 1 is a 2014 Telugu , anthology film directed by Praveen Sattaru and produced by Chanakya Bhooneti .

I Love You , Baby is a 2000 German action thriller movie directed by Nick Lyon with Jasmin Gerat , Mark Keller , Maximilian Schell and Burkhard Driest in the lead .

Raattinam is a 2012 Tamil romantic drama film , directed by K.S.Thangasamy , starring Laguparan and Swathy .

The Fire Patrol is surviving 1924 silent film melodrama directed by Hunt Stromberg and starring Anna Q. Nilsson .
Priests Ćira and Spira ( Serbo - Croatian : ' ' Pop Ćira i pop Spira '' ) is a 1957 Yugoslav film directed by Soja Jovanović .

Anybody 's War is a 1930 American Pre - Code comedy film directed by Richard Wallace and written by Lloyd Corrigan , Hector Turnbull and Walter Weems .
The Paper Wedding ( French : Les noces de papier ) is a 1989 made for television Canadian film directed by Michel Brault , screenplay by Jefferson Lewis .
Jagadeka Veeruni Katha ( Telugu : జగదేకవీరుని కధ ) is a 1961 Telugu Drama film directed and produced by Kadiri Venkata Reddy under the banner of Vijaya Pictures .
Kati Patang ( Cut Kite ) is an 1970 Indian film produced and directed by Shakti Samanta .
Swarg ( Hindi : स्वर्ग , Urdu : سورگ , translation : Heaven ) is a 1990 Indian Bollywood film directed by David Dhawan , released on 18 May 1990 .

The Dealer from Amsterdam ( German : Der Trödler von Amsterdam ) is a 1925 German silent film directed by Victor Janson and starring Werner Krauss , Hilde Hildebrand and Harry Hardt .

Too Much Wife is a 1922 American comedy silent film directed by Thomas N. Heffron and written by Percy Heath and Lorna Moon .
The Leech ( Arabic : Shabab emraa‎ , also known as A Woman 's Youth ) is a 1956 Egyptian drama film directed by Salah Abu Seif .
Hare Splitter is a 1948 Warner Bros. Merrie Melodies animated short directed by Friz Freleng .
The Muslims Are Coming ! is a 2013 American comedy documentary film co - directed and co - starring Negin Farsad and Dean Obeidallah .
The Miner 's Curse , or the Bush Wedding is a 1911 Australian silent film directed by Alfred Rolfe set during the Australian Gold Rush .
Le Guignolo is a 1980 French - Italian comedy film directed by Georges Lautner .
Tub Girls is a 1967 American avant garde film directed by Andy Warhol .
Prípad Barnabáš Kos ( The Case of Barnabáš Kos ) is a 1964 Czechoslovak film directed by Peter Solan .
Srabon Megher Din ( Bengali : শ্রাবন মেঘের দিন - English : A Rainy Day of the Month Srabon ) is a Bangladeshi drama film based on the Novel of Humayun Ahmed .
Der alte und der junge König ( The Old and the Young King ) is a German historical film by Hans Steinhoff , made under Nazi rule in 1935 .
The Young and Prodigious T.S. Spivet is a 2013 Franco - Canadian - Australian adventure drama film directed by Jean - Pierre Jeunet and co - written with Guillaume Laurant , based on the book The Selected Works of T.S. Spivet , written by Reif Larsen .
Sri Anjaneyam(Telugu : శ్రీ ఆంజనేయం ) is a Telugu film directed and produced by Krishna Vamsi .

The Flicker is a 1966 experimental film by Tony Conrad .
Roll , Freddy , Roll ! is a 1974 American TV film directed by Bill Persky .
The Adventures of Jane Arden is a 1939 American crime film directed by Terry O. Morse and written by Vincent Sherman , Lawrence Kimble and Charles W. Curran .

Inside Fighting China is a 1941 Canadian short documentary film directed by Stuart Legg , and narrated by Lorne Greene .
I Dream Too Much is a 1935 romantic comedy film directed by John Cromwell .

Speed Cross is a 1980 Italian crime - action film directed by Stelvio Massi .
Dangerous Twins is a 2004 Nigerian drama film produced by Tade Ogidan , written and directed by Niji Akanni .
Earth vs. the Spider ( also known as The Spider and Earth vs. the Giant Spider ) is a 1958 American black - and - white science fiction - horror film produced and directed by Bert I. Gordon , who also wrote the story , upon which the screenplay by George Worthing Yates and Laszlo Gorog is based .
Two Tickets to Broadway is a 1951 American Technicolor musical film directed by James V. Kern and filmed on the RKO Forty Acres backlot .
Western Heritage is a 1948 American Western directed by Wallace Grissell .
Mystery , Alaska is a 1999 comedy - drama film directed by Jay Roach about an amateur ice hockey team , from the fictional small - town of Mystery , that plays an exhibition game against the New York Rangers of the National Hockey League .
Hasida Hebbuli ( Kannada : ಹಸಿದ ಹೆಬ್ಬುಲಿ ) is a 1983 Indian Kannada film , directed by S. A. Chandrasekhar and produced by Venkataram .
A Woman for 24 Hours ( German : Die Frau für 24 Stunden ) is a 1925 German silent drama film directed by Reinhold Schünzel and starring Lotte Neumann , Harry Liedtke and Kurt Vespermann .
Meet Dr. Christian is a 1939 American film directed by Bernard Vorhaus , the first of six films in the Dr. Christian series .
AGO Flugzeugwerke was a German aircraft manufacturing company from 1911 until 1945 .
The Electorate of Bavaria ( German : Kurfürstentum Bayern ) was an independent hereditary electorate of the Holy Roman Empire from 1623 to 1806 , when it was succeeded by the Kingdom of Bavaria .
In 1969 , it was divided in two new universities : the University of Rennes 1 the University of Rennes 2 --
In 1938 , under intense pressure of the Nazis ' Aryanization policy , Mendelssohn & Co. were forced to hand over their assets to Deutsche Bank , and eventually to shut down .
The North American Football Confederation was founded in 1946 and a forerunner to the CONCACAF as the governing body of football in North America until 1961 , when it merged with the Confederación Centroamericana y del Caribe de Fútbol ( CCCF ) to form CONCACAF .
The Arbeitsrat für Kunst ( German : ' Workers council for art ' or ' Art Soviet ' ) was a union of architects , painters , sculptors and art writers , who were based in Berlin from 1918 to 1921 .
The County of Artois ( French : comté d'Artois , Dutch : graafschap Artesië ) was an historic province of the Kingdom of France , held by the Dukes of Burgundy from 1384 until 1477/82 , and a state of the Holy Roman Empire from 1493 until 1659 .
The Central Finland Province ( Finnish : Keski - Suomen lääni , Swedish : Mellersta Finlands län ) was a province of Finland from 1960 to 1997 .
In 1991 North Carolina National Bank acquired C&S / Sovran Corp. and took the new name , NationsBank .
The Zoological Garden of Hamburg ( German : Zoologischer Garten zu Hamburg ) was a zoo in Hamburg , Germany that operated from 1863 until 1930 .
The Esculapeus was a British automobile manufactured for one year only , 1902 .
The Hilfspolizei ( abbreviated Hipo ; literally : auxiliary police ) was a short - lived auxiliary police force in Nazi Germany in 1933 .
Thomas Cook AG was the parent company of Thomas Cook UK & Ireland , Condor Airlines and other such subsidiaries until 12 February 2007 when it merged with MyTravel Group PLC . The new combined company was named Thomas Cook Group plc and was listed on the London Stock Exchange .
JMT Records ( an acronym of Jazz Music Today ) was a German record label , based in Munich and founded by producer Stefan F. Winter , that specialised in contemporary jazz and operated from 1985 until 1995 .
The Taifa of Constantina and Hornachuelos was a medieval taifa kingdom that existed , in what is now southern Spain , from around 1143 to 1150 when it was conquered by the Almohads .
The Providence Grays were a Major League Baseball team based in Providence , Rhode Island who played in the National League from 1878 until 1885 .
The Avonside Engine Company was a locomotive manufacturer in Avon Street , St. Philip 's , Bristol , England between 1864 and 1934 .
The World Badminton Federation is a former badminton organization , it was founded in February 1978 and ceased its operation on May 26 , 1981 after it merged with the International Badminton Federation ( now known as Badminton World Federation or BWF ) .
Transavia Corporation was an Australian aircraft manufacturer active between 1965 and 1985 .
Mirrorsoft was bought by Acclaim Entertainment in 1992 , the year following Maxwell 's death .
Eretnids ( Turkish plural ; Eretnaoğulları ) was an Anatolian beylik that succeeded the Ilkhanid governors in Anatolia and that ruled in a large region extending between Caesarea ( Kayseri ) , Sebastea ( Sivas ) and Amaseia ( Amasya ) in Central Anatolia between 1328 - -1381 .
Plymouth Colony ( sometimes New Plymouth , or Plymouth Bay Colony ) was an English colonial venture in North America from 1620 to 1691 .
Webvan was an online `` credit and delivery '' grocery business that went bankrupt in 2001 .
The London Passenger Transport Board ( LPTB ) was the organisation responsible for local public transport in London , UK , and its environs from 1933 to 1948 .
Togoland was a German protectorate in West Africa from 1884 to 1914 , encompassing what is now the nation of Togo and most of what is now the Volta Region of Ghana .
The Republic of Maryland ( also known as the Independent State of Maryland ) was a small nation which existed from 1854 to 1857 , when it was merged into what is now Liberia .
The Frankford Yellow Jackets were a professional American football team , part of the National Football League from 1924 to 1931 , though its origin dates back to as early as 1899 with the Frankford Athletic Association .
ALM Antillean Airlines ( Dutch : Antilliaanse Luchtvaart Maatschappij ) was the main airline of the Netherlands Antilles between its foundation in 1964 and its shut - down in 2001 , operating out of Aruba , Bonaire , and Curaçao .
The Montoneros were effectively finished off by 1977 , although their `` Special Forces '' did fight on until 1981 .
Włocławek Voivodeship ( Polish : województwo włocławskie ) was a unit of administrative division and local government in Poland in years 1975 - -1998 , superseded by Kuyavian - Pomeranian Voivodeship .
FC Bârlad was a Romanian professional football club from Bârlad , Vaslui County , Romania , founded in 2005 and dissolved in 2009 .
Warner P. Woodworth is a professor in the Department of Organizations Leadership and Strategy in the Marriott School of Management at Brigham Young University ( BYU ) .
Nicholas J. Belkin is a professor at the School of Communication and Information at Rutgers University .
Sarah Falkland is a British television journalist , working as a reporter and newsreader for BBC Midlands Today for the West Midlands Region .
Valentine Snow ( 1685 - -1759 ) was the trumpeter for George Frideric Handel .
